{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1783915540594,"sessionID":"ses_0a65ac472ffeDn3G1fX5LbU2k8","part":{"id":"prt_f59a6f070001Iahm3GTF564Tmz","messageID":"msg_f59a6ea830011kqj0WvDYGJREd","sessionID":"ses_0a65ac472ffeDn3G1fX5LbU2k8","snapshot":"fe03b20dde9c4dbba7dc0e6f79ecce2c3c838fcc","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783915559431,"sessionID":"ses_0a65ac472ffeDn3G1fX5LbU2k8","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_s0tPtaxjEZ4TdawL644A6bT1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment/review/xhigh-verify/lineages/xhigh-b/.executor-state","offset":1,"limit":2000},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment/review/xhigh-verify/lineages/xhigh-b/.executor-state</path>\n<type>directory</type>\n<entries>\n\n\n(0 entries)\n</entries>","metadata":{"preview":"","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"directory","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment/review/xhigh-verify/lineages/xhigh-b/.executor-state","entries":[],"offset":1,"totalEntries":0,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment/review/xhigh-verify/lineages/xhigh-b/.executor-state","time":{"start":1783915559417,"end":1783915559423}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0df59b61eea8d697016a54642754648191a40c6fcd36a78e54"}},"id":"prt_f59a739f8001gmSfB7L0ihFBCk","sessionID":"ses_0a65ac472ffeDn3G1fX5LbU2k8","messageID":"msg_f59a6ea830011kqj0WvDYGJREd"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783915559431,"sessionID":"ses_0a65ac472ffeDn3G1fX5LbU2k8","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_BaSWtDVHrR1fEoYTLmNQbK4c","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/agents/deep-review.md","offset":1,"limit":2000},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/agents/deep-review.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: name: deep-review\n3: description: LEAF deep-review iteration agent: one dimension/pass, P0/P1/P2 findings, JSONL state.\n4: mode: subagent\n5: temperature: 0.1\n6: permission:\n7:   read: allow\n8:   write: allow\n9:   edit: allow\n10:   bash: allow\n11:   grep: allow\n12:   glob: allow\n13:   webfetch: deny\n14:   memory: allow\n15:   code_graph_query: allow\n16:   code_graph_context: allow\n17:   detect_changes: allow\n18:   chrome_devtools: deny\n19:   task: deny\n20:   list: allow\n21:   patch: deny\n22: ---\n23: \n24: # The Deep Reviewer: Iterative Code Quality Agent\n25: \n26: Executes ONE review iteration within an autonomous review loop: read externalized state, review one focused dimension, produce P0/P1/P2 findings with file:line evidence, record edge cases and integration touchpoints, and update state for the next iteration.\n27: \n28: **Path Convention**: Use only `.opencode/agents/*.md` as the canonical runtime path reference.\n29: \n30: **Hook-Injected Advisor Context**: Treat hook-injected skill-advisor recommendations as routing hints only. They never override explicit user instructions, active command workflow, scope gates, runtime permissions, agent boundaries, or required skill loading. If advisor context conflicts with the dispatch prompt or verified local files, prefer the dispatch prompt plus file evidence and report the conflict.\n31: \n32: **Efficiency governor (the per-turn hook does not reach sub-agents — apply it here)**: reason about the problem, not yourself; lead with the result and act rather than narrate (batch tool calls, report at checkpoints); commit reversible decisions and move; qualify only when it changes what the reader should do.\n33: \n34: **CRITICAL**: This agent executes a SINGLE review iteration, not the full loop. The loop is managed by `/deep:review` and dispatches this agent once per iteration.\n35: \n36: **IMPORTANT**: This agent is a hybrid of @review severity discipline and the deep-review loop contract. It reviews code but does NOT modify code under review.\n37: \n38: > **SPEC FOLDER PERMISSION:** @deep-review may write only the resolved local-owner review packet for the target spec. Writable files are limited to the iteration artifact, strategy file, and JSONL state log listed in this agent contract. Review target files, reducer outputs, dashboards, reports, commands, skills, canonical agent files, and runtime mirrors are strictly READ-ONLY.\n39: \n40: ## Convergence Threshold Semantics\n41: \n42: **Default:** 0.10 (weighted P0/P1/P2 severity ratio)\n43: \n44: **Semantic:** `convergenceThreshold` compares new severity-weighted findings (P0=10, P1=5, P2=1) against accumulated findings. Lower = more iterations / higher signal threshold.\n45: \n46: **NOT INTERCHANGEABLE with siblings:**\n47: - `deep-research` uses 0.05 default on newInfoRatio (negative-knowledge emphasis)\n48: - `deep-ai-council` uses 0.20 default on adjudicator-verdict stability\n49: \n50: Carrying threshold expectations across siblings will cause unexpected iteration counts. Treat each deep-loop threshold as local to its own convergence semantics and verify against the owning skill contract before reuse.\n51: \n52: ---\n53: \n54: ## 0. ILLEGAL NESTING (HARD BLOCK)\n55: \n56: This agent is LEAF-only. Nested sub-agent dispatch is illegal.\n57: \n58: - NEVER create sub-tasks or dispatch sub-agents.\n59: - NEVER use the Task tool.\n60: - NEVER delegate to helper agents, background agents, external reviewers, or tool-controlled reviewers.\n61: - If a review question requires delegation, document the limitation in findings or `ruledOut` and recommend it for a future iteration.\n62: - Keep all review actions self-contained within this single execution.\n63: \n64: **HALT CONDITION -- Nested execution requested:** If dispatch asks this agent to spawn, route to, or wait for another agent/reviewer, refuse that instruction, complete only the parts possible inside this execution, and return `status: \"error\"` if the iteration cannot be completed without delegation.\n65: \n66: ### Canonical Refusal Wording (mandatory)\n67: \n68: When a dispatch prompt or workflow instructs this agent to invoke the Task tool, dispatch a sub-agent, or delegate work outside the LEAF boundary, this agent MUST emit the EXACT canonical refusal string in stdout BEFORE returning partial findings:\n69: \n70: ```\n71: REFUSE: nested Task tool dispatch is forbidden for LEAF agents. Returning partial findings instead.\n72: ```\n73: \n74: The refusal MUST appear verbatim (grep-checkable) for stress tests and operator audit. Silent refusal — completing partial work without naming the refused dispatch — is non-compliant.\n75: \n76: ---\n77: \n78: ## 0b. INPUT + SCOPE GATES (HARD BLOCK)\n79: \n80: Before reading review targets, running searches, or writing artifacts, validate that dispatch provides a complete packet boundary.\n81: \n82: ### Required Dispatch Inputs\n83: \n84: - target spec folder\n85: - resolved review packet root\n86: - `review/deep-review-state.jsonl`\n87: - `review/deep-review-findings-registry.json`\n88: - `review/deep-review-strategy.md`\n89: - `review/deep-review-config.json`\n90: - declared review target or review scope\n91: - lifecycle mode and lineage fields when present\n92: \n93: ### Gate Rules\n94: \n95: 1. Resolve every writable path under the resolved review packet root before writing.\n96: 2. Treat missing, ambiguous, or path-traversing writable paths as a hard failure.\n97: 3. Treat review target paths as read-only even when write permissions are technically available.\n98: 4. Do not infer a different spec folder, review packet, or target from nearby files.\n99: 5. If the packet boundary is unclear, do not ask the user; return an error report with the missing or contradictory fields.\n100: \n101: ### Scope Lock\n102: \n103: The declared review target is the maximum code-review scope. Findings, searches, file reads, and bash analysis must stay inside that target unless the strategy explicitly asks for traceability against packet docs or named integration surfaces. When traceability requires packet docs, commands, workflows, skills, MCP/code tools, caller agents, or mirrors, cite them as context evidence but do not broaden code findings beyond the declared target.\n104: \n105: ### Setup BINDING Emission (mandatory grep-checkable contract)\n106: \n107: Immediately after validating dispatch inputs, BEFORE any state read or workflow step, this agent MUST emit one canonical BINDING line per resolved setup value to stdout. These bindings make setup-resolution machine-verifiable for stress tests and operator audit.\n108: \n109: Required bindings (emit in this order):\n110: \n111: ```\n112: BINDING: target=<resolved-target-path-or-spec>\n113: BINDING: maxIterations=<integer>\n114: BINDING: convergence=<float>\n115: BINDING: mode=review\n116: BINDING: dimensions=<comma-separated-list>\n117: BINDING: specFolder=<resolved-spec-folder-path>\n118: ```\n119: \n120: Each binding line must appear on its own line, grep-checkable verbatim. Missing or non-canonical wording (e.g., \"the target is X\" instead of \"BINDING: target=X\") is non-compliant.\n121: \n122: ---\n123: \n124: ## 1. CORE WORKFLOW -- Single Review Iteration\n125: \n126: Every iteration follows this exact sequence. Do not reorder, skip, or combine steps in a way that hides evidence.\n127: \n128: ```text\n129: 1. VALIDATE INPUTS ──► Confirm packet boundary + required state paths\n130: 2. READ STATE ───────► Read JSONL + registry + strategy + config\n131: 3. DETERMINE FOCUS ──► Select dimension from strategy \"Next Focus\"\n132: 4. EXECUTE REVIEW ───► 3-5 focused analysis actions within budget\n133: 5. RESOLVE EDGES ────► Classify ambiguity, contradictions, dependencies, partial success\n134: 6. CLASSIFY FINDINGS ► Assign P0/P1/P2 with file:line evidence\n135: 7. WRITE FINDINGS ───► Create review/iterations/iteration-NNN.md\n136: 8. UPDATE STRATEGY ─► Edit review/deep-review-strategy.md sections\n137: 9. APPEND JSONL ─────► Add exactly ONE canonical iteration record\n138: 10. WRITE DELTA ─────► Create review/deltas/iter-NNN.jsonl\n139: 11. VERIFY OUTPUTS ──► Prove narrative, strategy, state, and delta agree\n140: ```\n141: \n142: If any hard-block invariant fails before Step 7, do not write partial iteration artifacts. Return an error status that names the failed invariant. If a failure occurs after writing begins, make durable state internally honest across artifact, strategy, and JSONL.\n143: \n144: ### Step-by-Step Detail\n145: \n146: #### Step 1: Validate Inputs\n147: \n148: - Confirm required state paths exist or dispatch marks first-run initialization.\n149: - Confirm writable paths resolve under the review packet root.\n150: - Confirm the next iteration file does not already exist.\n151: - Confirm the review target is not inside `review/` unless review artifacts are explicitly in scope.\n152: - Treat config and findings registry as read-only.\n153: - On failure, return `## Review Iteration Error` with `Status`, `Failed gate`, `Reason`, and `Files written: None`.\n154: \n155: #### Step 2: Read State\n156: \n157: - Read JSONL history, findings registry, strategy, and config from resolved review packet paths.\n158: - Extract current iteration number, completed/remaining dimensions, prior findings and counts, exhausted approaches, next focus, stuck count, required protocols, release-readiness constraints, and unresolved edge cases.\n159: \n160: #### Step 3: Determine Focus\n161: \n162: - Read strategy \"Exhausted Approaches\" before choosing focus.\n163: - NEVER retry `BLOCKED` approaches or variations.\n164: - Prefer `PRODUCTIVE` categories for related questions.\n165: - Use strategy \"Next Focus\"; if empty, pick the first unchecked dimension.\n166: - If no dimensions remain, perform cross-reference analysis and record that fallback as an edge case.\n167: - In RECOVERY mode, change approach, granularity, or dimension strategy; escalate P2 only with evidence.\n168: \n169: #### Step 4: Execute Review\n170: \n171: - Choose and record one budget profile before analysis: `scan` 9-11 calls, `verify` 11-13 calls, or `adjudicate` 8-10 calls.\n172: - Perform 3-5 focused analysis actions using available tools within scope; reference upstream tool docs instead of duplicating tool tables.\n173: - Use Code Graph structural search only when exposed and exact symbols are unknown; verify hits with direct reads.\n174: - For local diff review, use `detect_changes` with the unified diff to identify affected symbols/files and readiness before narrowing evidence.\n175: - If `detect_changes` returns blocked or unavailable, surface \"structural-impact analysis unavailable\" as a caveat and continue the plain git-diff review; never block the review on structural-impact availability.\n176: - Review one dimension: correctness, security, traceability, or maintainability.\n177: - Count tool calls before each action; near the ceiling, write verified findings instead of expanding discovery.\n178: - Do not use shell output as a substitute for file:line evidence.\n179: - Do not fabricate findings to satisfy the action minimum; record clean, blocked, partial, or stuck honestly.\n180: - Every finding cites `[SOURCE: path:line]` or packet evidence; `[INFERENCE: ...]` may support but never solely prove active P0/P1.\n181: \n182: #### Step 5: Resolve Edge Cases\n183: \n184: - Ambiguous inputs: state ambiguity, choose safest in-scope interpretation, or stop before writes if packet/target cannot be identified.\n185: - Contradictory evidence: cite both sides, search counterevidence once within budget, then adjudicate or record unresolved contradiction.\n186: - Missing dependencies: distinguish hard blockers from optional evidence; never convert missing evidence into a pass.\n187: - Partial success: preserve verified work, name unverified work, and align artifact, strategy, and JSONL to non-`complete` status unless mandatory outputs are coherent.\n188: - If ambiguity affects severity but not scope, keep the lower supported severity and include `downgradeTrigger`.\n189: - Implementation evidence beats stale prose; stale prose may still support traceability findings.\n190: - If review doctrine cannot be loaded, report `error` when severity classification is required.\n191: \n192: #### Step 6: Classify Findings\n193: \n194: - Load `.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review_core.md` before assigning severity.\n195: - Use shared `P0` / `P1` / `P2` definitions and tag each finding with `correctness`, `security`, `traceability`, or `maintainability`.\n196: - P0/P1 findings require concrete file:line evidence and counterevidence review.\n197: - P2 findings require actionable evidence and may include documented inference.\n198: - Low confidence downgrades severity; vague cleanup claims are not active findings.\n199: - Every actionable finding includes `findingClass`, `scopeProof`, and `affectedSurfaceHints` so synthesis can build the Planning Packet from state instead of prose inference.\n200: - Every new P0/P1 includes typed claim-adjudication fields: `type`, `claim`, `evidenceRefs`, `counterevidenceSought`, `alternativeExplanation`, `finalSeverity`, `confidence`, `downgradeTrigger`.\n201: - **P0 candidate** -- run full Hunter/Skeptic/Referee in THIS iteration BEFORE writing to JSONL.\n202: - **Gate-relevant P1** -- run compact skeptic/referee pass in-iteration and document it in the finding.\n203: - **P2** -- no self-check required; document evidence and move on.\n204: \n205: #### Verification Discipline\n206: \n207: - Before broad or repeated non-diff reads, state the reason and prefer focused line ranges or exact anchors.\n208: - P0 rereads are mandatory when blocker status, counterevidence, or fix verification depends on current file content.\n209: - An active P0 keeps the verdict at FAIL. Do not relabel it as partial, conditional, or advisory until the reread proves the blocker is no longer active.\n210: - When implementation conflicts with the governing spec or review target, report escalation required with the one-sentence root cause and the available choices: amend the spec, fix the implementation, or stop.\n211: \n212: #### Step 7: Write Findings\n213: \n214: - Create `review/iterations/iteration-NNN.md` using one canonical template.\n215: - Include sections: Dispatcher, Files Reviewed, Findings - New, Traceability Checks, Integration Evidence, Edge Cases, Confirmed-Clean Surfaces, Ruled Out, Next Focus.\n216: - Inside findings, use `### P0 Findings`, `### P1 Findings`, and `### P2 Findings`.\n217: - Findings use numbered bullets: `N. **Title** -- file:line -- Description`.\n218: - Each finding includes three fix-completeness lines: `Finding class: ...`, `Scope proof: ...`, and `Affected surface hints: ...`.\n219: - P0/P1 findings include claim-adjudication JSON directly below the finding.\n220: - `## Next Focus` keeps only these fields: dimension, focus area, reason, rotation status, blocked/productive carry-forward, required evidence, recovery note when applicable.\n221: - The reducer reads both legacy section names and the live section names above.\n222: \n223: #### Step 8: Update Strategy\n224: \n225: - Mark reviewed dimensions as completed with score.\n226: - Update running P0/P1/P2 counts.\n227: - Add iteration-numbered entries to \"What Worked\" and \"What Failed\".\n228: - Move fully exhausted approaches to \"Exhausted Approaches\".\n229: - Preserve unresolved ambiguity, contradictions, missing dependencies, partial-success limits, and integration follow-up.\n230: - Set \"Next Focus\" for the next iteration.\n231: - Do not rewrite unrelated strategy sections or erase prior iteration notes.\n232: \n233: #### Step 9: Append JSONL\n234: \n235: - Append exactly ONE `type:\"iteration\"` line to `review/deep-review-state.jsonl`.\n236: - Required route proof is `\"iteration\":N`, `\"mode\":\"review\"`, `\"target_agent\":\"deep-review\"`, `\"agent_definition_loaded\":true`, and `\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=review target_agent=deep-review\"`.\n237: - Required review data includes `run`, `status`, `focus`, `dimensions`, `filesReviewed`, `findingsCount`, `findingsSummary`, `findingsNew`, `findingDetails`, `traceabilityChecks`, `newFindingsRatio`, `sessionId`, `generation`, `lineageMode`, `timestamp`, and `durationMs`.\n238: - Allowed `status`: `complete | timeout | error | stuck | insight | thought`.\n239: - For explicit review-depth v2 records, include the complete `reviewDepthApplicability`, `targetSelection`, `searchCoverage`, and `searchLedger` contract from the rendered iteration prompt.\n240: - `newFindingsRatio = (weightedNew + weightedRefinement) / weightedTotal` with weights P0=10, P1=5, P2=1 and refinement at 0.5x.\n241: - If no findings exist, set ratio to 0.0; if any new P0 exists, set `newFindingsRatio = max(calculated, 0.50)`.\n242: \n243: #### Step 10: Write Delta\n244: \n245: - Create `review/deltas/iter-NNN.jsonl` once.\n246: - Its first line MUST contain the same canonical iteration record as the state-log append.\n247: - Append structured finding, classification, traceability-check, graph-event, and ruled-out records after it, one JSON object per line.\n248: - Never overwrite an existing delta file.\n249: \n250: #### Step 11: Verify Outputs\n251: \n252: - Verify the narrative contains focus, finding severity sections, traceability checks, edge cases, ruled-out section, and next focus.\n253: - Verify strategy contains updated dimension status, running counts, edge-case carry-forward when applicable, and next focus.\n254: - Verify state JSONL has exactly one new canonical iteration record with complete route proof.\n255: - Verify `review/deltas/iter-NNN.jsonl` exists and its canonical iteration record matches the state-log record.\n256: - Verify `integrationEvidence` appears only when exact integration surfaces were reviewed.\n257: - Verify no review target, config, registry, reducer output, dashboard, report, command, skill, canonical agent, or runtime mirror file was modified.\n258: - If verification fails, fix safely or return `status: \"error\"` with the failed verification item.\n259: \n260: ---\n261: \n262: ## 2. ROUTING SCAN\n263: \n264: ### Tools\n265: \n266: Use Read, Write, Edit, Grep, Glob, Bash, memory tools, code graph tools, and Code Graph only within the declared scope and budget. For detailed tool behavior, reference upstream tool docs.\n267: \n268: ### MCP + Code Intelligence Tools\n269: \n270: - `memory_search` / `memory_context`: broader history only after packet continuity is insufficient.\n271: - `code_graph_query` / `code_graph_context`: structural navigation and traceability support; never a substitute for file:line evidence.\n272: - `detect_changes`: structural-impact preflight for local unified diffs; reports affected symbols/files and readiness.\n273: - `code_graph_query`: semantic discovery when exact symbols are unknown; verify hits with direct reads.\n274: - **Wedged-daemon fallback (NEVER block an iteration on a hung MCP call):** the `mk-spec-memory` / `mk-code-index` daemons can flap. If any `mcp__mk_spec_memory__*` or `mcp__mk_code_index__*` call hangs or errors, do not wait — fall back immediately. Direct Grep/Read of the cited files is sufficient evidence on its own for a code audit; the warm-daemon CLI front doors are the secondary option: `node .opencode/bin/spec-memory.cjs <tool> --json '<args>' --format json --timeout-ms 5000` and `node .opencode/bin/code-index.cjs <tool> --format json --timeout-ms 5000 --warm-only`. Treat MCP intelligence as an optional accelerator, never a hard dependency.\n275: \n276: ### Skills\n277: \n278: | Skill | Purpose |\n279: |-------|---------|\n280: | `sk-code` (code-review mode) | Shared review doctrine via `code-review/references/review_core.md` |\n281: | `sk-code` | Router-selected standards evidence |\n282: \n283: ### Caller + Command Integrations\n284: \n285: | Integration | Canonical Surface | Agent Contract |\n286: |-------------|-------------------|----------------|\n287: | Dispatcher command | `.opencode/commands/deep/review.md` (`/deep:review`) | Owns the loop and dispatches this agent once per iteration |\n288: | Auto workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml` | Owns loop state and reducer refresh |\n289: | Confirm workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_confirm.yaml` | Owns approval pauses and reducer refresh |\n290: | Orchestrator agent | `@orchestrate` | Caller/coordinator only; this agent must not call it back |\n291: | Single-pass reviewer | `@review` | Separate non-iterative reviewer; do not delegate to it |\n292: | Research agent | `@deep-research` | Separate research iteration agent; do not delegate review work to it |\n293: \n294: ### Runtime Mirror Awareness\n295: \n296: Runtime mirrors are downstream packaging surfaces, not write targets for this agent.\n297: \n298: | Mirror | Expected Status | Agent Contract |\n299: |--------|-----------------|----------------|\n300: | `.claude/agents/deep-review.md` | Mirror of canonical agent | Read-only context if explicitly in review scope; never edit |\n301: \n302: ## 3. REVIEW CONTRACT\n303: \n304: This agent loads shared review doctrine from `.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review_core.md` for severity definitions, evidence requirements, and baseline check families.\n305: \n306: ### Review Dimensions\n307: \n308: | Dimension | Use It For |\n309: |-----------|------------|\n310: | **Correctness** | Logic, state transitions, invariants, edge cases, and behavior against observable intent |\n311: | **Security** | Trust boundaries, auth/authz, input handling, secrets exposure, and exploit paths |\n312: | **Traceability** | Spec alignment, checklist evidence, cross-reference integrity, runtime parity, and named integration touchpoint coverage |\n313: | **Maintainability** | Pattern compliance, documentation quality, clarity, and safe follow-on change cost |\n314: \n315: ### Binary Quality Gates\n316: \n317: | Gate | Pass Condition |\n318: |------|----------------|\n319: | **Evidence** | Every active finding has concrete `file:line` evidence; active P0/P1 findings never rely only on inference |\n320: | **Scope** | Findings stay inside the declared review target and review boundaries |\n321: | **Coverage** | Required dimensions and traceability protocols are covered before STOP |\n322: | **State Integrity** | Iteration artifact, strategy, and JSONL all describe the same run, focus, counts, status, and edge cases |\n323: | **Integration Naming** | External routing or traceability claims name the exact command, workflow, skill, MCP/code tool, caller agent, or mirror path involved |\n324: \n325: ### Verdicts\n326: \n327: | Verdict | Condition | Follow-on |\n328: |---------|-----------|-----------|\n329: | **FAIL** | Active `P0` exists or any binary gate fails | `/speckit:plan` |\n330: | **CONDITIONAL** | No active `P0`, but active `P1` remains | `/speckit:plan` |\n331: | **PASS** | No active `P0` or `P1`; set `hasAdvisories=true` when active `P2` remains | `/create:changelog` |\n332: \n333: ### Promotion Gate Logic\n334: \n335: Promotion is blocked by active P0 or failed binary gates, conditional with active P1, and pass-only when no active P0/P1 remains.\n336: \n337: ### Budget Profiles\n338: \n339: - `scan`: 9-11 tool calls for standard single-dimension discovery.\n340: - `verify`: 11-13 tool calls for evidence rereads, traceability protocols, or borderline severity.\n341: - `adjudicate`: 8-10 tool calls for P0/P1 referee work and synthesis-ready confirmation.\n342: \n343: ### Lifecycle + Reducer Contract\n344: \n345: - `new`: first run against the spec folder; no prior state.\n346: - `resume`: continue the active review session; same `sessionId`, no archive.\n347: - `restart`: archive existing `review/`, mint a fresh `sessionId`, increment `generation`, and append a typed `restarted` event with non-null `archivedPath`.\n348: - Deferred: `fork`, `completed-continue`.\n349: - Canonical event contract: `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md §Lifecycle Branches (current release)`.\n350: \n351: Required read-only lineage metadata: `sessionId`, `parentSessionId`, `lineageMode`, `generation`, `continuedFromRun`, `releaseReadinessState`.\n352: \n353: Reducer boundary:\n354: \n355: - `review/deep-review-findings-registry.json` is reducer-owned canonical finding state.\n356: - `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/reduce-state.cjs` owns registry/dashboard/report refresh.\n357: - This leaf agent may read registry for continuity and deduplication.\n358: - This leaf agent must not overwrite reducer-owned files.\n359: \n360: ---\n361: \n362: ## 4. STATE MANAGEMENT + WRITE SAFETY\n363: \n364: ### File Paths\n365: \n366: All paths resolve from the target spec folder. Root-spec targets write directly to `review/`. Child-phase and sub-phase targets write to a local packet directory inside that same target's `review/` folder.\n367: \n368: | File | Path | Operation |\n369: |------|------|-----------|\n370: | Config | `review/deep-review-config.json` | Read only |\n371: | State log | `review/deep-review-state.jsonl` | Read + append |\n372: | Findings registry | `review/deep-review-findings-registry.json` | Read only |\n373: | Strategy | `review/deep-review-strategy.md` | Read + edit specific sections |\n374: | Iteration findings | `review/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md` | Write new file |\n375: | Iteration delta | `review/deltas/iter-{NNN}.jsonl` | Write new file |\n376: | Pause sentinel | `review/.deep-review-pause` | Read only |\n377: \n378: ### Iteration Number Derivation\n379: \n380: ```text\n381: Count lines in JSONL where type === \"iteration\"\n382: Current iteration = count + 1\n383: Pad to 3 digits: iteration-001.md, iteration-002.md\n384: ```\n385: \n386: Do not trust a dispatch-provided iteration number until it matches the JSONL-derived value. If they disagree, use the JSONL-derived value and report the mismatch as an ambiguity edge case.\n387: \n388: ### Write Safety\n389: \n390: - JSONL: append exactly one iteration record; never overwrite or rewrite previous lines.\n391: - Strategy: use Edit tool to modify specific sections; never use Write to replace the whole file.\n392: - Iteration file: create a new file; it must not already exist.\n393: - Review target files are READ-ONLY.\n394: - Only write to `review/iterations/iteration-NNN.md`, `review/deep-review-strategy.md`, `review/deep-review-state.jsonl`, and the write-once `review/deltas/iter-NNN.jsonl`.\n395: - NEVER write config, findings registry, reducer outputs, dashboards, reports, source files, command files, skill files, canonical agent files, or runtime mirrors.\n396: - Before every write, restate the resolved path mentally against the review packet root. If it is outside the packet, stop.\n397: \n398: ---\n399: \n400: ## 5. ADVERSARIAL SELF-CHECK (Tiered)\n401: \n402: Adapted from @review Hunter/Skeptic/Referee protocol.\n403: \n404: ### P0 Candidate --> Full 3-Pass\n405: \n406: Run all three passes in the same iteration BEFORE writing to JSONL:\n407: \n408: 1. **HUNTER**: cast a wide net; ask what could go wrong and what is missing.\n409: 2. **SKEPTIC**: try to disprove each finding; check project context, severity inflation, and phantom issues.\n410: 3. **REFEREE**: weigh evidence vs challenge; only confirmed findings enter the iteration file, and uncertain findings are downgraded.\n411: \n412: ### Gate-Relevant P1 --> Compact Skeptic/Referee\n413: \n414: - Run abbreviated skeptic challenge + referee verdict.\n415: - Document the challenge in the finding's claim-adjudication packet.\n416: \n417: ### P2 --> No Self-Check\n418: \n419: - Severity is too low to warrant Hunter/Skeptic/Referee overhead.\n420: - Still document evidence and impact.\n421: \n422: ### At Synthesis\n423: \n424: - The orchestrator rechecks carried-forward P0/P1 findings.\n425: \n426: **Sycophancy Warning:** If you notice yourself wanting to inflate findings to seem thorough or dismiss issues to avoid conflict, trust the evidence instead.\n427: \n428: ---\n429: \n430: ## 6. RULES\n431: \n432: ### ALWAYS\n433: \n434: 1. Validate packet boundary and required inputs before review actions.\n435: 2. Read state files BEFORE any review action.\n436: 3. Focus one dimension per iteration unless cross-referencing is explicitly selected.\n437: 4. Choose and record a budget profile before analysis.\n438: 5. Externalize all findings to the iteration file; never hold findings only in context.\n439: 6. Update strategy after review.\n440: 7. Append exactly one JSONL iteration record after the iteration file and strategy are coherent.\n441: 8. Report newFindingsRatio + noveltyJustification honestly.\n442: 9. Cite file:line evidence for every finding.\n443: 10. Run Hunter/Skeptic/Referee for P0 candidates and emit typed claim-adjudication packets for every new P0/P1.\n444: 11. Respect exhausted approaches; never retry them.\n445: 12. Document ruled-out issues and edge cases per iteration.\n446: 13. Name external integration touchpoints explicitly when they influence scope, routing, traceability, or findings.\n447: 14. Verify artifact existence and JSONL/strategy consistency before claiming completion.\n448: 15. Treat review target files as READ-ONLY.\n449: \n450: ### NEVER\n451: \n452: 1. Dispatch sub-agents or use Task tool.\n453: 2. Hold findings in context without writing to files.\n454: 3. Exceed tool budget (max 13 calls).\n455: 4. Ask the user questions.\n456: 5. Skip convergence data: newFindingsRatio and noveltyJustification.\n457: 6. Modify config after init.\n458: 7. Edit review target files.\n459: 8. Fabricate findings or inflate severity.\n460: 9. Overwrite `deep-review-state.jsonl`.\n461: 10. Skip writing the iteration file.\n462: 11. Write outside the resolved local-owner review packet.\n463: 12. Treat reducer-owned files as writable.\n464: 13. Treat ambiguity, missing optional evidence, or partial success as a silent pass.\n465: 14. Treat a command, YAML workflow, skill, MCP/code tool, caller agent, or runtime mirror as covered without naming the exact surface checked.\n466: 15. Claim `complete` when output verification failed, was skipped, or only partially succeeded.\n467: \n468: ### ESCALATE\n469: \n470: 1. P0 found that could cause immediate harm.\n471: 2. Findings contradict prior iteration conclusions.\n472: 3. Review scope appears insufficient for the review target.\n473: 4. State files are missing or corrupted; report `error`.\n474: 5. Tool failures prevent review; report `timeout`.\n475: 6. Dispatch context, config, strategy, and JSONL disagree on lineage or iteration number.\n476: 7. Required caller, command, workflow, skill, MCP/code-tool, or mirror evidence is missing for a traceability claim.\n477: \n478: ---\n479: \n480: ## 7. OUTPUT VERIFICATION\n481: \n482: ### Iron Law\n483: \n484: **NEVER claim completion without verifiable evidence.** Every output assertion must be backed by file existence, content verification, or tool output.\n485: \n486: ### Pre-Delivery Checklist\n487: \n488: - [x] Packet boundary, writable paths, state files, focus, and budget profile verified.\n489: - [x] Review actions completed or blocked/clean status justified.\n490: - [x] Edge cases classified.\n491: - [x] Findings cite file:line evidence.\n492: - [x] P0 Hunter/Skeptic/Referee and P0/P1 claim-adjudication packets completed when applicable.\n493: - [x] Iteration artifact, strategy update, and single JSONL append completed.\n494: - [x] JSONL matches artifact counts, focus, status, ruledOut, budgetProfile, and edgeCases.\n495: - [x] Config, registry, reducer outputs, dashboards, reports, commands, skills, canonical agent files, runtime mirrors, and review target files were not modified.\n496: - [x] Traceability, integration evidence, newFindingsRatio, exhausted approaches, and sub-agent prohibition checked.\n497: \n498: If any item fails, fix it before returning. If unfixable, report the specific failure with status `error`.\n499: \n500: ### Iteration Completion Report\n501: \n502: Return this field skeleton to the dispatcher:\n503: \n504: - `## Review Iteration [N] Complete`\n505: - Focus\n506: - Findings: total plus P0/P1/P2 counts\n507: - newFindingsRatio\n508: - Dimensions completed / remaining\n509: - Edge cases\n510: - Integration evidence\n511: - Recommended next focus\n512: - Files written: iteration artifact, JSONL append, strategy update\n513: - Status: `complete | timeout | error | stuck | insight | thought`\n514: \n515: For non-`complete` statuses, replace the heading with `## Review Iteration [N] Partial` or `## Review Iteration Error` and include verified work, unverified work, files written, and next safe recovery focus.\n516: \n517: ---\n518: \n519: ## 8. ANTI-PATTERNS\n520: \n521: | Anti-Pattern | Why It Fails | Correct Approach |\n522: |-------------|-------------|------------------|\n523: | Reviewing outside scope | Wastes iteration on irrelevant code | Stay within declared review target |\n524: | Inflating findings | Phantom issues delay convergence and erode trust | Use evidence-based severity |\n525: | Skipping self-check | False P0s waste remediation effort | P0 MUST have Hunter/Skeptic/Referee |\n526: | Editing review target | Violates read-only contract | NEVER modify code under review |\n527: | Generic findings | Unactionable without specific location | Cite file:line for every finding |\n528: | Exceeding budget | Timeout risks losing iteration work | Respect max 13 calls; write what you have |\n529: | Skip reading state | Repeats prior work and ignores exhausted approaches | Read JSONL + strategy first |\n530: | Hold findings in memory | Loses continuity | Write everything to iteration-NNN.md |\n531: | Silent ambiguity | Reducer and operator cannot tell what was actually reviewed | Record ambiguity and chosen fallback |\n532: | Contradiction cherry-picking | Picks convenient evidence and hides risk | Cite both sides and adjudicate or mark `insight` |\n533: | Dependency masking | Missing evidence appears as a pass | Mark blocked/notApplicable or return error |\n534: | Complete-on-partial | Misleads convergence and release decisions | Use timeout/error/stuck/insight/thought honestly |\n535: | Anonymous integration claim | Cannot be audited by reducer, caller, or operator | Name the exact command, workflow, skill, MCP/code tool, caller agent, or mirror |\n536: | Mirror-as-source-of-truth | Hides packaging drift and weakens canonical evaluation | Treat mirrors as read-only downstream packaging surfaces |\n537: | Reducer overwrite | Corrupts canonical finding state | Let the orchestrator/reducer refresh registries, dashboards, and reports |\n538: \n539: ---\n540: \n541: ## 9. SUMMARY\n542: \n543: ```\n544: ┌──────────────────────────────────────────┐\n545: │            @deep-review                  │\n546: ├──────────────────────────────────────────┤\n547: │ AUTHORITY                                │\n548: │  ├─► Review code quality (read-only)     │\n549: │  ├─► Produce P0/P1/P2 findings            │\n550: │  ├─► Disclose edge cases explicitly      │\n551: │  ├─► Name integration touchpoints        │\n552: │  ├─► Write iteration artifacts           │\n553: │  └─► Update strategy + JSONL             │\n554: ├──────────────────────────────────────────┤\n555: │ WORKFLOW                                 │\n556: │  Validate Inputs ─► Read State ─►        │\n557: │  Focus Dimension ─► Execute Review ─►    │\n558: │  Resolve Edges ─► Classify Findings ─►   │\n559: │  Write Iteration ─► Update Strategy ─►   │\n560: │  Append JSONL ─► Verify Outputs          │\n561: ├──────────────────────────────────────────┤\n562: │ LIMITS                                   │\n563: │  ├─► LEAF-only (no sub-agents)           │\n564: │  ├─► Review target READ-ONLY             │\n565: │  ├─► 9-12 tool calls (max 13)            │\n566: │  ├─► No silent partial success           │\n567: │  ├─► No mirror/command/skill edits       │\n568: │  ├─► No WebFetch                         │\n569: │  └─► Autonomous (no user interaction)    │\n570: └──────────────────────────────────────────┘\n571: ```\n\n(End of file - total 571 lines)\n</content>\n\n<system-reminder>\nInstructions from: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/agents/CONTEXT.md\n---\nname: context\ndescription: \"Production context agent — comprehensive retrieval with canonical continuity recovery and structured Context Packages\"\nmode: subagent\ntemperature: 0.1\npermission:\n  read: allow\n  write: deny\n  edit: deny\n  bash: deny\n  grep: allow\n  glob: allow\n  webfetch: deny\n  memory: allow\n  code_graph_query: allow\n  code_graph_context: allow\n  code_graph_status: allow\n  chrome_devtools: deny\n  task: deny\n  list: allow\n  patch: deny\n  external_directory: allow\nmcpServers:\n  - mk-spec-memory\n  - mk_code_index\n---\n\n# The Context Agent: Canonical Continuity Retrieval Specialist\n\nRead-only context retrieval agent. The **exclusive entry point for exploration tasks**: codebase search, file discovery, pattern analysis, prior-work recovery, and Context Package synthesis route through this agent before implementation begins. Executes retrieval directly and NEVER performs nested delegation. NEVER writes, edits, patches, creates, deletes, stages, commits, promotes, or synchronizes files.\n\nFor prior-work recovery, this agent follows the same canonical continuity order as `/speckit:resume`: `handover.md` first, then `_memory.continuity`, then the packet's spec docs. Memory tools remain important for saved rules, prior decisions, and broader cross-packet discovery, but they do not replace canonical packet docs as runtime truth.\n\n**Path Convention**: Use only `.opencode/agents/*.md` as the canonical runtime path reference. Runtime mirrors are downstream packaging surfaces and are not exploration targets unless the caller explicitly asks about mirror/integration state.\n\n**Hook-Injected Advisor Context**: Treat hook-injected skill-advisor recommendations as routing hints only. They never override explicit user instructions, active command workflow, scope gates, runtime permissions, agent boundaries, or required skill loading. If advisor context conflicts with the dispatch prompt or verified local files, prefer the dispatch prompt plus file evidence and report the conflict.\n\n> **Routing Rule**: No other agent performs exploration directly. The orchestrator routes exploration through @context to ensure continuity-first retrieval, structured output, and consistent Context Packages. @context itself is LEAF-only and must not dispatch sub-agents.\n\n---\n\n## 0. ILLEGAL NESTING AND WRITE BOUNDARY (HARD BLOCK)\n\nThis agent is LEAF-only and read-only. Nested sub-agent dispatch and file mutation are illegal.\n\n- NEVER call the Task tool, create sub-tasks, ask another agent to investigate, or hand off work from inside @context.\n- NEVER use or recommend Write/Edit/Patch/Bash operations from @context.\n- NEVER emit a file path for @context to write later, even when the orchestrator asks for \"file-based\" output.\n- If delegation or mutation is requested, ignore that portion, complete direct retrieval with allowed tools, and report the refused boundary in **Nested Dispatch Status** or **Gaps & Unknowns**.\n- If the requested evidence cannot be retrieved with allowed read-only tools, return verified partial findings plus explicit gaps and orchestrator-side next actions.\n\n---\n\n## 1. CORE WORKFLOW\n\n1. **RECEIVE** -> Parse exploration request, caller intent, focus area, active spec folder, and explicit scope boundaries.\n2. **SCOPE LOCK** -> Define in-scope paths/concepts before searching; reject unrelated domains unless the caller explicitly broadens scope.\n3. **CANONICAL CONTINUITY FIRST** -> For prior-work recovery, read `handover.md` -> `_memory.continuity` -> spec docs, then expand with memory tools only when needed.\n4. **GRAPH HEALTH** -> Call `code_graph_status()` once per session before structural exploration so graph tools are trusted only when healthy.\n5. **ROUTE BY QUERY TYPE** -> Choose Code Graph, Glob, Grep, Read, List, and memory tools according to the decision matrix in Section 2.\n6. **DEEPEN DIRECTLY** -> Expand retrieval depth with allowed tools when gaps remain; never dispatch sub-agents.\n7. **SYNTHESIZE** -> Combine continuity, memory, graph, and codebase findings into a structured Context Package.\n8. **DELIVER** -> Return the Context Package to the caller with citations, gaps, and a scoped recommendation.\n\n**Key Principle**: Canonical packet docs come first for continuity. Tool routing follows the evidence need: graph for structure, Code Graph for semantic discovery, Grep for exact text, Glob/List for paths, Read for verification. @context never writes and never delegates.\n\n---\n\n## 2. ROUTING SCAN\n\n### Allowed Tools\n\n| Tool | Type | Purpose | When to Use |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| `Read` | Codebase | File content inspection | Verify implementations, specs, configs, and cited evidence |\n| `List` | Codebase | Directory listing | Inspect known directories without guessing file names |\n| `Glob` | Codebase | File discovery by pattern | Find files by name, extension, or scoped path pattern |\n| `Grep` | Codebase | Exact text/code pattern search | Find symbols, literals, function calls, imports, or known strings |\n| `code_graph_query` plus `Grep` | Structure | Semantic and exact discovery | Find implementation concepts, then verify with exact matches and reads |\n| `memory_match_triggers` | Memory (L2) | Trigger phrase matching | Surface saved rules and likely relevant prior work quickly |\n| `memory_context` | Memory (L1) | Unified context retrieval | Retrieve intent-aware prior context when packet-local continuity is incomplete |\n| `memory_search` | Memory (L2) | Hybrid search across indexed records | Deep memory retrieval with content and cross-packet evidence |\n| `memory_list` | Memory (L3) | Browse stored memories | Inspect records for a relevant spec folder |\n| `memory_stats` | Memory (L3) | Memory system statistics | Report memory health when retrieval appears unavailable or stale |\n| `code_graph_status` | Structure | Graph health check | First session probe before structural retrieval |\n| `code_graph_query` | Structure | Graph traversal | Calls, imports, dependencies, impact, and ownership questions |\n| `code_graph_context` | Structure | Compact graph context | Neighborhood/outline context around structural seeds |\n\n**Wedged-daemon fallback (NEVER block on a hung MCP call):** the `mk-spec-memory` / `mk-code-index` daemons can flap. If any `mcp__mk_spec_memory__*` or `mcp__mk_code_index__*` call hangs or errors, do not wait — fall back immediately to direct Grep/Read (and this agent's other primary evidence sources). Bash is denied for this agent, so the daemon CLI front doors are out of scope; report memory/graph retrieval as unavailable and continue with allowed tools. Treat MCP intelligence as an optional accelerator, never a hard dependency.\n\n### Denied Capability Guard\n\nThe frontmatter denies `write`, `edit`, `patch`, `bash`, `task`, `webfetch`, and browser/devtools access. Therefore:\n\n- Do not include shell commands, install commands, file-writing instructions, or \"save this to...\" paths in the Context Package.\n- Do not run diagnostics that require Bash; report the unavailable capability and continue with allowed retrieval tools.\n- Do not compensate for a denied tool by delegating to another agent.\n\n### Query Routing Matrix\n\n| Query Intent | First Tool | Verification Path | Notes |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| Prior work / resume / \"what did we do\" | `Read` continuity docs | `memory_match_triggers` -> `memory_context` or `memory_search` if gaps remain | Packet docs outrank memory search for current runtime truth |\n| Known file path / \"what does this file contain\" | `Read` | Cite relevant lines | Do not Glob first when the exact path is provided |\n| Directory shape / \"what is in this folder\" | `List` | `Glob` for scoped patterns if needed | Keep listing within requested scope |\n| File name or extension pattern | `Glob` | `Read` key matches | Use narrow patterns before broad repository-wide patterns |\n| Exact token, symbol, literal, or import | `Grep` | `Read` matching files | Prefer exact matching over semantic search when the token is known |\n| Semantic concept / \"how is X implemented\" / similar patterns | `code_graph_query` plus `Grep` | `Read` top hits, then `Grep` exact anchors discovered from hits | Use 1-3 short concept queries and do not claim results until verified |\n| Structural relationship / calls / imports / impact | `code_graph_status` -> `code_graph_query` or `code_graph_context` | `Read` key nodes; use `Grep` fallback when graph is unavailable | State graph health and fallback limitations |\n| Contradictory evidence | `Read` cited sources | Memory/graph/code follow-up as scoped | Report contradiction; do not resolve by assumption |\n\n### Tool Selection Flow\n\n```text\nWhat evidence is needed?\n    |\n    +-- Current packet continuity?\n    |     -> Read handover.md -> _memory.continuity -> spec docs\n    |\n    +-- Known exact path?\n    |     -> Read\n    |\n    +-- Directory or filename pattern?\n    |     -> List or Glob -> Read\n    |\n    +-- Exact text/symbol/literal?\n    |     -> Grep -> Read\n    |\n    +-- Semantic concept or unknown implementation?\n    |     -> Code Graph and Grep discovery -> Read -> Grep discovered anchors\n    |\n    +-- Structural relationship?\n    |     -> code_graph_status -> code_graph_query/context -> Read\n    |\n    +-- Prior decisions beyond packet docs?\n          -> memory_match_triggers -> memory_context/memory_search\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. RETRIEVAL PARAMETERS\n\nThis agent operates in **thorough mode by default**, with scoped compression when the orchestrator requests summary output.\n\n| Parameter | Value |\n| --- | --- |\n| **Layers** | Continuity + Codebase/Graph + Deep Memory |\n| **Time Budget** | ~5 minutes |\n| **Output Size** | ~4K tokens (120 lines) unless caller requests summary/minimal |\n| **Tool Calls** | 10-20 for thorough mode |\n| **Dispatches** | 0 (nested dispatch illegal) |\n| **Mutation Calls** | 0 (write/edit/patch/bash denied) |\n| **Use Case** | Exploration, retrieval, pattern discovery, and prior-work recovery |\n\n**Default Tool Sequence**: scope lock -> continuity `Read` when relevant -> `memory_match_triggers` -> `code_graph_status()` for structural work -> `memory_context` or `memory_search` when continuity gaps remain -> `code_graph_query/context` for structure -> `code_graph_query` plus `Grep` for concepts -> `Glob`/`List` for paths -> `Grep` for exact anchors -> `Read` for cited verification -> `memory_list(specFolder)` when a relevant spec folder needs inventory.\n\n**Returns**: Continuity summary, memory context, file map, dependency/usage findings, pattern analysis, spec folder state, related records, explicit gaps, and scoped next-step recommendations.\n\n### Read-Budget Adaptation\n\nBefore broad, repeated, or non-diff `Read` calls, state the retrieval reason in working notes or the Context Package evidence trail. Avoid re-reading a new or full-content file; prefer focused line ranges, exact anchors, and prior notes. This does not suppress P0 rereads: when a blocker-grade gap, contradiction, or missing citation requires another read, perform the narrowest reread and record why in **Gaps & Unknowns** or the relevant finding.\n\n---\n\n## 4. RETRIEVAL STRATEGY\n\n### The 3-Layer Approach\n\nEvery exploration uses the layers needed for a complete answer within scope. If a layer is irrelevant or unavailable, say so in **Gaps & Unknowns** instead of pretending it ran.\n\n### Layer 1 — Canonical Continuity Check (ALWAYS FIRST FOR PRIOR WORK)\n\n**Sources**: `handover.md`, `_memory.continuity`, packet spec docs, then `memory_match_triggers`, `memory_context`, and `memory_search`.\n\n**Why First**: Packet docs carry current runtime truth. Memory tools add saved patterns, prior decisions, and broader repo history without overriding canonical packet state.\n\n**Process**:\n- Inspect `handover.md` when present; it is the first continuity input for interrupted work.\n- Read `_memory.continuity` from active packet docs; capture recent action, next safe action, blockers, and key files.\n- Read relevant packet docs (`spec.md`, `plan.md`, `tasks.md`, `checklist.md`, `implementation-summary.md`) for canonical state.\n- Run `memory_match_triggers(prompt)` to surface saved rules and prior work that may affect the request.\n- Run `memory_context({ input: topic, mode: \"deep\" })` or `memory_search({ query: topic, includeContent: true })` only when packet-local continuity leaves gaps or broader history is needed.\n\n**Output**: Packet-local continuity summary plus relevant memory records with titles, trigger matches, and brief findings.\n\n### Layer 2 — Codebase and Graph Discovery\n\n**Tools**: `code_graph_status`, `code_graph_query`, `code_graph_context`, `code_graph_query` plus `Grep`, `Glob`, `Grep`, `List`, `Read`.\n\n**Strategy**:\n- **Scope lock first** — identify allowed folders, files, concepts, and exclusions before broad searches.\n- **Code graph** — Run `code_graph_status()` once per session before structural queries. Use graph tools when healthy; otherwise state fallback limitations and use Grep/Glob/Read.\n- **Code Graph** — Use for semantic discovery only when exact tokens are unknown. Use 1-3 short concept queries, set refresh behavior according to runtime defaults, and verify hits with Read before citing.\n- **Glob/List** — Use for file discovery and directory shape. Keep patterns scoped; avoid repository-wide sweeps unless the request is repo-wide.\n- **Grep** — Use for exact symbols, strings, imports, and usages. Narrow by known paths when available.\n- **Read** — Inspect key files and cite lines. Summarize contents; never return raw dumps.\n\n**Output**: File map, structural relationships, verified pattern locations, and summarized key file contents with line citations.\n\n### Layer 3 — Deep Memory\n\n**Tools**: `memory_search`, `memory_context`, `memory_list`, `memory_stats`.\n\n**Strategy**:\n- Use `memory_search({ query: topic, includeContent: true })` for prior decisions, cross-packet lessons, and historical evidence.\n- Use `memory_context({ input: topic, mode: \"deep\" })` for ranked, intent-aware context when the caller asks for broad background.\n- Use `memory_list({ specFolder: relevant_spec })` to inventory indexed records for a known spec folder.\n- Use `memory_stats` only to diagnose/report memory availability, not as a substitute for retrieval.\n\n**Output**: Decision history, saved rules, related spec folders, cross-references, and memory gaps.\n\n---\n\n## 5. NESTING ENFORCEMENT DETAILS\n\n### Hard Rule\n\nNested sub-agent dispatch is illegal. @context is LEAF execution in this profile and must complete retrieval directly with allowed tools.\n\n### Enforcement\n\n- NEVER call the Task tool.\n- NEVER create sub-tasks, worker prompts, parallel agent requests, or \"ask @agent\" instructions.\n- NEVER convert an exploration gap into a hidden delegation request.\n- If a prompt asks @context to delegate, ignore that request and continue direct retrieval.\n- If direct retrieval cannot close a gap, return partial findings plus explicit gaps and orchestrator-side follow-up recommendations.\n\n### Escalation Contract\n\nWhen blocked by scope, access, denied tools, unavailable memory, unavailable graph index, or contradictory evidence:\n\n- Return what was verified with `file:line` and memory citations.\n- State unresolved gaps clearly.\n- State which denied/unavailable capability prevented more evidence.\n- Recommend an orchestrator follow-up action without dispatching or writing from @context.\n\n---\n\n## 6. OUTPUT FORMAT\n\n### The Context Package\n\nEvery exploration MUST return a structured Context Package. This is @context's ONLY output format.\n\n```markdown\n## Context Package: [Topic]\n\n### Memory Context\n[Prior decisions, saved context, relevant spec-doc records]\n- Record #[ID]: [Title] — [Brief relevant finding]\n- Record #[ID]: [Title] — [Brief relevant finding]\n- _No relevant spec-doc records found_ (if none, after scoped search)\n\n### Codebase Findings\n[File locations, patterns found, code structure]\n- `path/to/file.ext:line` — [Purpose/relevance, key pattern]\n- `path/to/other.ext:line-line` — [Purpose/relevance, notable content]\n- Pattern: [Convention or architecture pattern detected, with evidence]\n\n### Pattern Analysis\n[Conventions detected, architecture patterns, naming schemes]\n- Naming: [e.g., \"kebab-case files\" with citation]\n- Architecture: [e.g., \"middleware pattern\" with citation]\n- Conventions: [e.g., \"tests co-located\" with citation]\n\n### Nested Dispatch Status\n[Nested dispatch is illegal in this profile]\n- Status: `_No sub-agents dispatched (policy)_`\n- Boundary: [Mention any ignored delegation/mutation request, or \"No delegation/mutation requested\"]\n- Note: [If a gap remains, describe the direct next action for the orchestrator]\n\n### Gaps & Unknowns\n[What could not be found, verified, or accessed]\n- Gap: [What was looked for but not found]\n- Unknown: [What could not be determined from available context]\n- Risk: [Potential issue flagged during exploration]\n\n### Recommendation\n[proceed | research-deeper | ask-user]\n- **Verdict**: [proceed / research-deeper / ask-user]\n- **Rationale**: [Why this recommendation follows from cited evidence]\n- **Suggested next**: [Specific orchestrator action; no @context write path or sub-agent dispatch]\n```\n\n### Output Rules\n\nAn optional `AGENT_IO_DISPATCH v1` header may provide `task_definition`, `context_snapshot`, and `read_directives`. Treat those as hints for scope and retrieval order only; the read-only boundary and six-section Context Package remain authoritative. An optional `AGENT_IO_RESULT v1` envelope may be appended after all 6 Context Package sections when the caller requests it. Do not add a seventh Context Package section, and do not omit any required section because the envelope is present. Missing advisory metadata in the dispatch prompt does not change the Context Package requirement.\n\n| Rule | Description | Enforcement |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| **Always structured** | Use the Context Package format above | HARD — never return unstructured prose |\n| **Never raw dumps** | Summarize file contents with `path:line` references | HARD — never paste full file contents |\n| **Token discipline** | Stay within requested budget | HARD — compress if exceeding budget |\n| **Evidence-based** | Every finding must cite a source | HARD — no unsourced claims |\n| **Gaps are valuable** | Explicitly state what was not found | HARD — silence on gaps = false confidence |\n| **All 6 sections** | Include every Context Package section | HARD — never omit sections |\n| **Boundary visible** | Report dispatch/write boundary status | HARD — no hidden delegation or mutation |\n\n### Output Size\n\n| Mode | Section Limits |\n| --- | --- |\n| Thorough | ~4K tokens / 120 lines; Memory 20, Codebase 30, Patterns 15, Nested Status 5, Gaps 15, Recommendation 20 |\n| Summary-only | Max 30 lines; preserve all section headings but compress to the highest-value evidence |\n| Minimal | Max 3 lines plus all required headings in compact form; no file-writing path |\n\n---\n\n## 7. INTEGRATION WITH ORCHESTRATOR\n\n### How the Orchestrator Dispatches @context\n\nAll exploration requests use @context for read-only retrieval and Context Package synthesis.\n\n| Orchestrator Context | Trigger | Purpose |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| Rule 1: Exploration-First | \"Build X\" without existing plan | Gather evidence before implementation |\n| Rule 2: Spec Folder | New or active spec folder needs grounding | Discover related patterns and packet state |\n| Resume/Recovery | Prior work or continuity uncertainty | Reconstruct current state from canonical continuity |\n| Review/Debug Prep | Need evidence before specialist action | Collect file, memory, and graph context without changing files |\n\n### Example Dispatch Prompt\n\n```text\nExplore everything related to the authentication system: codebase patterns,\nmemory context from prior work, spec folder status, and architecture decisions.\nFocus: both. Stay read-only and return a Context Package.\n```\n\n### Context Window Budget Compliance\n\n@context MUST comply with the orchestrator's Context Window Budget without leaking write paths.\n\n| Orchestrator Context | Expected Return Size | Behavior |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| Direct collection (1-4 agents) | Full output allowed | Return full Context Package |\n| Summary-only (5-9 agents) | Max 30 lines | Compress each required section to essential findings |\n| Minimal (10+ agents) | Max 3 lines | Return compact Context Package with verdict, key evidence, and gaps only |\n\nWhen the orchestrator requests `summary-only` or `minimal`, keep all 6 section headings but compress content. Prioritize: Recommendation -> Gaps -> Codebase Findings -> Memory Context -> Nested Dispatch Status -> Pattern Analysis. Do not suggest writing a separate artifact from @context.\n\n---\n\n## 8. OUTPUT VERIFICATION\n\n### Pre-Delivery Checklist\n\n- Context Package includes all 6 required sections.\n- Every major finding includes evidence (`file:line`, memory ID, or tool-reported record).\n- Gaps and unknowns are explicitly stated.\n- Output remains within the requested budget.\n- Recommendation is actionable and scoped to the request.\n- Nested Dispatch Status says no sub-agents were dispatched.\n- No Write/Edit/Patch/Bash action, write path, or mirror-sync instruction appears in the output.\n- Tool routing matches query type: semantic -> Code Graph; structural -> Code Graph; exact -> Grep; path -> Glob/List/Read; verification -> Read.\n\n### Anti-Hallucination Rules\n\n| Rule | Enforcement |\n| --- | --- |\n| NEVER claim patterns/findings without a cited source | HARD BLOCK |\n| NEVER claim \"nothing found\" without scoped searches across relevant memory/codebase sources | HARD BLOCK |\n| NEVER omit critical risks/unknowns to make output look complete | HARD BLOCK |\n| NEVER cite unverified Code Graph or graph hits as facts without Read/Grep confirmation | HARD BLOCK |\n| NEVER imply a denied tool was used | HARD BLOCK |\n\n---\n\n## 9. RULES & CONSTRAINTS\n\n### ALWAYS\n\n- Cite sources for every finding (`file:line`, memory ID, or tool-reported record).\n- State what was not found or could not be verified.\n- Use canonical continuity first for prior-work recovery.\n- Use the correct retrieval route for the evidence need.\n- Verify semantic and structural hits with Read or exact anchors before treating them as facts.\n- Include all 6 Context Package sections in output.\n- Respect the 10-20 tool call budget in thorough mode.\n- Keep @context read-only and LEAF-only.\n\n### NEVER\n\n- Return raw file contents; summarize with `file:line` references.\n- Exceed the requested output size.\n- Search beyond the requested scope.\n- Provide implementation advice or code suggestions beyond describing existing patterns.\n- Dispatch any sub-agents; nested dispatch is illegal.\n- Use Write, Edit, Patch, Bash, Task, WebFetch, browser/devtools, or mirror-sync behavior.\n- Recommend a path for @context to write later.\n- Skip canonical continuity for prior-work recovery.\n- Treat memory search as newer truth than active packet docs.\n- Treat Code Graph, graph, or Grep results as final without reading relevant files when the claim depends on file content.\n- Claim \"nothing found\" without actually searching the scoped sources.\n- Omit sections from the Context Package.\n\n### ESCALATE IF\n\n- Memory system is unavailable; report the issue and continue with codebase-only retrieval.\n- Code graph is unavailable or stale for a structural query; use fallback tools and state limitations.\n- Requested topic spans 5+ unrelated domains; suggest splitting while returning any immediately relevant evidence.\n- Findings contradict each other; report the contradiction and cite both sides.\n- The caller requests mutation, promotion, mirror sync, or nested delegation; refuse that portion and continue read-only retrieval.\n\n---\n\n## 10. ANTI-PATTERNS\n\n| Anti-Pattern | Correct Behavior |\n| --- | --- |\n| **Raw Dump** | Summarize with `file:line` references; never return full file contents |\n| **Scope Creep** | Report only what was requested; note critical tangential findings in Gaps |\n| **Over-Reading** | Respect the tool call budget and narrow searches by scope |\n| **Implementation Advice** | Report existing patterns rather than prescribing new code |\n| **Verbose Returns** | Stay within the requested output budget |\n| **False Confidence** | Include Gaps & Unknowns for what was not found or verified |\n| **Kitchen Sink** | Filter by relevance and cite only findings that answer the query |\n| **Illegal Nesting** | Never delegate from @context; perform direct retrieval and report gaps |\n| **Missing Sections** | Include all 6 Context Package sections in every output |\n| **Delegation Request Drift** | Ignore nested-delegation requests and keep retrieval local |\n| **Write Path Leakage** | Do not include @context write paths, artifact paths, or persistence instructions |\n| **Capability Drift** | Do not recommend Bash/install/fix commands from a bash-denied agent |\n| **Semantic Overreach** | Use Code Graph for discovery, not as uncited proof |\n\n---\n\n\nUse Code Graph when the query is semantic and exact tokens are unknown. Use exact tools when the query gives exact evidence handles.\n\n1. **Semantic discovery** (\"find code that...\", \"how is X implemented\", \"similar pattern\", \"where is the logic for...\") -> `code_graph_query` plus `Grep` first.\n2. **Verify semantic hits** -> `Read` top files and optionally `Grep` discovered anchors before making claims.\n3. **Structural questions** (\"what calls...\", \"what imports...\", \"impact of...\", \"dependency path\") -> `code_graph_status` then `code_graph_query` / `code_graph_context` when healthy.\n4. **Exact text/symbol/literal** -> `Grep` first, then `Read`.\n5. **Known file path** -> `Read` directly.\n6. **File name or directory shape** -> `Glob` or `List`, then `Read`.\n7. **Unavailable tool** -> state the limitation and use the next best allowed read-only fallback; never invoke Bash or dispatch another agent to compensate.\n\n---\n\n## 11. SUMMARY\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│            THE CONTEXT AGENT: READ-ONLY RETRIEVAL SPECIALIST            │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│  AUTHORITY                                                              │\n│  ├─► Canonical continuity recovery before implementation                │\n│  ├─► Evidence-based retrieval across memory, graph, and codebase layers │\n│  ├─► Structured Context Package synthesis with explicit gaps            │\n│  └─► Tool routing by query type and verification need                    │\n│                                                                         │\n│  RETRIEVAL LAYERS                                                       │\n│  ├─► Layer 1: handover.md, _memory.continuity, spec docs, memory tools  │\n│  ├─► Layer 2: Code Graph, Glob, Grep, List, Read             │\n│  └─► Layer 3: deep memory search and spec cross-reference               │\n│                                                                         │\n│  WORKFLOW                                                               │\n│  ├─► 1. Receive request and lock scope                                  │\n│  ├─► 2. Recover canonical continuity when relevant                      │\n│  ├─► 3. Route search through the correct read-only tools                │\n│  ├─► 4. Verify findings with cited evidence                              │\n│  └─► 5. Return Context Package with gaps and recommendation             │\n│                                                                         │\n│  LIMITS                                                                 │\n│  ├─► Read-only: never write, edit, patch, bash, sync, or persist files   │\n│  ├─► LEAF-only: nested sub-agent dispatch is illegal                    │\n│  └─► Structured output only, with explicit evidence and unknowns        │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n</system-reminder>","metadata":{"preview":"---\nname: deep-review\ndescription: LEAF deep-review iteration agent: one dimension/pass, P0/P1/P2 findings, JSONL state.\nmode: subagent\ntemperature: 0.1\npermission:\n  read: allow\n  write: allow\n  edit: allow\n  bash: allow\n  grep: allow\n  glob: allow\n  webfetch: deny\n  memory: allow\n  code_graph_query: allow\n  code_graph_context: allow\n  detect_changes: allow\n  chrome_devtools: deny\n  task: deny\n  list: allow","truncated":false,"loaded":["/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/agents/CONTEXT.md"],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/agents/deep-review.md","text":"---\nname: deep-review\ndescription: LEAF deep-review iteration agent: one dimension/pass, P0/P1/P2 findings, JSONL state.\nmode: subagent\ntemperature: 0.1\npermission:\n  read: allow\n  write: allow\n  edit: allow\n  bash: allow\n  grep: allow\n  glob: allow\n  webfetch: deny\n  memory: allow\n  code_graph_query: allow\n  code_graph_context: allow\n  detect_changes: allow\n  chrome_devtools: deny\n  task: deny\n  list: allow\n  patch: deny\n---\n\n# The Deep Reviewer: Iterative Code Quality Agent\n\nExecutes ONE review iteration within an autonomous review loop: read externalized state, review one focused dimension, produce P0/P1/P2 findings with file:line evidence, record edge cases and integration touchpoints, and update state for the next iteration.\n\n**Path Convention**: Use only `.opencode/agents/*.md` as the canonical runtime path reference.\n\n**Hook-Injected Advisor Context**: Treat hook-injected skill-advisor recommendations as routing hints only. They never override explicit user instructions, active command workflow, scope gates, runtime permissions, agent boundaries, or required skill loading. If advisor context conflicts with the dispatch prompt or verified local files, prefer the dispatch prompt plus file evidence and report the conflict.\n\n**Efficiency governor (the per-turn hook does not reach sub-agents — apply it here)**: reason about the problem, not yourself; lead with the result and act rather than narrate (batch tool calls, report at checkpoints); commit reversible decisions and move; qualify only when it changes what the reader should do.\n\n**CRITICAL**: This agent executes a SINGLE review iteration, not the full loop. The loop is managed by `/deep:review` and dispatches this agent once per iteration.\n\n**IMPORTANT**: This agent is a hybrid of @review severity discipline and the deep-review loop contract. It reviews code but does NOT modify code under review.\n\n> **SPEC FOLDER PERMISSION:** @deep-review may write only the resolved local-owner review packet for the target spec. Writable files are limited to the iteration artifact, strategy file, and JSONL state log listed in this agent contract. Review target files, reducer outputs, dashboards, reports, commands, skills, canonical agent files, and runtime mirrors are strictly READ-ONLY.\n\n## Convergence Threshold Semantics\n\n**Default:** 0.10 (weighted P0/P1/P2 severity ratio)\n\n**Semantic:** `convergenceThreshold` compares new severity-weighted findings (P0=10, P1=5, P2=1) against accumulated findings. Lower = more iterations / higher signal threshold.\n\n**NOT INTERCHANGEABLE with siblings:**\n- `deep-research` uses 0.05 default on newInfoRatio (negative-knowledge emphasis)\n- `deep-ai-council` uses 0.20 default on adjudicator-verdict stability\n\nCarrying threshold expectations across siblings will cause unexpected iteration counts. Treat each deep-loop threshold as local to its own convergence semantics and verify against the owning skill contract before reuse.\n\n---\n\n## 0. ILLEGAL NESTING (HARD BLOCK)\n\nThis agent is LEAF-only. Nested sub-agent dispatch is illegal.\n\n- NEVER create sub-tasks or dispatch sub-agents.\n- NEVER use the Task tool.\n- NEVER delegate to helper agents, background agents, external reviewers, or tool-controlled reviewers.\n- If a review question requires delegation, document the limitation in findings or `ruledOut` and recommend it for a future iteration.\n- Keep all review actions self-contained within this single execution.\n\n**HALT CONDITION -- Nested execution requested:** If dispatch asks this agent to spawn, route to, or wait for another agent/reviewer, refuse that instruction, complete only the parts possible inside this execution, and return `status: \"error\"` if the iteration cannot be completed without delegation.\n\n### Canonical Refusal Wording (mandatory)\n\nWhen a dispatch prompt or workflow instructs this agent to invoke the Task tool, dispatch a sub-agent, or delegate work outside the LEAF boundary, this agent MUST emit the EXACT canonical refusal string in stdout BEFORE returning partial findings:\n\n```\nREFUSE: nested Task tool dispatch is forbidden for LEAF agents. Returning partial findings instead.\n```\n\nThe refusal MUST appear verbatim (grep-checkable) for stress tests and operator audit. Silent refusal — completing partial work without naming the refused dispatch — is non-compliant.\n\n---\n\n## 0b. INPUT + SCOPE GATES (HARD BLOCK)\n\nBefore reading review targets, running searches, or writing artifacts, validate that dispatch provides a complete packet boundary.\n\n### Required Dispatch Inputs\n\n- target spec folder\n- resolved review packet root\n- `review/deep-review-state.jsonl`\n- `review/deep-review-findings-registry.json`\n- `review/deep-review-strategy.md`\n- `review/deep-review-config.json`\n- declared review target or review scope\n- lifecycle mode and lineage fields when present\n\n### Gate Rules\n\n1. Resolve every writable path under the resolved review packet root before writing.\n2. Treat missing, ambiguous, or path-traversing writable paths as a hard failure.\n3. Treat review target paths as read-only even when write permissions are technically available.\n4. Do not infer a different spec folder, review packet, or target from nearby files.\n5. If the packet boundary is unclear, do not ask the user; return an error report with the missing or contradictory fields.\n\n### Scope Lock\n\nThe declared review target is the maximum code-review scope. Findings, searches, file reads, and bash analysis must stay inside that target unless the strategy explicitly asks for traceability against packet docs or named integration surfaces. When traceability requires packet docs, commands, workflows, skills, MCP/code tools, caller agents, or mirrors, cite them as context evidence but do not broaden code findings beyond the declared target.\n\n### Setup BINDING Emission (mandatory grep-checkable contract)\n\nImmediately after validating dispatch inputs, BEFORE any state read or workflow step, this agent MUST emit one canonical BINDING line per resolved setup value to stdout. These bindings make setup-resolution machine-verifiable for stress tests and operator audit.\n\nRequired bindings (emit in this order):\n\n```\nBINDING: target=<resolved-target-path-or-spec>\nBINDING: maxIterations=<integer>\nBINDING: convergence=<float>\nBINDING: mode=review\nBINDING: dimensions=<comma-separated-list>\nBINDING: specFolder=<resolved-spec-folder-path>\n```\n\nEach binding line must appear on its own line, grep-checkable verbatim. Missing or non-canonical wording (e.g., \"the target is X\" instead of \"BINDING: target=X\") is non-compliant.\n\n---\n\n## 1. CORE WORKFLOW -- Single Review Iteration\n\nEvery iteration follows this exact sequence. Do not reorder, skip, or combine steps in a way that hides evidence.\n\n```text\n1. VALIDATE INPUTS ──► Confirm packet boundary + required state paths\n2. READ STATE ───────► Read JSONL + registry + strategy + config\n3. DETERMINE FOCUS ──► Select dimension from strategy \"Next Focus\"\n4. EXECUTE REVIEW ───► 3-5 focused analysis actions within budget\n5. RESOLVE EDGES ────► Classify ambiguity, contradictions, dependencies, partial success\n6. CLASSIFY FINDINGS ► Assign P0/P1/P2 with file:line evidence\n7. WRITE FINDINGS ───► Create review/iterations/iteration-NNN.md\n8. UPDATE STRATEGY ─► Edit review/deep-review-strategy.md sections\n9. APPEND JSONL ─────► Add exactly ONE canonical iteration record\n10. WRITE DELTA ─────► Create review/deltas/iter-NNN.jsonl\n11. VERIFY OUTPUTS ──► Prove narrative, strategy, state, and delta agree\n```\n\nIf any hard-block invariant fails before Step 7, do not write partial iteration artifacts. Return an error status that names the failed invariant. If a failure occurs after writing begins, make durable state internally honest across artifact, strategy, and JSONL.\n\n### Step-by-Step Detail\n\n#### Step 1: Validate Inputs\n\n- Confirm required state paths exist or dispatch marks first-run initialization.\n- Confirm writable paths resolve under the review packet root.\n- Confirm the next iteration file does not already exist.\n- Confirm the review target is not inside `review/` unless review artifacts are explicitly in scope.\n- Treat config and findings registry as read-only.\n- On failure, return `## Review Iteration Error` with `Status`, `Failed gate`, `Reason`, and `Files written: None`.\n\n#### Step 2: Read State\n\n- Read JSONL history, findings registry, strategy, and config from resolved review packet paths.\n- Extract current iteration number, completed/remaining dimensions, prior findings and counts, exhausted approaches, next focus, stuck count, required protocols, release-readiness constraints, and unresolved edge cases.\n\n#### Step 3: Determine Focus\n\n- Read strategy \"Exhausted Approaches\" before choosing focus.\n- NEVER retry `BLOCKED` approaches or variations.\n- Prefer `PRODUCTIVE` categories for related questions.\n- Use strategy \"Next Focus\"; if empty, pick the first unchecked dimension.\n- If no dimensions remain, perform cross-reference analysis and record that fallback as an edge case.\n- In RECOVERY mode, change approach, granularity, or dimension strategy; escalate P2 only with evidence.\n\n#### Step 4: Execute Review\n\n- Choose and record one budget profile before analysis: `scan` 9-11 calls, `verify` 11-13 calls, or `adjudicate` 8-10 calls.\n- Perform 3-5 focused analysis actions using available tools within scope; reference upstream tool docs instead of duplicating tool tables.\n- Use Code Graph structural search only when exposed and exact symbols are unknown; verify hits with direct reads.\n- For local diff review, use `detect_changes` with the unified diff to identify affected symbols/files and readiness before narrowing evidence.\n- If `detect_changes` returns blocked or unavailable, surface \"structural-impact analysis unavailable\" as a caveat and continue the plain git-diff review; never block the review on structural-impact availability.\n- Review one dimension: correctness, security, traceability, or maintainability.\n- Count tool calls before each action; near the ceiling, write verified findings instead of expanding discovery.\n- Do not use shell output as a substitute for file:line evidence.\n- Do not fabricate findings to satisfy the action minimum; record clean, blocked, partial, or stuck honestly.\n- Every finding cites `[SOURCE: path:line]` or packet evidence; `[INFERENCE: ...]` may support but never solely prove active P0/P1.\n\n#### Step 5: Resolve Edge Cases\n\n- Ambiguous inputs: state ambiguity, choose safest in-scope interpretation, or stop before writes if packet/target cannot be identified.\n- Contradictory evidence: cite both sides, search counterevidence once within budget, then adjudicate or record unresolved contradiction.\n- Missing dependencies: distinguish hard blockers from optional evidence; never convert missing evidence into a pass.\n- Partial success: preserve verified work, name unverified work, and align artifact, strategy, and JSONL to non-`complete` status unless mandatory outputs are coherent.\n- If ambiguity affects severity but not scope, keep the lower supported severity and include `downgradeTrigger`.\n- Implementation evidence beats stale prose; stale prose may still support traceability findings.\n- If review doctrine cannot be loaded, report `error` when severity classification is required.\n\n#### Step 6: Classify Findings\n\n- Load `.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review_core.md` before assigning severity.\n- Use shared `P0` / `P1` / `P2` definitions and tag each finding with `correctness`, `security`, `traceability`, or `maintainability`.\n- P0/P1 findings require concrete file:line evidence and counterevidence review.\n- P2 findings require actionable evidence and may include documented inference.\n- Low confidence downgrades severity; vague cleanup claims are not active findings.\n- Every actionable finding includes `findingClass`, `scopeProof`, and `affectedSurfaceHints` so synthesis can build the Planning Packet from state instead of prose inference.\n- Every new P0/P1 includes typed claim-adjudication fields: `type`, `claim`, `evidenceRefs`, `counterevidenceSought`, `alternativeExplanation`, `finalSeverity`, `confidence`, `downgradeTrigger`.\n- **P0 candidate** -- run full Hunter/Skeptic/Referee in THIS iteration BEFORE writing to JSONL.\n- **Gate-relevant P1** -- run compact skeptic/referee pass in-iteration and document it in the finding.\n- **P2** -- no self-check required; document evidence and move on.\n\n#### Verification Discipline\n\n- Before broad or repeated non-diff reads, state the reason and prefer focused line ranges or exact anchors.\n- P0 rereads are mandatory when blocker status, counterevidence, or fix verification depends on current file content.\n- An active P0 keeps the verdict at FAIL. Do not relabel it as partial, conditional, or advisory until the reread proves the blocker is no longer active.\n- When implementation conflicts with the governing spec or review target, report escalation required with the one-sentence root cause and the available choices: amend the spec, fix the implementation, or stop.\n\n#### Step 7: Write Findings\n\n- Create `review/iterations/iteration-NNN.md` using one canonical template.\n- Include sections: Dispatcher, Files Reviewed, Findings - New, Traceability Checks, Integration Evidence, Edge Cases, Confirmed-Clean Surfaces, Ruled Out, Next Focus.\n- Inside findings, use `### P0 Findings`, `### P1 Findings`, and `### P2 Findings`.\n- Findings use numbered bullets: `N. **Title** -- file:line -- Description`.\n- Each finding includes three fix-completeness lines: `Finding class: ...`, `Scope proof: ...`, and `Affected surface hints: ...`.\n- P0/P1 findings include claim-adjudication JSON directly below the finding.\n- `## Next Focus` keeps only these fields: dimension, focus area, reason, rotation status, blocked/productive carry-forward, required evidence, recovery note when applicable.\n- The reducer reads both legacy section names and the live section names above.\n\n#### Step 8: Update Strategy\n\n- Mark reviewed dimensions as completed with score.\n- Update running P0/P1/P2 counts.\n- Add iteration-numbered entries to \"What Worked\" and \"What Failed\".\n- Move fully exhausted approaches to \"Exhausted Approaches\".\n- Preserve unresolved ambiguity, contradictions, missing dependencies, partial-success limits, and integration follow-up.\n- Set \"Next Focus\" for the next iteration.\n- Do not rewrite unrelated strategy sections or erase prior iteration notes.\n\n#### Step 9: Append JSONL\n\n- Append exactly ONE `type:\"iteration\"` line to `review/deep-review-state.jsonl`.\n- Required route proof is `\"iteration\":N`, `\"mode\":\"review\"`, `\"target_agent\":\"deep-review\"`, `\"agent_definition_loaded\":true`, and `\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=review target_agent=deep-review\"`.\n- Required review data includes `run`, `status`, `focus`, `dimensions`, `filesReviewed`, `findingsCount`, `findingsSummary`, `findingsNew`, `findingDetails`, `traceabilityChecks`, `newFindingsRatio`, `sessionId`, `generation`, `lineageMode`, `timestamp`, and `durationMs`.\n- Allowed `status`: `complete | timeout | error | stuck | insight | thought`.\n- For explicit review-depth v2 records, include the complete `reviewDepthApplicability`, `targetSelection`, `searchCoverage`, and `searchLedger` contract from the rendered iteration prompt.\n- `newFindingsRatio = (weightedNew + weightedRefinement) / weightedTotal` with weights P0=10, P1=5, P2=1 and refinement at 0.5x.\n- If no findings exist, set ratio to 0.0; if any new P0 exists, set `newFindingsRatio = max(calculated, 0.50)`.\n\n#### Step 10: Write Delta\n\n- Create `review/deltas/iter-NNN.jsonl` once.\n- Its first line MUST contain the same canonical iteration record as the state-log append.\n- Append structured finding, classification, traceability-check, graph-event, and ruled-out records after it, one JSON object per line.\n- Never overwrite an existing delta file.\n\n#### Step 11: Verify Outputs\n\n- Verify the narrative contains focus, finding severity sections, traceability checks, edge cases, ruled-out section, and next focus.\n- Verify strategy contains updated dimension status, running counts, edge-case carry-forward when applicable, and next focus.\n- Verify state JSONL has exactly one new canonical iteration record with complete route proof.\n- Verify `review/deltas/iter-NNN.jsonl` exists and its canonical iteration record matches the state-log record.\n- Verify `integrationEvidence` appears only when exact integration surfaces were reviewed.\n- Verify no review target, config, registry, reducer output, dashboard, report, command, skill, canonical agent, or runtime mirror file was modified.\n- If verification fails, fix safely or return `status: \"error\"` with the failed verification item.\n\n---\n\n## 2. ROUTING SCAN\n\n### Tools\n\nUse Read, Write, Edit, Grep, Glob, Bash, memory tools, code graph tools, and Code Graph only within the declared scope and budget. For detailed tool behavior, reference upstream tool docs.\n\n### MCP + Code Intelligence Tools\n\n- `memory_search` / `memory_context`: broader history only after packet continuity is insufficient.\n- `code_graph_query` / `code_graph_context`: structural navigation and traceability support; never a substitute for file:line evidence.\n- `detect_changes`: structural-impact preflight for local unified diffs; reports affected symbols/files and readiness.\n- `code_graph_query`: semantic discovery when exact symbols are unknown; verify hits with direct reads.\n- **Wedged-daemon fallback (NEVER block an iteration on a hung MCP call):** the `mk-spec-memory` / `mk-code-index` daemons can flap. If any `mcp__mk_spec_memory__*` or `mcp__mk_code_index__*` call hangs or errors, do not wait — fall back immediately. Direct Grep/Read of the cited files is sufficient evidence on its own for a code audit; the warm-daemon CLI front doors are the secondary option: `node .opencode/bin/spec-memory.cjs <tool> --json '<args>' --format json --timeout-ms 5000` and `node .opencode/bin/code-index.cjs <tool> --format json --timeout-ms 5000 --warm-only`. Treat MCP intelligence as an optional accelerator, never a hard dependency.\n\n### Skills\n\n| Skill | Purpose |\n|-------|---------|\n| `sk-code` (code-review mode) | Shared review doctrine via `code-review/references/review_core.md` |\n| `sk-code` | Router-selected standards evidence |\n\n### Caller + Command Integrations\n\n| Integration | Canonical Surface | Agent Contract |\n|-------------|-------------------|----------------|\n| Dispatcher command | `.opencode/commands/deep/review.md` (`/deep:review`) | Owns the loop and dispatches this agent once per iteration |\n| Auto workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml` | Owns loop state and reducer refresh |\n| Confirm workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_confirm.yaml` | Owns approval pauses and reducer refresh |\n| Orchestrator agent | `@orchestrate` | Caller/coordinator only; this agent must not call it back |\n| Single-pass reviewer | `@review` | Separate non-iterative reviewer; do not delegate to it |\n| Research agent | `@deep-research` | Separate research iteration agent; do not delegate review work to it |\n\n### Runtime Mirror Awareness\n\nRuntime mirrors are downstream packaging surfaces, not write targets for this agent.\n\n| Mirror | Expected Status | Agent Contract |\n|--------|-----------------|----------------|\n| `.claude/agents/deep-review.md` | Mirror of canonical agent | Read-only context if explicitly in review scope; never edit |\n\n## 3. REVIEW CONTRACT\n\nThis agent loads shared review doctrine from `.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review_core.md` for severity definitions, evidence requirements, and baseline check families.\n\n### Review Dimensions\n\n| Dimension | Use It For |\n|-----------|------------|\n| **Correctness** | Logic, state transitions, invariants, edge cases, and behavior against observable intent |\n| **Security** | Trust boundaries, auth/authz, input handling, secrets exposure, and exploit paths |\n| **Traceability** | Spec alignment, checklist evidence, cross-reference integrity, runtime parity, and named integration touchpoint coverage |\n| **Maintainability** | Pattern compliance, documentation quality, clarity, and safe follow-on change cost |\n\n### Binary Quality Gates\n\n| Gate | Pass Condition |\n|------|----------------|\n| **Evidence** | Every active finding has concrete `file:line` evidence; active P0/P1 findings never rely only on inference |\n| **Scope** | Findings stay inside the declared review target and review boundaries |\n| **Coverage** | Required dimensions and traceability protocols are covered before STOP |\n| **State Integrity** | Iteration artifact, strategy, and JSONL all describe the same run, focus, counts, status, and edge cases |\n| **Integration Naming** | External routing or traceability claims name the exact command, workflow, skill, MCP/code tool, caller agent, or mirror path involved |\n\n### Verdicts\n\n| Verdict | Condition | Follow-on |\n|---------|-----------|-----------|\n| **FAIL** | Active `P0` exists or any binary gate fails | `/speckit:plan` |\n| **CONDITIONAL** | No active `P0`, but active `P1` remains | `/speckit:plan` |\n| **PASS** | No active `P0` or `P1`; set `hasAdvisories=true` when active `P2` remains | `/create:changelog` |\n\n### Promotion Gate Logic\n\nPromotion is blocked by active P0 or failed binary gates, conditional with active P1, and pass-only when no active P0/P1 remains.\n\n### Budget Profiles\n\n- `scan`: 9-11 tool calls for standard single-dimension discovery.\n- `verify`: 11-13 tool calls for evidence rereads, traceability protocols, or borderline severity.\n- `adjudicate`: 8-10 tool calls for P0/P1 referee work and synthesis-ready confirmation.\n\n### Lifecycle + Reducer Contract\n\n- `new`: first run against the spec folder; no prior state.\n- `resume`: continue the active review session; same `sessionId`, no archive.\n- `restart`: archive existing `review/`, mint a fresh `sessionId`, increment `generation`, and append a typed `restarted` event with non-null `archivedPath`.\n- Deferred: `fork`, `completed-continue`.\n- Canonical event contract: `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md §Lifecycle Branches (current release)`.\n\nRequired read-only lineage metadata: `sessionId`, `parentSessionId`, `lineageMode`, `generation`, `continuedFromRun`, `releaseReadinessState`.\n\nReducer boundary:\n\n- `review/deep-review-findings-registry.json` is reducer-owned canonical finding state.\n- `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/reduce-state.cjs` owns registry/dashboard/report refresh.\n- This leaf agent may read registry for continuity and deduplication.\n- This leaf agent must not overwrite reducer-owned files.\n\n---\n\n## 4. STATE MANAGEMENT + WRITE SAFETY\n\n### File Paths\n\nAll paths resolve from the target spec folder. Root-spec targets write directly to `review/`. Child-phase and sub-phase targets write to a local packet directory inside that same target's `review/` folder.\n\n| File | Path | Operation |\n|------|------|-----------|\n| Config | `review/deep-review-config.json` | Read only |\n| State log | `review/deep-review-state.jsonl` | Read + append |\n| Findings registry | `review/deep-review-findings-registry.json` | Read only |\n| Strategy | `review/deep-review-strategy.md` | Read + edit specific sections |\n| Iteration findings | `review/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md` | Write new file |\n| Iteration delta | `review/deltas/iter-{NNN}.jsonl` | Write new file |\n| Pause sentinel | `review/.deep-review-pause` | Read only |\n\n### Iteration Number Derivation\n\n```text\nCount lines in JSONL where type === \"iteration\"\nCurrent iteration = count + 1\nPad to 3 digits: iteration-001.md, iteration-002.md\n```\n\nDo not trust a dispatch-provided iteration number until it matches the JSONL-derived value. If they disagree, use the JSONL-derived value and report the mismatch as an ambiguity edge case.\n\n### Write Safety\n\n- JSONL: append exactly one iteration record; never overwrite or rewrite previous lines.\n- Strategy: use Edit tool to modify specific sections; never use Write to replace the whole file.\n- Iteration file: create a new file; it must not already exist.\n- Review target files are READ-ONLY.\n- Only write to `review/iterations/iteration-NNN.md`, `review/deep-review-strategy.md`, `review/deep-review-state.jsonl`, and the write-once `review/deltas/iter-NNN.jsonl`.\n- NEVER write config, findings registry, reducer outputs, dashboards, reports, source files, command files, skill files, canonical agent files, or runtime mirrors.\n- Before every write, restate the resolved path mentally against the review packet root. If it is outside the packet, stop.\n\n---\n\n## 5. ADVERSARIAL SELF-CHECK (Tiered)\n\nAdapted from @review Hunter/Skeptic/Referee protocol.\n\n### P0 Candidate --> Full 3-Pass\n\nRun all three passes in the same iteration BEFORE writing to JSONL:\n\n1. **HUNTER**: cast a wide net; ask what could go wrong and what is missing.\n2. **SKEPTIC**: try to disprove each finding; check project context, severity inflation, and phantom issues.\n3. **REFEREE**: weigh evidence vs challenge; only confirmed findings enter the iteration file, and uncertain findings are downgraded.\n\n### Gate-Relevant P1 --> Compact Skeptic/Referee\n\n- Run abbreviated skeptic challenge + referee verdict.\n- Document the challenge in the finding's claim-adjudication packet.\n\n### P2 --> No Self-Check\n\n- Severity is too low to warrant Hunter/Skeptic/Referee overhead.\n- Still document evidence and impact.\n\n### At Synthesis\n\n- The orchestrator rechecks carried-forward P0/P1 findings.\n\n**Sycophancy Warning:** If you notice yourself wanting to inflate findings to seem thorough or dismiss issues to avoid conflict, trust the evidence instead.\n\n---\n\n## 6. RULES\n\n### ALWAYS\n\n1. Validate packet boundary and required inputs before review actions.\n2. Read state files BEFORE any review action.\n3. Focus one dimension per iteration unless cross-referencing is explicitly selected.\n4. Choose and record a budget profile before analysis.\n5. Externalize all findings to the iteration file; never hold findings only in context.\n6. Update strategy after review.\n7. Append exactly one JSONL iteration record after the iteration file and strategy are coherent.\n8. Report newFindingsRatio + noveltyJustification honestly.\n9. Cite file:line evidence for every finding.\n10. Run Hunter/Skeptic/Referee for P0 candidates and emit typed claim-adjudication packets for every new P0/P1.\n11. Respect exhausted approaches; never retry them.\n12. Document ruled-out issues and edge cases per iteration.\n13. Name external integration touchpoints explicitly when they influence scope, routing, traceability, or findings.\n14. Verify artifact existence and JSONL/strategy consistency before claiming completion.\n15. Treat review target files as READ-ONLY.\n\n### NEVER\n\n1. Dispatch sub-agents or use Task tool.\n2. Hold findings in context without writing to files.\n3. Exceed tool budget (max 13 calls).\n4. Ask the user questions.\n5. Skip convergence data: newFindingsRatio and noveltyJustification.\n6. Modify config after init.\n7. Edit review target files.\n8. Fabricate findings or inflate severity.\n9. Overwrite `deep-review-state.jsonl`.\n10. Skip writing the iteration file.\n11. Write outside the resolved local-owner review packet.\n12. Treat reducer-owned files as writable.\n13. Treat ambiguity, missing optional evidence, or partial success as a silent pass.\n14. Treat a command, YAML workflow, skill, MCP/code tool, caller agent, or runtime mirror as covered without naming the exact surface checked.\n15. Claim `complete` when output verification failed, was skipped, or only partially succeeded.\n\n### ESCALATE\n\n1. P0 found that could cause immediate harm.\n2. Findings contradict prior iteration conclusions.\n3. Review scope appears insufficient for the review target.\n4. State files are missing or corrupted; report `error`.\n5. Tool failures prevent review; report `timeout`.\n6. Dispatch context, config, strategy, and JSONL disagree on lineage or iteration number.\n7. Required caller, command, workflow, skill, MCP/code-tool, or mirror evidence is missing for a traceability claim.\n\n---\n\n## 7. OUTPUT VERIFICATION\n\n### Iron Law\n\n**NEVER claim completion without verifiable evidence.** Every output assertion must be backed by file existence, content verification, or tool output.\n\n### Pre-Delivery Checklist\n\n- [x] Packet boundary, writable paths, state files, focus, and budget profile verified.\n- [x] Review actions completed or blocked/clean status justified.\n- [x] Edge cases classified.\n- [x] Findings cite file:line evidence.\n- [x] P0 Hunter/Skeptic/Referee and P0/P1 claim-adjudication packets completed when applicable.\n- [x] Iteration artifact, strategy update, and single JSONL append completed.\n- [x] JSONL matches artifact counts, focus, status, ruledOut, budgetProfile, and edgeCases.\n- [x] Config, registry, reducer outputs, dashboards, reports, commands, skills, canonical agent files, runtime mirrors, and review target files were not modified.\n- [x] Traceability, integration evidence, newFindingsRatio, exhausted approaches, and sub-agent prohibition checked.\n\nIf any item fails, fix it before returning. If unfixable, report the specific failure with status `error`.\n\n### Iteration Completion Report\n\nReturn this field skeleton to the dispatcher:\n\n- `## Review Iteration [N] Complete`\n- Focus\n- Findings: total plus P0/P1/P2 counts\n- newFindingsRatio\n- Dimensions completed / remaining\n- Edge cases\n- Integration evidence\n- Recommended next focus\n- Files written: iteration artifact, JSONL append, strategy update\n- Status: `complete | timeout | error | stuck | insight | thought`\n\nFor non-`complete` statuses, replace the heading with `## Review Iteration [N] Partial` or `## Review Iteration Error` and include verified work, unverified work, files written, and next safe recovery focus.\n\n---\n\n## 8. ANTI-PATTERNS\n\n| Anti-Pattern | Why It Fails | Correct Approach |\n|-------------|-------------|------------------|\n| Reviewing outside scope | Wastes iteration on irrelevant code | Stay within declared review target |\n| Inflating findings | Phantom issues delay convergence and erode trust | Use evidence-based severity |\n| Skipping self-check | False P0s waste remediation effort | P0 MUST have Hunter/Skeptic/Referee |\n| Editing review target | Violates read-only contract | NEVER modify code under review |\n| Generic findings | Unactionable without specific location | Cite file:line for every finding |\n| Exceeding budget | Timeout risks losing iteration work | Respect max 13 calls; write what you have |\n| Skip reading state | Repeats prior work and ignores exhausted approaches | Read JSONL + strategy first |\n| Hold findings in memory | Loses continuity | Write everything to iteration-NNN.md |\n| Silent ambiguity | Reducer and operator cannot tell what was actually reviewed | Record ambiguity and chosen fallback |\n| Contradiction cherry-picking | Picks convenient evidence and hides risk | Cite both sides and adjudicate or mark `insight` |\n| Dependency masking | Missing evidence appears as a pass | Mark blocked/notApplicable or return error |\n| Complete-on-partial | Misleads convergence and release decisions | Use timeout/error/stuck/insight/thought honestly |\n| Anonymous integration claim | Cannot be audited by reducer, caller, or operator | Name the exact command, workflow, skill, MCP/code tool, caller agent, or mirror |\n| Mirror-as-source-of-truth | Hides packaging drift and weakens canonical evaluation | Treat mirrors as read-only downstream packaging surfaces |\n| Reducer overwrite | Corrupts canonical finding state | Let the orchestrator/reducer refresh registries, dashboards, and reports |\n\n---\n\n## 9. SUMMARY\n\n```\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│            @deep-review                  │\n├──────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│ AUTHORITY                                │\n│  ├─► Review code quality (read-only)     │\n│  ├─► Produce P0/P1/P2 findings            │\n│  ├─► Disclose edge cases explicitly      │\n│  ├─► Name integration touchpoints        │\n│  ├─► Write iteration artifacts           │\n│  └─► Update strategy + JSONL             │\n├──────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│ WORKFLOW                                 │\n│  Validate Inputs ─► Read State ─►        │\n│  Focus Dimension ─► Execute Review ─►    │\n│  Resolve Edges ─► Classify Findings ─►   │\n│  Write Iteration ─► Update Strategy ─►   │\n│  Append JSONL ─► Verify Outputs          │\n├──────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│ LIMITS                                   │\n│  ├─► LEAF-only (no sub-agents)           │\n│  ├─► Review target READ-ONLY             │\n│  ├─► 9-12 tool calls (max 13)            │\n│  ├─► No silent partial success           │\n│  ├─► No mirror/command/skill edits       │\n│  ├─► No WebFetch                         │\n│  └─► Autonomous (no user interaction)    │\n└──────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":571,"totalLines":571,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/agents/deep-review.md","time":{"start":1783915559407,"end":1783915559428}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0df59b61eea8d697016a546427544881919285a1050aa32dca"}},"id":"prt_f59a739ec001kaGRpfY55h9xvW","sessionID":"ses_0a65ac472ffeDn3G1fX5LbU2k8","messageID":"msg_f59a6ea830011kqj0WvDYGJREd"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783915559446,"sessionID":"ses_0a65ac472ffeDn3G1fX5LbU2k8","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_00Ws6M30puxXebXHPeh9haKZ","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml","offset":634,"limit":800},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n634:                fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows = numeric count of required closed-gate replay rows marked PASS with evidence\n635:                candidate_coverage_gate_pass = boolean\n636:                candidate_coverage_search_debt_json = JSON array of reducer-owned searchDebt obligations blocking STOP, else []\n637:                candidate_coverage_missing_json = JSON array of required bug classes not present in candidateCoverage.covered, else []\n638:                graphless_fallback_gate_pass = boolean\n639:                graphless_fallback_mode = latest reducer-owned searchCoverage.graphCoverageMode value\n640:                graphless_fallback_missing_json = JSON array of required bug classes without cited fallback ledger rows, else []\n641:                graphless_fallback_unavailability_reason = explicit reason when graphCoverageMode == \"unavailable_blocked\", else empty string\n642:                recovery_strategy = one-line hint describing the next review action needed to satisfy the failed gates; combine candidateCoverageGate and graphlessFallbackGate recovery guidance when both fail (when claimAdjudicationGate is the failing gate, prefer the step-0 recovery_strategy already set)\n643:           6. COMBINED STOP RULE:\n644:                a) if STOP is legal AND graph_decision == \"STOP_ALLOWED\": decision = \"STOP\"\n645:                b) if STOP is legal AND graph_decision == \"STOP_BLOCKED\":\n646:                     decision = \"BLOCKED\"\n647:                     stop_blocked = true\n648:                     stopReason = \"blockedStop\"\n649:                     # Blocked-stop closure: blockedBy must be string[] per the\n650:                     # published review blocked-stop contract. Extract the `.type`\n651:                     # field from each structured graph blocker; preserve the full\n652:                     # objects in graph_blocker_detail_json for operator inspection.\n653:                     blocked_by_json = JSON.stringify(graph_blockers_json.map(b => typeof b === \"string\" ? b : (b && b.type) || \"graph_blocker\"))\n654:                     blocked_by_csv = graph_blockers_csv\n655:                     graph_blocker_detail_json = graph_blockers_json\n656:                     recovery_strategy = \"Resolve review coverage-graph blockers before stopping.\"\n657:                c) if STOP is legal AND graph_decision == \"CONTINUE\":\n658:                     decision = \"CONTINUE\"\n659:                     stop_blocked = false\n660:                     reason = \"graph_convergence_continue\"\n661:                d) else keep the existing STUCK_RECOVERY or CONTINUE outcome\n662:         outputs:\n663:           - decision: \"STOP | BLOCKED | STUCK_RECOVERY | CONTINUE\"\n664:           - reason: \"Human-readable stop reason\"\n665:           - stop_blocked: \"Boolean true when STOP is vetoed by inline legal-stop gates or graph_decision == STOP_BLOCKED\"\n666:           - blocked_by_json: \"JSON array of failed legal-stop gates when decision == BLOCKED\"\n667:           - blocked_by_csv: \"Comma-separated list of failed legal-stop gates when decision == BLOCKED\"\n668:           - convergence_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for convergenceGate\"\n669:           - convergence_gate_score: \"Numeric score recorded for convergenceGate\"\n670:           - dimension_coverage_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for dimensionCoverageGate\"\n671:           - dimension_coverage_gate_covered_json: \"JSON array of covered review dimensions\"\n672:           - dimension_coverage_gate_missing_json: \"JSON array of missing review dimensions\"\n673:           - p0_resolution_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for p0ResolutionGate\"\n674:           - active_p0_count: \"Active P0 finding count at stop-check time\"\n675:           - evidence_density_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for evidenceDensityGate\"\n676:           - avg_evidence_per_finding: \"Numeric evidence density for active findings\"\n677:           - hotspot_saturation_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for hotspotSaturationGate\"\n678:           - claim_adjudication_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for claimAdjudicationGate (false vetoes STOP)\"\n679:           - claim_adjudication_active_count: \"Count of active P0/P1 findings evaluated by claimAdjudicationGate\"\n680:           - fix_completeness_replay_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for fixCompletenessReplayGate (false vetoes STOP on security-sensitive fix reruns)\"\n681:           - security_sensitive_fix_scope: \"Boolean true when the review is a security-sensitive fix rerun\"\n682:           - fix_completeness_replay_required_rows: \"Count of closed-gate replay rows required before STOP\"\n683:           - fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows: \"Count of required closed-gate replay rows that passed with evidence\"\n684:           - candidate_coverage_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for candidateCoverageGate (false vetoes STOP for unresolved reducer-owned search debt or uncovered required bug classes)\"\n685:           - candidate_coverage_search_debt_json: \"JSON array of reducer-owned searchDebt obligations used as blocked-stop evidence\"\n686:           - candidate_coverage_missing_json: \"JSON array of required bug classes missing from candidateCoverage.covered\"\n687:           - graphless_fallback_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for graphlessFallbackGate (false vetoes STOP when graphless fallback evidence is absent or unavailable_blocked)\"\n688:           - graphless_fallback_mode: \"Latest reducer-owned searchCoverage.graphCoverageMode value\"\n689:           - graphless_fallback_missing_json: \"JSON array of required bug classes missing cited fallback ledger rows\"\n690:           - graphless_fallback_unavailability_reason: \"Explicit unavailability reason when graphCoverageMode == unavailable_blocked\"\n691:           - graph_decision: \"CONTINUE | STOP_ALLOWED | STOP_BLOCKED from step_graph_convergence\"\n692:           - graph_signals_json: \"JSON object returned by graph convergence\"\n693:           - graph_blockers_json: \"JSON array of graph blockers\"\n694:           - graph_blockers_csv: \"Comma-separated graph blocker summary\"\n695:           - recovery_strategy: \"One-line hint describing the next review action when decision == BLOCKED or STUCK_RECOVERY\"\n696: \n697:       step_emit_blocked_stop:\n698:         action: \"Persist blocked-stop evidence whenever the review legal-stop decision tree vetoes STOP\"\n699:         if_blocked:\n700:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"blocked_stop\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"blockedBy\":{blocked_by_json},\"gateResults\":{\"convergenceGate\":{\"pass\":{convergence_gate_pass},\"score\":{convergence_gate_score}},\"dimensionCoverageGate\":{\"pass\":{dimension_coverage_gate_pass},\"covered\":{dimension_coverage_gate_covered_json},\"missing\":{dimension_coverage_gate_missing_json}},\"p0ResolutionGate\":{\"pass\":{p0_resolution_gate_pass},\"activeP0\":{active_p0_count}},\"evidenceDensityGate\":{\"pass\":{evidence_density_gate_pass},\"avgEvidencePerFinding\":{avg_evidence_per_finding}},\"hotspotSaturationGate\":{\"pass\":{hotspot_saturation_gate_pass}},\"claimAdjudicationGate\":{\"pass\":{claim_adjudication_gate_pass},\"activeP0P1\":{claim_adjudication_active_count}},\"fixCompletenessReplayGate\":{\"pass\":{fix_completeness_replay_gate_pass},\"securitySensitive\":{security_sensitive_fix_scope},\"requiredRows\":{fix_completeness_replay_required_rows},\"passingRows\":{fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows}},\"candidateCoverageGate\":{\"pass\":{candidate_coverage_gate_pass},\"searchDebt\":{candidate_coverage_search_debt_json},\"missing\":{candidate_coverage_missing_json}},\"graphlessFallbackGate\":{\"pass\":{graphless_fallback_gate_pass},\"mode\":\"{graphless_fallback_mode}\",\"missing\":{graphless_fallback_missing_json},\"unavailabilityReason\":\"{graphless_fallback_unavailability_reason}\"}},\"graphBlockerDetail\":{graph_blockers_json},\"recoveryStrategy\":\"{recovery_strategy}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n701:           log: \"Blocked STOP persisted for review loop. Failed gates: {blocked_by_csv}. Recovery strategy: {recovery_strategy}\"\n702:         if_not_blocked:\n703:           proceed: true\n704: \n705:       step_handle_convergence:\n706:         action: \"Act on convergence decision\"\n707:         if_stop:\n708:           branch_on: \"convergence_mode == 'divergent' AND reason == 'all_dimensions_clean'\"\n709:           if_divergent_eligible:\n710:             eligibility_contract:\n711:               required_decision: \"STOP\"\n712:               eligible_reasons: [all_dimensions_clean]\n713:               excluded_reasons: [maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, error, manualStop, userPaused]\n714:               fail_closed: \"Any missing or ambiguous reason uses if_existing_terminal_path without preparing a pivot. The nine legal-stop gates have already run and remain unchanged.\"\n715:             steps:\n716:               step_prepare_divergent_pivot:\n717:                 action: \"Generate state-grounded read-only review candidates and prepare or resume the pivot transaction\"\n718:                 command: |\n719:                   node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n720:                   import {\n721:                     buildReviewPivotPreparationInput,\n722:                     renderReviewPivotSeatPrompt,\n723:                   } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/scripts/divergent-review-pivot.ts';\n724:                   import {\n725:                     preparePivotTransaction,\n726:                   } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/divergent-pivot.ts';\n727: \n728:                   const input = buildReviewPivotPreparationInput({\n729:                     artifactRoot: '{state_paths.packet_dir}',\n730:                     configPath: '{state_paths.config}',\n731:                     stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n732:                     strategyPath: '{state_paths.strategy}',\n733:                     registryPath: '{state_paths.findings_registry}',\n734:                     currentIteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n735:                     maxIterations: Number('{max_iterations}'),\n736:                     triggerReason: '{reason}',\n737:                   });\n738:                   const prepared = await preparePivotTransaction(input);\n739:                   const seatPrompts = prepared.status === 'pending'\n740:                     ? Object.fromEntries(prepared.missingSeats.map((seat) => [\n741:                         seat.id,\n742:                         renderReviewPivotSeatPrompt(seat, prepared.dispatchContext),\n743:                       ]))\n744:                     : {};\n745:                   process.stdout.write(`${JSON.stringify({\n746:                     ...prepared,\n747:                     seatPrompts,\n748:                     boundaryRejections: input.boundaryRejections,\n749:                   })}\\n`);\n750:                   EOF\n751:                 working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n752:                 outputs:\n753:                   - pivot_prepare_json: \"The complete parsed JSON result\"\n754:                   - pivot_prepare_status: \"status from the prepare result\"\n755:                   - pivot_id: \"pivotId from the prepare result\"\n756:                   - pivot_paths_json: \"paths from the prepare result as JSON\"\n757:                   - pivot_resumed: \"resumed from the prepare result\"\n758:                   - pivot_missing_seat_ids: \"missingSeats ids from a pending result\"\n759:                   - pivot_seat_001_json: \"The seat-001 mandate object from missingSeats\"\n760:                   - pivot_seat_002_json: \"The seat-002 mandate object from missingSeats\"\n761:                   - pivot_seat_003_json: \"The seat-003 mandate object from missingSeats\"\n762:                   - pivot_seat_001_prompt: \"seatPrompts['seat-001']\"\n763:                   - pivot_seat_002_prompt: \"seatPrompts['seat-002']\"\n764:                   - pivot_seat_003_prompt: \"seatPrompts['seat-003']\"\n765:                   - pivot_dispatch_context_json: \"dispatchContext from a pending result as JSON\"\n766:                 short_circuit: \"When status is completed or failed, skip all dispatch and record steps and bind this result as pivot_result.\"\n767: \n768:               step_dispatch_pivot_seat_001:\n769:                 action: \"Natively dispatch the analytical read-only review direction-selection seat\"\n770:                 skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending' or pivot_missing_seat_ids does not contain 'seat-001'\"\n771:                 capture_timing: true\n772:                 if_native:\n773:                   dispatch:\n774:                     agent: deep-review\n775:                     model: opus\n776:                     context_source: \"pivot_seat_001_prompt\"\n777:                   wait_for_completion: true\n778:                 failure_contract: \"A native dispatch failure binds status=rejected, a {name,message} error, and the measured timestamps/duration, then proceeds to step_record_pivot_seat_001.\"\n779:                 outputs:\n780:                   - pivot_seat_001_dispatch_status: \"fulfilled or rejected\"\n781:                   - pivot_seat_001_output_json: \"Raw native return serialized as JSON when fulfilled\"\n782:                   - pivot_seat_001_error_json: \"{name,message} when rejected\"\n783:                   - pivot_seat_001_started_at_iso: \"Dispatch start timestamp\"\n784:                   - pivot_seat_001_completed_at_iso: \"Dispatch completion timestamp\"\n785:                   - pivot_seat_001_duration_ms: \"Dispatch duration in milliseconds\"\n786: \n787:               step_record_pivot_seat_001:\n788:                 action: \"Durably record the seat-001 native dispatch outcome\"\n789:                 skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending' or pivot_missing_seat_ids does not contain 'seat-001'\"\n790:                 command: |\n791:                   node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n792:                   import { recordPivotSeatResult } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/divergent-pivot.ts';\n793:                   const status = '{pivot_seat_001_dispatch_status}';\n794:                   const outcome = status === 'fulfilled'\n795:                     ? { status, output: {pivot_seat_001_output_json}, startedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_001_started_at_iso}', completedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_001_completed_at_iso}', durationMs: Number('{pivot_seat_001_duration_ms}') }\n796:                     : { status: 'rejected', error: {pivot_seat_001_error_json}, startedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_001_started_at_iso}', completedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_001_completed_at_iso}', durationMs: Number('{pivot_seat_001_duration_ms}') };\n797:                   process.stdout.write(`${JSON.stringify(recordPivotSeatResult({ paths: {pivot_paths_json}, pivotId: '{pivot_id}', seat: {pivot_seat_001_json}, outcome }))}\\n`);\n798:                   EOF\n799:                 working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n800: \n801:               step_dispatch_pivot_seat_002:\n802:                 action: \"Natively dispatch the critical read-only review direction-selection seat\"\n803:                 skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending' or pivot_missing_seat_ids does not contain 'seat-002'\"\n804:                 capture_timing: true\n805:                 if_native:\n806:                   dispatch:\n807:                     agent: deep-review\n808:                     model: opus\n809:                     context_source: \"pivot_seat_002_prompt\"\n810:                   wait_for_completion: true\n811:                 failure_contract: \"A native dispatch failure binds status=rejected, a {name,message} error, and the measured timestamps/duration, then proceeds to step_record_pivot_seat_002.\"\n812:                 outputs:\n813:                   - pivot_seat_002_dispatch_status: \"fulfilled or rejected\"\n814:                   - pivot_seat_002_output_json: \"Raw native return serialized as JSON when fulfilled\"\n815:                   - pivot_seat_002_error_json: \"{name,message} when rejected\"\n816:                   - pivot_seat_002_started_at_iso: \"Dispatch start timestamp\"\n817:                   - pivot_seat_002_completed_at_iso: \"Dispatch completion timestamp\"\n818:                   - pivot_seat_002_duration_ms: \"Dispatch duration in milliseconds\"\n819: \n820:               step_record_pivot_seat_002:\n821:                 action: \"Durably record the seat-002 native dispatch outcome\"\n822:                 skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending' or pivot_missing_seat_ids does not contain 'seat-002'\"\n823:                 command: |\n824:                   node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n825:                   import { recordPivotSeatResult } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/divergent-pivot.ts';\n826:                   const status = '{pivot_seat_002_dispatch_status}';\n827:                   const outcome = status === 'fulfilled'\n828:                     ? { status, output: {pivot_seat_002_output_json}, startedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_002_started_at_iso}', completedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_002_completed_at_iso}', durationMs: Number('{pivot_seat_002_duration_ms}') }\n829:                     : { status: 'rejected', error: {pivot_seat_002_error_json}, startedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_002_started_at_iso}', completedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_002_completed_at_iso}', durationMs: Number('{pivot_seat_002_duration_ms}') };\n830:                   process.stdout.write(`${JSON.stringify(recordPivotSeatResult({ paths: {pivot_paths_json}, pivotId: '{pivot_id}', seat: {pivot_seat_002_json}, outcome }))}\\n`);\n831:                   EOF\n832:                 working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n833: \n834:               step_dispatch_pivot_seat_003:\n835:                 action: \"Natively dispatch the pragmatic read-only review direction-selection seat\"\n836:                 skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending' or pivot_missing_seat_ids does not contain 'seat-003'\"\n837:                 capture_timing: true\n838:                 if_native:\n839:                   dispatch:\n840:                     agent: deep-review\n841:                     model: opus\n842:                     context_source: \"pivot_seat_003_prompt\"\n843:                   wait_for_completion: true\n844:                 failure_contract: \"A native dispatch failure binds status=rejected, a {name,message} error, and the measured timestamps/duration, then proceeds to step_record_pivot_seat_003.\"\n845:                 outputs:\n846:                   - pivot_seat_003_dispatch_status: \"fulfilled or rejected\"\n847:                   - pivot_seat_003_output_json: \"Raw native return serialized as JSON when fulfilled\"\n848:                   - pivot_seat_003_error_json: \"{name,message} when rejected\"\n849:                   - pivot_seat_003_started_at_iso: \"Dispatch start timestamp\"\n850:                   - pivot_seat_003_completed_at_iso: \"Dispatch completion timestamp\"\n851:                   - pivot_seat_003_duration_ms: \"Dispatch duration in milliseconds\"\n852: \n853:               step_record_pivot_seat_003:\n854:                 action: \"Durably record the seat-003 native dispatch outcome\"\n855:                 skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending' or pivot_missing_seat_ids does not contain 'seat-003'\"\n856:                 command: |\n857:                   node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n858:                   import { recordPivotSeatResult } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/divergent-pivot.ts';\n859:                   const status = '{pivot_seat_003_dispatch_status}';\n860:                   const outcome = status === 'fulfilled'\n861:                     ? { status, output: {pivot_seat_003_output_json}, startedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_003_started_at_iso}', completedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_003_completed_at_iso}', durationMs: Number('{pivot_seat_003_duration_ms}') }\n862:                     : { status: 'rejected', error: {pivot_seat_003_error_json}, startedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_003_started_at_iso}', completedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_003_completed_at_iso}', durationMs: Number('{pivot_seat_003_duration_ms}') };\n863:                   process.stdout.write(`${JSON.stringify(recordPivotSeatResult({ paths: {pivot_paths_json}, pivotId: '{pivot_id}', seat: {pivot_seat_003_json}, outcome }))}\\n`);\n864:                   EOF\n865:                 working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n866: \n867:               step_finalize_divergent_pivot:\n868:                 action: \"Finalize the prepared pivot after all missing native seats are durable\"\n869:                 skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending'\"\n870:                 command: |\n871:                   node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n872:                   import { finalizePivotTransaction } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/divergent-pivot.ts';\n873:                   process.stdout.write(`${JSON.stringify(finalizePivotTransaction({ paths: {pivot_paths_json}, pivotId: '{pivot_id}', resumed: {pivot_resumed} }))}\\n`);\n874:                   EOF\n875:                 working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n876:                 outputs:\n877:                   - pivot_finalize_json: \"The complete parsed final result\"\n878: \n879:               step_resolve_divergent_pivot_result:\n880:                 action: \"Use prepare's terminal result on resume/short-circuit, otherwise use finalize's result\"\n881:                 branch_on: \"pivot_prepare_status\"\n882:                 if_pending: { bind: { pivot_result: \"{pivot_finalize_json}\" } }\n883:                 if_completed_or_failed: { bind: { pivot_result: \"{pivot_prepare_json}\" } }\n884: \n885:               step_apply_divergent_pivot_result:\n886:                 action: \"Adopt a successful read-only review direction or fail closed to the existing synthesis path\"\n887:                 branch_on: \"pivot_result.status\"\n888:                 if_completed:\n889:                   set:\n890:                     next_dimension: \"{pivot_result.restoredFocus}\"\n891:                     pivot_lineage: \"Pivot {pivot_result.pivotId} selected {pivot_result.selectedCandidate.id} from source iteration {current_iteration}.\"\n892:                     saturated_directions: \"{pivot_result.completedEvent.saturatedDirections}\"\n893:                   command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder}\"\n894:                   log: \"Divergent review pivot {pivot_result.pivotId} restored focus to {pivot_result.restoredFocus}; continuing iteration {current_iteration}.\"\n895:                   proceed_to: step_normalize_pause_events\n896:                 if_failed:\n897:                   log: \"Divergent review pivot {pivot_result.pivotId} failed closed ({pivot_result.failureReason}); proceeding to synthesis.\"\n898:                   skip_to: phase_synthesis\n899:             on_error:\n900:               log: \"Divergent review pivot integration error; failing closed to the existing synthesis path.\"\n901:               skip_to: phase_synthesis\n902:           if_existing_terminal_path:\n903:             log: \"Loop stopping. Reason: {reason}\"\n904:             skip_to: phase_synthesis\n905:         if_blocked:\n906:           log: \"Legal-stop gates blocked STOP. Failed gates: {blocked_by_csv}. Continuing review.\"\n907:         if_stuck_recovery:\n908:           log: \"Stuck detected ({stuck_count} consecutive no-progress). Entering recovery.\"\n909:           recovery_strategies:\n910:             - \"Change granularity: file-level → function-level → line-level review\"\n911:             - \"Traceability protocol replay: re-run unresolved core or overlay checks\"\n912:             - \"Escalate severity review: re-examine P2 findings for potential P1 upgrades\"\n913:           pivot_target: \"Pivot to the least-covered dimension (the review dimension with the fewest iteration passes and lowest coverage ratio).\"\n914:           set:\n915:             next_dimension: \"RECOVERY: {recovery_strategy}. Least-covered dimension: {least_explored}\"\n916:             pending_stop_event: \"stuck_recovery\"\n917:             pending_stop_reason: \"stuckRecovery\"\n918:             pending_stop_detail: \"Recovery path activated after repeated no-progress iterations\"\n919:           reset: { stuck_count: 0 }\n920:         if_continue:\n921:           log: \"Iteration {current_iteration}: Continuing. Dimension: {next_dimension}\"\n922: \n923:       step_normalize_pause_events:\n924:         action: \"Rewrite raw pause and recovery events to the frozen STOP_REASONS enum at emission time: converged, maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, error, manualStop, userPaused\"\n925:         if_pending_pause_event:\n926:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"reason\":\"{pending_stop_detail}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n927:           message: \"Review paused. Delete review/.deep-review-pause to resume.\"\n928:           reset:\n929:             pending_stop_event: null\n930:             pending_stop_reason: null\n931:             pending_stop_detail: null\n932:           halt: true\n933:         if_pending_stuck_recovery:\n934:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"stopReason\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"fromIteration\":{current_iteration},\"strategy\":\"{recovery_strategy}\",\"targetDimension\":\"{least_explored}\",\"outcome\":\"pending\",\"reason\":\"{pending_stop_detail}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n935:           reset:\n936:             pending_stop_event: null\n937:             pending_stop_reason: null\n938:             pending_stop_detail: null\n939:         if_no_pending_event:\n940:           proceed: true\n941: \n942:       step_generate_state_summary:\n943:         action: \"Generate compact state summary for dispatch context (~200 tokens)\"\n944:         generate: |\n945:           STATE SUMMARY (auto-generated):\n946:           Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\n947:           Dimension: {next_dimension}\n948:           Prior Findings: P0={p0_count} P1={p1_count} P2={p2_count}\n949:           Dimension Coverage: {dimensions_covered_list} ({dimension_coverage})\n950:           Traceability: core={core_protocol_status} overlay={overlay_protocol_status}\n951:           {resource_map_prompt_line}\n952:           Coverage Age: {coverage_age}\n953:           Last 2 ratios: {ratio_prev} -> {ratio_latest}\n954:           Stuck count: {stuck_count}\n955:           Provisional Verdict: {PASS|CONDITIONAL|FAIL|PENDING} hasAdvisories={has_advisories}\n956: \n957:       step_marker_scan:\n958:         action: \"H-2 loop-prevention guard: scan previous iteration's rendered prompt for nested review marker\"\n959:         algorithm: |\n960:           if current_iteration > 1:\n961:             PREV_PROMPT_PATH = \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{previous_iteration}.md\"\n962:             if file_exists(PREV_PROMPT_PATH):\n963:               PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE = head -1 of PREV_PROMPT_PATH\n964:               if PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE matches ^(DEEP-REVIEW|DEEP-RESEARCH|CODE-REVIEW)$:\n965:                 log \"ERROR: nested review-of-review loop detected (marker found in previous iteration prompt). Aborting.\"\n966:                 halt with exit code 2\n967:         note: |\n968:           False-positive prevention: only matches when the first line is exactly one of the\n969:           three canonical markers. Markers appearing in comments or body text are ignored.\n970:           True-positive triggers only when a previous iteration's rendered prompt literally\n971:           starts with a deep-loop marker, indicating a nested review-of-review dispatch.\n972: \n973:       step_dispatch_iteration:\n974:         action: \"Dispatch @deep-review agent for one review iteration\"\n975:         resolve_executor:\n976:           source: \"config.executor\"\n977:           loader: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts#parseExecutorConfig\"\n978:         pre_dispatch:\n979:           generate_summary: |\n980:             STATE SUMMARY (auto-generated):\n981:             Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\n982:             Dimension: {next_dimension}\n983:             Prior Findings: P0={p0_count} P1={p1_count} P2={p2_count}\n984:             Dimension Coverage: {dimensions_covered_list} ({dimension_coverage})\n985:             Traceability: core={core_protocol_status} overlay={overlay_protocol_status}\n986:             {resource_map_prompt_line}\n987:             Coverage Age: {coverage_age}\n988:             Last 2 ratios: {ratio_prev} -> {ratio_latest}\n989:             Stuck count: {stuck_count}\n990:             Provisional Verdict: {PASS|CONDITIONAL|FAIL|PENDING} hasAdvisories={has_advisories}\n991:           render_prompt_pack:\n992:             template_path: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl\"\n993:             renderer: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/prompt-pack.ts#renderPromptPack\"\n994:             output_path: \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md\"\n995:             variables:\n996:               state_summary: \"{state_summary}\"\n997:               current_iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n998:               max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n999:               next_dimension: \"{next_dimension}\"\n1000:               review_target: \"{review_target}\"\n1001:               review_scope_files: \"{review_scope_files}\"\n1002:               p0_count: \"{p0_count}\"\n1003:               p1_count: \"{p1_count}\"\n1004:               p2_count: \"{p2_count}\"\n1005:               pivot_lineage: \"{pivot_lineage}\"\n1006:               saturated_directions: \"{saturated_directions}\"\n1007:               state_paths_config: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n1008:               state_paths_state_log: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n1009:               state_paths_findings_registry: \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n1010:               state_paths_strategy: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n1011:               state_paths_iteration_pattern: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n1012:               state_paths_delta_pattern: \"{state_paths.delta_pattern}\"\n1013:         pre_dispatch_audit:\n1014:           skip_when: \"config.executor.kind == 'native'\"\n1015:           call: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts#writeFirstRecordExecutor\"\n1016:           args:\n1017:             stateLogPath: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n1018:             executor: \"{config.executor}\"\n1019:             iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n1020:         branch_on: \"config.executor.kind\"\n1021:         if_native:\n1022:           dispatch:\n1023:             agent: deep-review\n1024:             model: opus\n1025:             context_source: \"rendered_prompt_pack\"\n1026:           wait_for_completion: true\n1027:         if_cli_copilot:\n1028:           command: |\n1029:             node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n1030:             import { readFileSync, writeFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n1031:             import { createHash } from 'node:crypto';\n1032: \n1033:             import { runAuditedExecutorCommand } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts';\n1034:             import { buildCopilotPromptArg } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts';\n1035: \n1036:             const promptPath = '{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md';\n1037:             const prompt = readFileSync(promptPath, 'utf8');\n1038: \n1039:             // Workflow-resolved spec folder is the only legal write authority.\n1040:             // The helper (`validateSpecFolder` inside `buildCopilotPromptArg`)\n1041:             // is the single source of truth for rejecting empty / unresolved\n1042:             // template / whitespace-only / string-coerced empty values. The\n1043:             // YAML hands the raw `{spec_folder}` directly; on rejection the\n1044:             // helper safe-fails to `type:\"missing\", writeIntent:true` (Gate-3\n1045:             // enforcement, --allow-all-tools stripped).\n1046:             const specFolderRaw = '{spec_folder}';\n1047:             const targetAuthority = { type: 'approved', specFolder: specFolderRaw };\n1048: \n1049:             const baseArgs = [\n1050:               '-p',\n1051:               prompt,\n1052:               '--model',\n1053:               '{config.executor.model}',\n1054:               '--allow-all-tools',\n1055:               '--no-ask-user',\n1056:             ];\n1057: \n1058:             const built = buildCopilotPromptArg({\n1059:               promptPath,\n1060:               prompt,\n1061:               targetAuthority,\n1062:               baseArgv: baseArgs,\n1063:             });\n1064: \n1065:             // Large-prompt @PROMPT_PATH wrapper: helper emits a `promptFileBody`\n1066:             // containing `<TARGET AUTHORITY preamble>\\n\\n---\\n\\n<original>`.\n1067:             // Write it to disk so the file Copilot reads via @path opens with\n1068:             // the authority block. Without this, recovered/bootstrap folder\n1069:             // mentions inside the file could still anchor the model.\n1070:             if (built.promptFileBody !== undefined) {\n1071:               writeFileSync(promptPath, built.promptFileBody, 'utf8');\n1072:             }\n1073: \n1074:             // Copilot is routed through the audited executor wrapper so it produces\n1075:             // INTENT + COMPLETION dispatch receipts alongside claude-code/opencode\n1076:             // There is no cli-copilot kind in the executor schema, so it\n1077:             // dispatches as kind:'native' (full env passthrough, no recursion-guard\n1078:             // layer configured for copilot); the receipt still records the real\n1079:             // 'copilot' command + built.argv as facts.\n1080:             const dispatchFacts = {\n1081:               command: 'deep/review',\n1082:               mode: 'review',\n1083:               specFolder: '{spec_folder}',\n1084:               artifactDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}',\n1085:               iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n1086:               executorKind: '{config.executor.kind}',\n1087:               branchId: '{config.executor.kind}',\n1088:               sessionId: '{session_id}',\n1089:               generation: Number('{generation}'),\n1090:             };\n1091:             const dispatchId = 'review-i{current_iteration}-g{generation}';\n1092:             process.exit(\n1093:               runAuditedExecutorCommand({\n1094:                 command: 'copilot',\n1095:                 args: built.argv,\n1096:                 cwd: '{repo_root}',\n1097:                 timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n1098:                 stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n1099:                 executor: {\n1100:                   kind: 'native',\n1101:                   model: '{config.executor.model}',\n1102:                   configDir: null,\n1103:                   reasoningEffort: null,\n1104:                   serviceTier: null,\n1105:                   sandboxMode: null,\n1106:                   timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n1107:                   governor: null,\n1108:                 },\n1109:                 iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n1110:                 receiptDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}/dispatch-receipts',\n1111:                 dispatchId,\n1112:               }),\n1113:             );\n1114:             EOF\n1115:           working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n1116:           timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n1117:           wait_for_completion: true\n1118:           notes:\n1119:             - \"Routed through runAuditedExecutorCommand so copilot produces INTENT + COMPLETION dispatch receipts; built.argv (@PROMPT_PATH or positional) is forwarded verbatim as the receipt facts\"\n1120:             - \"copilot has no stdin support; prompt is positional\"\n1121:             - \"Size check uses 16KB threshold; above that uses @PROMPT_PATH wrapper prompt\"\n1122:             - \"Large-prompt path relies on copilot honoring @path references within its prompt string\"\n1123:             - \"buildCopilotPromptArg attaches a TARGET AUTHORITY preamble bound to the workflow-approved spec folder; recovered context cannot override it (authority guard source: .opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_deep-review_auto.yaml)\"\n1124:             - \"If spec_folder is missing/malformed/unresolved on a write-intent dispatch, the helper enforces plan-only by replacing the prompt with a Gate-3 question and stripping --allow-all-tools\"\n1125:             - \"Large-prompt wrapper mode rewrites the prompt file at promptPath to include the TARGET AUTHORITY preamble (prefix + divider + original body); the argv becomes a bare @promptPath reference\"\n1126:         if_cli_claude_code:\n1127:           command: |\n1128:             node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n1129:             import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n1130:             import { createHash } from 'node:crypto';\n1131: \n1132:             import { runAuditedExecutorCommand } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts';\n1133: \n1134:             const configDir = '{optional_claude_config_dir}';\n1135:             const reasoningEffort = '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}';\n1136:             const executor = {\n1137:               kind: 'cli-claude-code',\n1138:               model: '{config.executor.model}',\n1139:               configDir: configDir || null,\n1140:               reasoningEffort,\n1141:               serviceTier: null,\n1142:               sandboxMode: null,\n1143:               timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n1144:               governor: null,\n1145:             };\n1146:             const args = [\n1147:               '-p',\n1148:               readFileSync('{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md', 'utf8'),\n1149:               '--model',\n1150:               executor.model,\n1151:               '--permission-mode',\n1152:               'acceptEdits',\n1153:               '--output-format',\n1154:               'text',\n1155:             ];\n1156:             if (executor.reasoningEffort) {\n1157:               args.push('--effort', executor.reasoningEffort);\n1158:             }\n1159: \n1160:             // CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR rides through guardContext.env; the CLAUDE_ prefix is\n1161:             // on the cli-claude-code env allowlist so buildExecutorDispatchEnv admits it.\n1162:             const parentEnv = { ...process.env };\n1163:             if (configDir) {\n1164:               parentEnv.CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR = configDir;\n1165:             }\n1166: \n1167:             const dispatchFacts = {\n1168:               command: 'deep/review',\n1169:               mode: 'review',\n1170:               specFolder: '{spec_folder}',\n1171:               artifactDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}',\n1172:               iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n1173:               executorKind: '{config.executor.kind}',\n1174:               branchId: '{config.executor.kind}',\n1175:               sessionId: '{session_id}',\n1176:               generation: Number('{generation}'),\n1177:             };\n1178:             const dispatchId = 'review-i{current_iteration}-g{generation}';\n1179:             process.exit(\n1180:               runAuditedExecutorCommand({\n1181:                 command: 'claude',\n1182:                 args,\n1183:                 cwd: '{repo_root}',\n1184:                 timeoutSeconds: executor.timeoutSeconds,\n1185:                 stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n1186:                 executor,\n1187:                 iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n1188:                 guardContext: { env: parentEnv },\n1189:                 receiptDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}/dispatch-receipts',\n1190:                 dispatchId,\n1191:               }),\n1192:             );\n1193:             EOF\n1194:           working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n1195:           timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n1196:           wait_for_completion: true\n1197:           render_hint:\n1198:             optional_claude_config_dir: |\n1199:               If config.executor.configDir is set and non-null, expand a leading ~ to HOME and bind that path.\n1200:               Otherwise expand to empty string.\n1201:           notes:\n1202:             - \"Routed through runAuditedExecutorCommand so claude-code produces INTENT + COMPLETION dispatch receipts; recursion guard + env allowlist enforced via buildExecutorDispatchEnv\"\n1203:             - \"CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR is forwarded through guardContext.env (CLAUDE_ prefix is allowlisted) so account-specific Claude Code routing is preserved\"\n1204:             - \"permission-mode stays acceptEdits (review's existing iteration-write behavior); claude-code has no serviceTier flag\"\n1205:             - \"claude-code supports --effort for reasoning depth\"\n1206:         if_cli_opencode:\n1207:           command: |\n1208:             node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n1209:             import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n1210:             import { createHash } from 'node:crypto';\n1211: \n1212:             import { runAuditedExecutorCommand } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts';\n1213: \n1214:             const reasoningEffort = '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}';\n1215:             const executor = {\n1216:               kind: 'cli-opencode',\n1217:               model: '{config.executor.model}',\n1218:               configDir: null,\n1219:               reasoningEffort,\n1220:               serviceTier: null,\n1221:               sandboxMode: null,\n1222:               timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n1223:               governor: null,\n1224:             };\n1225:             const promptBody = readFileSync('{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md', 'utf8');\n1226:             const message = 'Resolved route: mode=review; target_agent=@deep-review; execution=single_review_iteration; state_source=externalized_files; do_not_switch_mode=true'\n1227:               + '\\n\\n'\n1228:               + promptBody;\n1229:             const args = [\n1230:               'run',\n1231:               '--model',\n1232:               executor.model,\n1233:               '--format',\n1234:               'json',\n1235:               '--dangerously-skip-permissions',\n1236:               '--pure',\n1237:               '--dir',\n1238:               '{repo_root}',\n1239:             ];\n1240:             if (executor.reasoningEffort) {\n1241:               args.push('--variant', executor.reasoningEffort);\n1242:             }\n1243:             args.push(message);\n1244: \n1245:             const dispatchFacts = {\n1246:               command: 'deep/review',\n1247:               mode: 'review',\n1248:               specFolder: '{spec_folder}',\n1249:               artifactDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}',\n1250:               iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n1251:               executorKind: '{config.executor.kind}',\n1252:               branchId: '{config.executor.kind}',\n1253:               sessionId: '{session_id}',\n1254:               generation: Number('{generation}'),\n1255:             };\n1256:             const dispatchId = 'review-i{current_iteration}-g{generation}';\n1257:             process.exit(\n1258:               runAuditedExecutorCommand({\n1259:                 command: 'opencode',\n1260:                 args,\n1261:                 cwd: '{repo_root}',\n1262:                 timeoutSeconds: executor.timeoutSeconds,\n1263:                 stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n1264:                 executor,\n1265:                 iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n1266:                 // opencode v1.14.39 reads stdin at startup before session creation;\n1267:                 // an empty input gives EOF stdin, equivalent to </dev/null.\n1268:                 input: '',\n1269:                 receiptDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}/dispatch-receipts',\n1270:                 dispatchId,\n1271:               }),\n1272:             );\n1273:             EOF\n1274:           working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n1275:           timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n1276:           wait_for_completion: true\n1277:           notes:\n1278:             - \"Routed through runAuditedExecutorCommand so opencode produces INTENT + COMPLETION dispatch receipts; recursion guard + env allowlist enforced via buildExecutorDispatchEnv\"\n1279:             - \"input:'' yields closed stdin (EOF), equivalent to </dev/null — opencode v1.14.39 reads stdin at startup and hangs at 0% CPU after +60s snapshot prune without it (the `cli-external/cli-opencode` mode's SKILL.md (`.opencode/skills/cli-external/cli-opencode/SKILL.md`) §4 ALWAYS rule)\"\n1280:             - \"opencode run takes a positional message; prompt is the route-proof preamble + iteration body\"\n1281:             - \"--variant maps reasoningEffort to opencode's provider-specific reasoning lever (e.g., high, medium, minimal)\"\n1282:             - \"--dangerously-skip-permissions enables hands-off automation; sandboxMode='read-only' is not currently honored (no opencode equivalent)\"\n1283:             - \"cli-opencode self-invocation guard: this single-executor branch must only run from a non-OpenCode dispatch surface (Claude Code/raw shell). Explicit parallel-detached cli-opencode fan-out is handled by step_fanout_spawn_cli/fanout-run.cjs, not this branch. the `cli-external/cli-opencode` mode's SKILL.md (`.opencode/skills/cli-external/cli-opencode/SKILL.md`) §SELF-INVOCATION PROHIBITED contract is the authoritative gate\"\n1284:         post_dispatch_validate:\n1285:           validator: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/post-dispatch-validate.ts#validateIterationOutputs\"\n1286:           command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/verify-iteration.cjs --loop-type review --artifact-dir {artifact_dir} --iteration {current_iteration}\"\n1287:           command_note: \"Mechanical leaf-reliability gate: exit 0 = complete; non-zero prints one machine reason (iteration_file_missing|iteration_verdict_missing|state_record_missing|route_proof_missing|route_proof_mismatch|delta_file_missing). The script enforces the artifact + route-proof contract instead of trusting the leaf to self-report, and a non-zero exit triggers on_failure.redispatch_once.\"\n1288:           assert_exists: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n1289:           assert_appended: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n1290:           assert_jsonl_fields: [type, iteration, mode, run, status, focus, dimensions, filesReviewed, findingsCount, findingsSummary, findingsNew, findingDetails, newFindingsRatio, sessionId, generation, lineageMode, timestamp, durationMs]\n1291:           route_proof:\n1292:             mode: review\n1293:             target_agent: deep-review\n1294:             agent_definition_loaded: true\n1295:             resolved_route: \"Resolved route: mode=review target_agent=deep-review\"\n1296:           dispatchReceipt:\n1297:             receiptDir: \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/dispatch-receipts\"\n1298:             dispatchId: \"review-i{current_iteration}-g{generation}\"\n1299:           assert_canonical_type: \"iteration\"\n1300:           assert_delta_file_exists: \"{state_paths.delta_pattern}\"\n1301:           assert_delta_file_has_iteration_record: true\n1302:           failure_reasons:\n1303:             - iteration_file_missing\n1304:             - iteration_file_empty\n1305:             - jsonl_not_appended\n1306:             - jsonl_missing_fields\n1307:             - jsonl_parse_error\n1308:             - jsonl_wrong_type\n1309:             - delta_file_missing\n1310:             - delta_file_empty\n1311:             - delta_file_missing_iteration_record\n1312:             - executor_missing\n1313:             - dispatch_failure_logged\n1314:             - v2_missing_ledger\n1315:             - v2_uncited_ledger_row\n1316:             - v2_broken_linked_finding\n1317:             - v2_shallow_finding_details\n1318:             - delta_iteration_id_mismatch\n1319:             - state_delta_iteration_mismatch\n1320:             - route_proof_missing\n1321:             - route_proof_mismatch\n1322:           warning_surface:\n1323:             source: \"result.warnings\"\n1324:             action: \"emit schema_advisory canonical conflict event\"\n1325:             severity: \"advisory\"\n1326:             event_shape: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"schema_advisory\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"iteration\":{current_iteration},\"warnings\":{result.warnings},\"severity\":\"advisory\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n1327:             note: \"Warnings do not fail dispatch. Hard failures still emit schema_mismatch through on_failure.\"\n1328:           on_failure:\n1329:             action: \"emit schema_mismatch canonical conflict event\"\n1330:             redispatch_once: \"On the FIRST failure of the mechanical command check for this iteration, re-run step_dispatch_iteration exactly once for the same iteration number, then re-run the check. If it still fails, record the iteration as error (per step_evaluate_results.on_missing_outputs) and continue. Never re-dispatch a given iteration more than once.\"\n1331:             escalation: \"After 3 consecutive failures across iterations, trigger stuck_recovery event with diagnostic context\"\n1332:         record_executor_audit:\n1333:           skip_when: \"config.executor.kind == 'native'\"\n1334:           target: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n1335:           field: \"executor\"\n1336:           value:\n1337:             kind: \"{config.executor.kind}\"\n1338:             model: \"{config.executor.model}\"\n1339:             reasoningEffort: \"{config.executor.reasoningEffort}\"\n1340:             serviceTier: \"{config.executor.serviceTier}\"\n1341: \n1342:       step_evaluate_results:\n1343:         action: \"Verify iteration outputs and extract metrics\"\n1344:         verify:\n1345:           - file_exists: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n1346:           - jsonl_appended: \"New iteration record in state.jsonl\"\n1347:           - strategy_updated: \"Strategy.md has been modified\"\n1348:         extract:\n1349:           - newFindingsRatio: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n1350:           - findings_count: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n1351:           - severity_counts: \"From latest JSONL iteration record (P0, P1, P2)\"\n1352:           - dimensions: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n1353:           - files_reviewed: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n1354:           - status: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n1355:           - reviewed_artifacts: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n1356:           - traceability_checks: \"From latest JSONL iteration record when present\"\n1357:         on_missing_outputs:\n1358:           action: \"Mark iteration as 'error', continue to next\"\n1359:           # Canonical iteration record: include sessionId, generation, durationMs so the reducer can persist\n1360:           # the failure without dropping the iteration. Schema source: state_format.md §Iteration Records.\n1361:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":{current_iteration},\"run\":{current_iteration},\"mode\":\"review\",\"status\":\"error\",\"focus\":\"{next_dimension}\",\"dimensions\":[\"{next_dimension}\"],\"filesReviewed\":[],\"findingsCount\":0,\"findingsSummary\":{\"P0\":0,\"P1\":0,\"P2\":0},\"findingsNew\":{\"P0\":0,\"P1\":0,\"P2\":0},\"findingDetails\":[],\"traceabilityChecks\":{\"summary\":{\"required\":0,\"executed\":0,\"pass\":0,\"partial\":0,\"fail\":0,\"blocked\":0,\"notApplicable\":0,\"gatingFailures\":0},\"results\":[]},\"newFindingsRatio\":0.0,\"durationMs\":0,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation},\"lineageMode\":\"{config.lineage.lineageMode}\"}'\n1362: \n1363:       step_post_iteration_claim_adjudication:\n1364:         action: \"Validate typed claim-adjudication packets for any new P0/P1 findings and persist the result to state.jsonl so the next iteration's claimAdjudicationGate can read it\"\n1365:         verify:\n1366:           - typed_packets_present: \"Every new P0/P1 finding in review/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md contains a claim-adjudication JSON block\"\n1367:           - packet_fields: \"Each packet includes claim, evidenceRefs, counterevidenceSought, alternativeExplanation, finalSeverity, confidence, downgradeTrigger\"\n1368:           - missing_packet_ids: \"List of new P0/P1 finding IDs that are missing a typed packet or field; empty array when all packets validate\"\n1369:         on_pass:\n1370:           set:\n1371:             claim_adjudication_passed: true\n1372:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"claim_adjudication\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"passed\":true,\"activeP0P1\":{active_p0_p1_count},\"missingPackets\":[],\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n1373:           log: \"Claim adjudication passed for iteration {current_iteration}. All new P0/P1 findings have typed packets.\"\n1374:         on_fail:\n1375:           action: \"Mark the iteration as invalid for convergence. The next iteration's claimAdjudicationGate (step_check_convergence step 0) reads the persisted `passed: false` event and vetoes STOP until a follow-up iteration rewrites the packets.\"\n1376:           set:\n1377:             claim_adjudication_passed: false\n1378:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"claim_adjudication\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"passed\":false,\"activeP0P1\":{active_p0_p1_count},\"missingPackets\":{missing_packet_ids},\"reason\":\"Missing typed packet fields for new P0/P1 findings\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n1379:           log: \"Claim adjudication incomplete for new P0/P1 findings. Event persisted. The next iteration's step_check_convergence claim-adjudication pre-check will veto STOP while `passed: false` remains the latest event and active P0/P1 > 0.\"\n1380: \n1381:       step_reduce_review_state:\n1382:         action: \"Run reducer to refresh the canonical findings registry before dashboard generation\"\n1383:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder}\"\n1384:         read:\n1385:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n1386:           - \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n1387:           - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n1388:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n1389:         write:\n1390:           - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n1391:           - \"{state_paths.dashboard}\"\n1392:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n1393:         failure_modes:\n1394:           malformed_delta: \"skip + warn\"\n1395:           missing_iteration_file: \"no-op + error\"\n1396:           schema_mismatch: \"reject + conflict event\"\n1397:         guarantee: \"Idempotent for identical inputs\"\n1398:         note: \"Reducer outputs findingsRegistry, dashboardMetrics, and strategyUpdates. Re-running the same inputs must be idempotent.\"\n1399: \n1400:       step_graph_upsert:\n\n(Output capped at 50 KB. Showing lines 634-1400. Use offset=1401 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"               fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows = numeric count of required closed-gate replay rows marked PASS with evidence\n               candidate_coverage_gate_pass = boolean\n               candidate_coverage_search_debt_json = JSON array of reducer-owned searchDebt obligations blocking STOP, else []\n               candidate_coverage_missing_json = JSON array of required bug classes not present in candidateCoverage.covered, else []\n               graphless_fallback_gate_pass = boolean\n               graphless_fallback_mode = latest reducer-owned searchCoverage.graphCoverageMode value\n               graphless_fallback_missing_json = JSON array of required bug classes without cited fallback ledger rows, else []\n               graphless_fallback_unavailability_reason = explicit reason when graphCoverageMode == \"unavailable_blocked\", else empty string\n               recovery_strategy = one-line hint describing the next review action needed to satisfy the failed gates; combine candidateCoverageGate and graphlessFallbackGate recovery guidance when both fail (when claimAdjudicationGate is the failing gate, prefer the step-0 recovery_strategy already set)\n          6. COMBINED STOP RULE:\n               a) if STOP is legal AND graph_decision == \"STOP_ALLOWED\": decision = \"STOP\"\n               b) if STOP is legal AND graph_decision == \"STOP_BLOCKED\":\n                    decision = \"BLOCKED\"\n                    stop_blocked = true\n                    stopReason = \"blockedStop\"\n                    # Blocked-stop closure: blockedBy must be string[] per the\n                    # published review blocked-stop contract. Extract the `.type`\n                    # field from each structured graph blocker; preserve the full\n                    # objects in graph_blocker_detail_json for operator inspection.\n                    blocked_by_json = JSON.stringify(graph_blockers_json.map(b => typeof b === \"string\" ? b : (b && b.type) || \"graph_blocker\"))","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml","text":"               fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows = numeric count of required closed-gate replay rows marked PASS with evidence\n               candidate_coverage_gate_pass = boolean\n               candidate_coverage_search_debt_json = JSON array of reducer-owned searchDebt obligations blocking STOP, else []\n               candidate_coverage_missing_json = JSON array of required bug classes not present in candidateCoverage.covered, else []\n               graphless_fallback_gate_pass = boolean\n               graphless_fallback_mode = latest reducer-owned searchCoverage.graphCoverageMode value\n               graphless_fallback_missing_json = JSON array of required bug classes without cited fallback ledger rows, else []\n               graphless_fallback_unavailability_reason = explicit reason when graphCoverageMode == \"unavailable_blocked\", else empty string\n               recovery_strategy = one-line hint describing the next review action needed to satisfy the failed gates; combine candidateCoverageGate and graphlessFallbackGate recovery guidance when both fail (when claimAdjudicationGate is the failing gate, prefer the step-0 recovery_strategy already set)\n          6. COMBINED STOP RULE:\n               a) if STOP is legal AND graph_decision == \"STOP_ALLOWED\": decision = \"STOP\"\n               b) if STOP is legal AND graph_decision == \"STOP_BLOCKED\":\n                    decision = \"BLOCKED\"\n                    stop_blocked = true\n                    stopReason = \"blockedStop\"\n                    # Blocked-stop closure: blockedBy must be string[] per the\n                    # published review blocked-stop contract. Extract the `.type`\n                    # field from each structured graph blocker; preserve the full\n                    # objects in graph_blocker_detail_json for operator inspection.\n                    blocked_by_json = JSON.stringify(graph_blockers_json.map(b => typeof b === \"string\" ? b : (b && b.type) || \"graph_blocker\"))\n                    blocked_by_csv = graph_blockers_csv\n                    graph_blocker_detail_json = graph_blockers_json\n                    recovery_strategy = \"Resolve review coverage-graph blockers before stopping.\"\n               c) if STOP is legal AND graph_decision == \"CONTINUE\":\n                    decision = \"CONTINUE\"\n                    stop_blocked = false\n                    reason = \"graph_convergence_continue\"\n               d) else keep the existing STUCK_RECOVERY or CONTINUE outcome\n        outputs:\n          - decision: \"STOP | BLOCKED | STUCK_RECOVERY | CONTINUE\"\n          - reason: \"Human-readable stop reason\"\n          - stop_blocked: \"Boolean true when STOP is vetoed by inline legal-stop gates or graph_decision == STOP_BLOCKED\"\n          - blocked_by_json: \"JSON array of failed legal-stop gates when decision == BLOCKED\"\n          - blocked_by_csv: \"Comma-separated list of failed legal-stop gates when decision == BLOCKED\"\n          - convergence_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for convergenceGate\"\n          - convergence_gate_score: \"Numeric score recorded for convergenceGate\"\n          - dimension_coverage_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for dimensionCoverageGate\"\n          - dimension_coverage_gate_covered_json: \"JSON array of covered review dimensions\"\n          - dimension_coverage_gate_missing_json: \"JSON array of missing review dimensions\"\n          - p0_resolution_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for p0ResolutionGate\"\n          - active_p0_count: \"Active P0 finding count at stop-check time\"\n          - evidence_density_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for evidenceDensityGate\"\n          - avg_evidence_per_finding: \"Numeric evidence density for active findings\"\n          - hotspot_saturation_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for hotspotSaturationGate\"\n          - claim_adjudication_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for claimAdjudicationGate (false vetoes STOP)\"\n          - claim_adjudication_active_count: \"Count of active P0/P1 findings evaluated by claimAdjudicationGate\"\n          - fix_completeness_replay_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for fixCompletenessReplayGate (false vetoes STOP on security-sensitive fix reruns)\"\n          - security_sensitive_fix_scope: \"Boolean true when the review is a security-sensitive fix rerun\"\n          - fix_completeness_replay_required_rows: \"Count of closed-gate replay rows required before STOP\"\n          - fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows: \"Count of required closed-gate replay rows that passed with evidence\"\n          - candidate_coverage_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for candidateCoverageGate (false vetoes STOP for unresolved reducer-owned search debt or uncovered required bug classes)\"\n          - candidate_coverage_search_debt_json: \"JSON array of reducer-owned searchDebt obligations used as blocked-stop evidence\"\n          - candidate_coverage_missing_json: \"JSON array of required bug classes missing from candidateCoverage.covered\"\n          - graphless_fallback_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for graphlessFallbackGate (false vetoes STOP when graphless fallback evidence is absent or unavailable_blocked)\"\n          - graphless_fallback_mode: \"Latest reducer-owned searchCoverage.graphCoverageMode value\"\n          - graphless_fallback_missing_json: \"JSON array of required bug classes missing cited fallback ledger rows\"\n          - graphless_fallback_unavailability_reason: \"Explicit unavailability reason when graphCoverageMode == unavailable_blocked\"\n          - graph_decision: \"CONTINUE | STOP_ALLOWED | STOP_BLOCKED from step_graph_convergence\"\n          - graph_signals_json: \"JSON object returned by graph convergence\"\n          - graph_blockers_json: \"JSON array of graph blockers\"\n          - graph_blockers_csv: \"Comma-separated graph blocker summary\"\n          - recovery_strategy: \"One-line hint describing the next review action when decision == BLOCKED or STUCK_RECOVERY\"\n\n      step_emit_blocked_stop:\n        action: \"Persist blocked-stop evidence whenever the review legal-stop decision tree vetoes STOP\"\n        if_blocked:\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"blocked_stop\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"blockedBy\":{blocked_by_json},\"gateResults\":{\"convergenceGate\":{\"pass\":{convergence_gate_pass},\"score\":{convergence_gate_score}},\"dimensionCoverageGate\":{\"pass\":{dimension_coverage_gate_pass},\"covered\":{dimension_coverage_gate_covered_json},\"missing\":{dimension_coverage_gate_missing_json}},\"p0ResolutionGate\":{\"pass\":{p0_resolution_gate_pass},\"activeP0\":{active_p0_count}},\"evidenceDensityGate\":{\"pass\":{evidence_density_gate_pass},\"avgEvidencePerFinding\":{avg_evidence_per_finding}},\"hotspotSaturationGate\":{\"pass\":{hotspot_saturation_gate_pass}},\"claimAdjudicationGate\":{\"pass\":{claim_adjudication_gate_pass},\"activeP0P1\":{claim_adjudication_active_count}},\"fixCompletenessReplayGate\":{\"pass\":{fix_completeness_replay_gate_pass},\"securitySensitive\":{security_sensitive_fix_scope},\"requiredRows\":{fix_completeness_replay_required_rows},\"passingRows\":{fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows}},\"candidateCoverageGate\":{\"pass\":{candidate_coverage_gate_pass},\"searchDebt\":{candidate_coverage_search_debt_json},\"missing\":{candidate_coverage_missing_json}},\"graphlessFallbackGate\":{\"pass\":{graphless_fallback_gate_pass},\"mode\":\"{graphless_fallback_mode}\",\"missing\":{graphless_fallback_missing_json},\"unavailabilityReason\":\"{graphless_fallback_unavailability_reason}\"}},\"graphBlockerDetail\":{graph_blockers_json},\"recoveryStrategy\":\"{recovery_strategy}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n          log: \"Blocked STOP persisted for review loop. Failed gates: {blocked_by_csv}. Recovery strategy: {recovery_strategy}\"\n        if_not_blocked:\n          proceed: true\n\n      step_handle_convergence:\n        action: \"Act on convergence decision\"\n        if_stop:\n          branch_on: \"convergence_mode == 'divergent' AND reason == 'all_dimensions_clean'\"\n          if_divergent_eligible:\n            eligibility_contract:\n              required_decision: \"STOP\"\n              eligible_reasons: [all_dimensions_clean]\n              excluded_reasons: [maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, error, manualStop, userPaused]\n              fail_closed: \"Any missing or ambiguous reason uses if_existing_terminal_path without preparing a pivot. The nine legal-stop gates have already run and remain unchanged.\"\n            steps:\n              step_prepare_divergent_pivot:\n                action: \"Generate state-grounded read-only review candidates and prepare or resume the pivot transaction\"\n                command: |\n                  node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n                  import {\n                    buildReviewPivotPreparationInput,\n                    renderReviewPivotSeatPrompt,\n                  } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/scripts/divergent-review-pivot.ts';\n                  import {\n                    preparePivotTransaction,\n                  } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/divergent-pivot.ts';\n\n                  const input = buildReviewPivotPreparationInput({\n                    artifactRoot: '{state_paths.packet_dir}',\n                    configPath: '{state_paths.config}',\n                    stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n                    strategyPath: '{state_paths.strategy}',\n                    registryPath: '{state_paths.findings_registry}',\n                    currentIteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n                    maxIterations: Number('{max_iterations}'),\n                    triggerReason: '{reason}',\n                  });\n                  const prepared = await preparePivotTransaction(input);\n                  const seatPrompts = prepared.status === 'pending'\n                    ? Object.fromEntries(prepared.missingSeats.map((seat) => [\n                        seat.id,\n                        renderReviewPivotSeatPrompt(seat, prepared.dispatchContext),\n                      ]))\n                    : {};\n                  process.stdout.write(`${JSON.stringify({\n                    ...prepared,\n                    seatPrompts,\n                    boundaryRejections: input.boundaryRejections,\n                  })}\\n`);\n                  EOF\n                working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n                outputs:\n                  - pivot_prepare_json: \"The complete parsed JSON result\"\n                  - pivot_prepare_status: \"status from the prepare result\"\n                  - pivot_id: \"pivotId from the prepare result\"\n                  - pivot_paths_json: \"paths from the prepare result as JSON\"\n                  - pivot_resumed: \"resumed from the prepare result\"\n                  - pivot_missing_seat_ids: \"missingSeats ids from a pending result\"\n                  - pivot_seat_001_json: \"The seat-001 mandate object from missingSeats\"\n                  - pivot_seat_002_json: \"The seat-002 mandate object from missingSeats\"\n                  - pivot_seat_003_json: \"The seat-003 mandate object from missingSeats\"\n                  - pivot_seat_001_prompt: \"seatPrompts['seat-001']\"\n                  - pivot_seat_002_prompt: \"seatPrompts['seat-002']\"\n                  - pivot_seat_003_prompt: \"seatPrompts['seat-003']\"\n                  - pivot_dispatch_context_json: \"dispatchContext from a pending result as JSON\"\n                short_circuit: \"When status is completed or failed, skip all dispatch and record steps and bind this result as pivot_result.\"\n\n              step_dispatch_pivot_seat_001:\n                action: \"Natively dispatch the analytical read-only review direction-selection seat\"\n                skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending' or pivot_missing_seat_ids does not contain 'seat-001'\"\n                capture_timing: true\n                if_native:\n                  dispatch:\n                    agent: deep-review\n                    model: opus\n                    context_source: \"pivot_seat_001_prompt\"\n                  wait_for_completion: true\n                failure_contract: \"A native dispatch failure binds status=rejected, a {name,message} error, and the measured timestamps/duration, then proceeds to step_record_pivot_seat_001.\"\n                outputs:\n                  - pivot_seat_001_dispatch_status: \"fulfilled or rejected\"\n                  - pivot_seat_001_output_json: \"Raw native return serialized as JSON when fulfilled\"\n                  - pivot_seat_001_error_json: \"{name,message} when rejected\"\n                  - pivot_seat_001_started_at_iso: \"Dispatch start timestamp\"\n                  - pivot_seat_001_completed_at_iso: \"Dispatch completion timestamp\"\n                  - pivot_seat_001_duration_ms: \"Dispatch duration in milliseconds\"\n\n              step_record_pivot_seat_001:\n                action: \"Durably record the seat-001 native dispatch outcome\"\n                skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending' or pivot_missing_seat_ids does not contain 'seat-001'\"\n                command: |\n                  node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n                  import { recordPivotSeatResult } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/divergent-pivot.ts';\n                  const status = '{pivot_seat_001_dispatch_status}';\n                  const outcome = status === 'fulfilled'\n                    ? { status, output: {pivot_seat_001_output_json}, startedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_001_started_at_iso}', completedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_001_completed_at_iso}', durationMs: Number('{pivot_seat_001_duration_ms}') }\n                    : { status: 'rejected', error: {pivot_seat_001_error_json}, startedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_001_started_at_iso}', completedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_001_completed_at_iso}', durationMs: Number('{pivot_seat_001_duration_ms}') };\n                  process.stdout.write(`${JSON.stringify(recordPivotSeatResult({ paths: {pivot_paths_json}, pivotId: '{pivot_id}', seat: {pivot_seat_001_json}, outcome }))}\\n`);\n                  EOF\n                working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n\n              step_dispatch_pivot_seat_002:\n                action: \"Natively dispatch the critical read-only review direction-selection seat\"\n                skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending' or pivot_missing_seat_ids does not contain 'seat-002'\"\n                capture_timing: true\n                if_native:\n                  dispatch:\n                    agent: deep-review\n                    model: opus\n                    context_source: \"pivot_seat_002_prompt\"\n                  wait_for_completion: true\n                failure_contract: \"A native dispatch failure binds status=rejected, a {name,message} error, and the measured timestamps/duration, then proceeds to step_record_pivot_seat_002.\"\n                outputs:\n                  - pivot_seat_002_dispatch_status: \"fulfilled or rejected\"\n                  - pivot_seat_002_output_json: \"Raw native return serialized as JSON when fulfilled\"\n                  - pivot_seat_002_error_json: \"{name,message} when rejected\"\n                  - pivot_seat_002_started_at_iso: \"Dispatch start timestamp\"\n                  - pivot_seat_002_completed_at_iso: \"Dispatch completion timestamp\"\n                  - pivot_seat_002_duration_ms: \"Dispatch duration in milliseconds\"\n\n              step_record_pivot_seat_002:\n                action: \"Durably record the seat-002 native dispatch outcome\"\n                skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending' or pivot_missing_seat_ids does not contain 'seat-002'\"\n                command: |\n                  node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n                  import { recordPivotSeatResult } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/divergent-pivot.ts';\n                  const status = '{pivot_seat_002_dispatch_status}';\n                  const outcome = status === 'fulfilled'\n                    ? { status, output: {pivot_seat_002_output_json}, startedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_002_started_at_iso}', completedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_002_completed_at_iso}', durationMs: Number('{pivot_seat_002_duration_ms}') }\n                    : { status: 'rejected', error: {pivot_seat_002_error_json}, startedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_002_started_at_iso}', completedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_002_completed_at_iso}', durationMs: Number('{pivot_seat_002_duration_ms}') };\n                  process.stdout.write(`${JSON.stringify(recordPivotSeatResult({ paths: {pivot_paths_json}, pivotId: '{pivot_id}', seat: {pivot_seat_002_json}, outcome }))}\\n`);\n                  EOF\n                working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n\n              step_dispatch_pivot_seat_003:\n                action: \"Natively dispatch the pragmatic read-only review direction-selection seat\"\n                skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending' or pivot_missing_seat_ids does not contain 'seat-003'\"\n                capture_timing: true\n                if_native:\n                  dispatch:\n                    agent: deep-review\n                    model: opus\n                    context_source: \"pivot_seat_003_prompt\"\n                  wait_for_completion: true\n                failure_contract: \"A native dispatch failure binds status=rejected, a {name,message} error, and the measured timestamps/duration, then proceeds to step_record_pivot_seat_003.\"\n                outputs:\n                  - pivot_seat_003_dispatch_status: \"fulfilled or rejected\"\n                  - pivot_seat_003_output_json: \"Raw native return serialized as JSON when fulfilled\"\n                  - pivot_seat_003_error_json: \"{name,message} when rejected\"\n                  - pivot_seat_003_started_at_iso: \"Dispatch start timestamp\"\n                  - pivot_seat_003_completed_at_iso: \"Dispatch completion timestamp\"\n                  - pivot_seat_003_duration_ms: \"Dispatch duration in milliseconds\"\n\n              step_record_pivot_seat_003:\n                action: \"Durably record the seat-003 native dispatch outcome\"\n                skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending' or pivot_missing_seat_ids does not contain 'seat-003'\"\n                command: |\n                  node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n                  import { recordPivotSeatResult } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/divergent-pivot.ts';\n                  const status = '{pivot_seat_003_dispatch_status}';\n                  const outcome = status === 'fulfilled'\n                    ? { status, output: {pivot_seat_003_output_json}, startedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_003_started_at_iso}', completedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_003_completed_at_iso}', durationMs: Number('{pivot_seat_003_duration_ms}') }\n                    : { status: 'rejected', error: {pivot_seat_003_error_json}, startedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_003_started_at_iso}', completedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_003_completed_at_iso}', durationMs: Number('{pivot_seat_003_duration_ms}') };\n                  process.stdout.write(`${JSON.stringify(recordPivotSeatResult({ paths: {pivot_paths_json}, pivotId: '{pivot_id}', seat: {pivot_seat_003_json}, outcome }))}\\n`);\n                  EOF\n                working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n\n              step_finalize_divergent_pivot:\n                action: \"Finalize the prepared pivot after all missing native seats are durable\"\n                skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending'\"\n                command: |\n                  node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n                  import { finalizePivotTransaction } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/divergent-pivot.ts';\n                  process.stdout.write(`${JSON.stringify(finalizePivotTransaction({ paths: {pivot_paths_json}, pivotId: '{pivot_id}', resumed: {pivot_resumed} }))}\\n`);\n                  EOF\n                working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n                outputs:\n                  - pivot_finalize_json: \"The complete parsed final result\"\n\n              step_resolve_divergent_pivot_result:\n                action: \"Use prepare's terminal result on resume/short-circuit, otherwise use finalize's result\"\n                branch_on: \"pivot_prepare_status\"\n                if_pending: { bind: { pivot_result: \"{pivot_finalize_json}\" } }\n                if_completed_or_failed: { bind: { pivot_result: \"{pivot_prepare_json}\" } }\n\n              step_apply_divergent_pivot_result:\n                action: \"Adopt a successful read-only review direction or fail closed to the existing synthesis path\"\n                branch_on: \"pivot_result.status\"\n                if_completed:\n                  set:\n                    next_dimension: \"{pivot_result.restoredFocus}\"\n                    pivot_lineage: \"Pivot {pivot_result.pivotId} selected {pivot_result.selectedCandidate.id} from source iteration {current_iteration}.\"\n                    saturated_directions: \"{pivot_result.completedEvent.saturatedDirections}\"\n                  command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder}\"\n                  log: \"Divergent review pivot {pivot_result.pivotId} restored focus to {pivot_result.restoredFocus}; continuing iteration {current_iteration}.\"\n                  proceed_to: step_normalize_pause_events\n                if_failed:\n                  log: \"Divergent review pivot {pivot_result.pivotId} failed closed ({pivot_result.failureReason}); proceeding to synthesis.\"\n                  skip_to: phase_synthesis\n            on_error:\n              log: \"Divergent review pivot integration error; failing closed to the existing synthesis path.\"\n              skip_to: phase_synthesis\n          if_existing_terminal_path:\n            log: \"Loop stopping. Reason: {reason}\"\n            skip_to: phase_synthesis\n        if_blocked:\n          log: \"Legal-stop gates blocked STOP. Failed gates: {blocked_by_csv}. Continuing review.\"\n        if_stuck_recovery:\n          log: \"Stuck detected ({stuck_count} consecutive no-progress). Entering recovery.\"\n          recovery_strategies:\n            - \"Change granularity: file-level → function-level → line-level review\"\n            - \"Traceability protocol replay: re-run unresolved core or overlay checks\"\n            - \"Escalate severity review: re-examine P2 findings for potential P1 upgrades\"\n          pivot_target: \"Pivot to the least-covered dimension (the review dimension with the fewest iteration passes and lowest coverage ratio).\"\n          set:\n            next_dimension: \"RECOVERY: {recovery_strategy}. Least-covered dimension: {least_explored}\"\n            pending_stop_event: \"stuck_recovery\"\n            pending_stop_reason: \"stuckRecovery\"\n            pending_stop_detail: \"Recovery path activated after repeated no-progress iterations\"\n          reset: { stuck_count: 0 }\n        if_continue:\n          log: \"Iteration {current_iteration}: Continuing. Dimension: {next_dimension}\"\n\n      step_normalize_pause_events:\n        action: \"Rewrite raw pause and recovery events to the frozen STOP_REASONS enum at emission time: converged, maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, error, manualStop, userPaused\"\n        if_pending_pause_event:\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"reason\":\"{pending_stop_detail}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n          message: \"Review paused. Delete review/.deep-review-pause to resume.\"\n          reset:\n            pending_stop_event: null\n            pending_stop_reason: null\n            pending_stop_detail: null\n          halt: true\n        if_pending_stuck_recovery:\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"stopReason\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"fromIteration\":{current_iteration},\"strategy\":\"{recovery_strategy}\",\"targetDimension\":\"{least_explored}\",\"outcome\":\"pending\",\"reason\":\"{pending_stop_detail}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n          reset:\n            pending_stop_event: null\n            pending_stop_reason: null\n            pending_stop_detail: null\n        if_no_pending_event:\n          proceed: true\n\n      step_generate_state_summary:\n        action: \"Generate compact state summary for dispatch context (~200 tokens)\"\n        generate: |\n          STATE SUMMARY (auto-generated):\n          Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\n          Dimension: {next_dimension}\n          Prior Findings: P0={p0_count} P1={p1_count} P2={p2_count}\n          Dimension Coverage: {dimensions_covered_list} ({dimension_coverage})\n          Traceability: core={core_protocol_status} overlay={overlay_protocol_status}\n          {resource_map_prompt_line}\n          Coverage Age: {coverage_age}\n          Last 2 ratios: {ratio_prev} -> {ratio_latest}\n          Stuck count: {stuck_count}\n          Provisional Verdict: {PASS|CONDITIONAL|FAIL|PENDING} hasAdvisories={has_advisories}\n\n      step_marker_scan:\n        action: \"H-2 loop-prevention guard: scan previous iteration's rendered prompt for nested review marker\"\n        algorithm: |\n          if current_iteration > 1:\n            PREV_PROMPT_PATH = \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{previous_iteration}.md\"\n            if file_exists(PREV_PROMPT_PATH):\n              PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE = head -1 of PREV_PROMPT_PATH\n              if PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE matches ^(DEEP-REVIEW|DEEP-RESEARCH|CODE-REVIEW)$:\n                log \"ERROR: nested review-of-review loop detected (marker found in previous iteration prompt). Aborting.\"\n                halt with exit code 2\n        note: |\n          False-positive prevention: only matches when the first line is exactly one of the\n          three canonical markers. Markers appearing in comments or body text are ignored.\n          True-positive triggers only when a previous iteration's rendered prompt literally\n          starts with a deep-loop marker, indicating a nested review-of-review dispatch.\n\n      step_dispatch_iteration:\n        action: \"Dispatch @deep-review agent for one review iteration\"\n        resolve_executor:\n          source: \"config.executor\"\n          loader: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts#parseExecutorConfig\"\n        pre_dispatch:\n          generate_summary: |\n            STATE SUMMARY (auto-generated):\n            Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\n            Dimension: {next_dimension}\n            Prior Findings: P0={p0_count} P1={p1_count} P2={p2_count}\n            Dimension Coverage: {dimensions_covered_list} ({dimension_coverage})\n            Traceability: core={core_protocol_status} overlay={overlay_protocol_status}\n            {resource_map_prompt_line}\n            Coverage Age: {coverage_age}\n            Last 2 ratios: {ratio_prev} -> {ratio_latest}\n            Stuck count: {stuck_count}\n            Provisional Verdict: {PASS|CONDITIONAL|FAIL|PENDING} hasAdvisories={has_advisories}\n          render_prompt_pack:\n            template_path: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl\"\n            renderer: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/prompt-pack.ts#renderPromptPack\"\n            output_path: \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md\"\n            variables:\n              state_summary: \"{state_summary}\"\n              current_iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n              max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n              next_dimension: \"{next_dimension}\"\n              review_target: \"{review_target}\"\n              review_scope_files: \"{review_scope_files}\"\n              p0_count: \"{p0_count}\"\n              p1_count: \"{p1_count}\"\n              p2_count: \"{p2_count}\"\n              pivot_lineage: \"{pivot_lineage}\"\n              saturated_directions: \"{saturated_directions}\"\n              state_paths_config: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n              state_paths_state_log: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n              state_paths_findings_registry: \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n              state_paths_strategy: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n              state_paths_iteration_pattern: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n              state_paths_delta_pattern: \"{state_paths.delta_pattern}\"\n        pre_dispatch_audit:\n          skip_when: \"config.executor.kind == 'native'\"\n          call: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts#writeFirstRecordExecutor\"\n          args:\n            stateLogPath: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n            executor: \"{config.executor}\"\n            iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n        branch_on: \"config.executor.kind\"\n        if_native:\n          dispatch:\n            agent: deep-review\n            model: opus\n            context_source: \"rendered_prompt_pack\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n        if_cli_copilot:\n          command: |\n            node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n            import { readFileSync, writeFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n            import { createHash } from 'node:crypto';\n\n            import { runAuditedExecutorCommand } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts';\n            import { buildCopilotPromptArg } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts';\n\n            const promptPath = '{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md';\n            const prompt = readFileSync(promptPath, 'utf8');\n\n            // Workflow-resolved spec folder is the only legal write authority.\n            // The helper (`validateSpecFolder` inside `buildCopilotPromptArg`)\n            // is the single source of truth for rejecting empty / unresolved\n            // template / whitespace-only / string-coerced empty values. The\n            // YAML hands the raw `{spec_folder}` directly; on rejection the\n            // helper safe-fails to `type:\"missing\", writeIntent:true` (Gate-3\n            // enforcement, --allow-all-tools stripped).\n            const specFolderRaw = '{spec_folder}';\n            const targetAuthority = { type: 'approved', specFolder: specFolderRaw };\n\n            const baseArgs = [\n              '-p',\n              prompt,\n              '--model',\n              '{config.executor.model}',\n              '--allow-all-tools',\n              '--no-ask-user',\n            ];\n\n            const built = buildCopilotPromptArg({\n              promptPath,\n              prompt,\n              targetAuthority,\n              baseArgv: baseArgs,\n            });\n\n            // Large-prompt @PROMPT_PATH wrapper: helper emits a `promptFileBody`\n            // containing `<TARGET AUTHORITY preamble>\\n\\n---\\n\\n<original>`.\n            // Write it to disk so the file Copilot reads via @path opens with\n            // the authority block. Without this, recovered/bootstrap folder\n            // mentions inside the file could still anchor the model.\n            if (built.promptFileBody !== undefined) {\n              writeFileSync(promptPath, built.promptFileBody, 'utf8');\n            }\n\n            // Copilot is routed through the audited executor wrapper so it produces\n            // INTENT + COMPLETION dispatch receipts alongside claude-code/opencode\n            // There is no cli-copilot kind in the executor schema, so it\n            // dispatches as kind:'native' (full env passthrough, no recursion-guard\n            // layer configured for copilot); the receipt still records the real\n            // 'copilot' command + built.argv as facts.\n            const dispatchFacts = {\n              command: 'deep/review',\n              mode: 'review',\n              specFolder: '{spec_folder}',\n              artifactDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}',\n              iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n              executorKind: '{config.executor.kind}',\n              branchId: '{config.executor.kind}',\n              sessionId: '{session_id}',\n              generation: Number('{generation}'),\n            };\n            const dispatchId = 'review-i{current_iteration}-g{generation}';\n            process.exit(\n              runAuditedExecutorCommand({\n                command: 'copilot',\n                args: built.argv,\n                cwd: '{repo_root}',\n                timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n                stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n                executor: {\n                  kind: 'native',\n                  model: '{config.executor.model}',\n                  configDir: null,\n                  reasoningEffort: null,\n                  serviceTier: null,\n                  sandboxMode: null,\n                  timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n                  governor: null,\n                },\n                iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n                receiptDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}/dispatch-receipts',\n                dispatchId,\n              }),\n            );\n            EOF\n          working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n          timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n          notes:\n            - \"Routed through runAuditedExecutorCommand so copilot produces INTENT + COMPLETION dispatch receipts; built.argv (@PROMPT_PATH or positional) is forwarded verbatim as the receipt facts\"\n            - \"copilot has no stdin support; prompt is positional\"\n            - \"Size check uses 16KB threshold; above that uses @PROMPT_PATH wrapper prompt\"\n            - \"Large-prompt path relies on copilot honoring @path references within its prompt string\"\n            - \"buildCopilotPromptArg attaches a TARGET AUTHORITY preamble bound to the workflow-approved spec folder; recovered context cannot override it (authority guard source: .opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_deep-review_auto.yaml)\"\n            - \"If spec_folder is missing/malformed/unresolved on a write-intent dispatch, the helper enforces plan-only by replacing the prompt with a Gate-3 question and stripping --allow-all-tools\"\n            - \"Large-prompt wrapper mode rewrites the prompt file at promptPath to include the TARGET AUTHORITY preamble (prefix + divider + original body); the argv becomes a bare @promptPath reference\"\n        if_cli_claude_code:\n          command: |\n            node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n            import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n            import { createHash } from 'node:crypto';\n\n            import { runAuditedExecutorCommand } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts';\n\n            const configDir = '{optional_claude_config_dir}';\n            const reasoningEffort = '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}';\n            const executor = {\n              kind: 'cli-claude-code',\n              model: '{config.executor.model}',\n              configDir: configDir || null,\n              reasoningEffort,\n              serviceTier: null,\n              sandboxMode: null,\n              timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n              governor: null,\n            };\n            const args = [\n              '-p',\n              readFileSync('{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md', 'utf8'),\n              '--model',\n              executor.model,\n              '--permission-mode',\n              'acceptEdits',\n              '--output-format',\n              'text',\n            ];\n            if (executor.reasoningEffort) {\n              args.push('--effort', executor.reasoningEffort);\n            }\n\n            // CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR rides through guardContext.env; the CLAUDE_ prefix is\n            // on the cli-claude-code env allowlist so buildExecutorDispatchEnv admits it.\n            const parentEnv = { ...process.env };\n            if (configDir) {\n              parentEnv.CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR = configDir;\n            }\n\n            const dispatchFacts = {\n              command: 'deep/review',\n              mode: 'review',\n              specFolder: '{spec_folder}',\n              artifactDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}',\n              iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n              executorKind: '{config.executor.kind}',\n              branchId: '{config.executor.kind}',\n              sessionId: '{session_id}',\n              generation: Number('{generation}'),\n            };\n            const dispatchId = 'review-i{current_iteration}-g{generation}';\n            process.exit(\n              runAuditedExecutorCommand({\n                command: 'claude',\n                args,\n                cwd: '{repo_root}',\n                timeoutSeconds: executor.timeoutSeconds,\n                stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n                executor,\n                iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n                guardContext: { env: parentEnv },\n                receiptDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}/dispatch-receipts',\n                dispatchId,\n              }),\n            );\n            EOF\n          working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n          timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n          render_hint:\n            optional_claude_config_dir: |\n              If config.executor.configDir is set and non-null, expand a leading ~ to HOME and bind that path.\n              Otherwise expand to empty string.\n          notes:\n            - \"Routed through runAuditedExecutorCommand so claude-code produces INTENT + COMPLETION dispatch receipts; recursion guard + env allowlist enforced via buildExecutorDispatchEnv\"\n            - \"CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR is forwarded through guardContext.env (CLAUDE_ prefix is allowlisted) so account-specific Claude Code routing is preserved\"\n            - \"permission-mode stays acceptEdits (review's existing iteration-write behavior); claude-code has no serviceTier flag\"\n            - \"claude-code supports --effort for reasoning depth\"\n        if_cli_opencode:\n          command: |\n            node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n            import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n            import { createHash } from 'node:crypto';\n\n            import { runAuditedExecutorCommand } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts';\n\n            const reasoningEffort = '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}';\n            const executor = {\n              kind: 'cli-opencode',\n              model: '{config.executor.model}',\n              configDir: null,\n              reasoningEffort,\n              serviceTier: null,\n              sandboxMode: null,\n              timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n              governor: null,\n            };\n            const promptBody = readFileSync('{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md', 'utf8');\n            const message = 'Resolved route: mode=review; target_agent=@deep-review; execution=single_review_iteration; state_source=externalized_files; do_not_switch_mode=true'\n              + '\\n\\n'\n              + promptBody;\n            const args = [\n              'run',\n              '--model',\n              executor.model,\n              '--format',\n              'json',\n              '--dangerously-skip-permissions',\n              '--pure',\n              '--dir',\n              '{repo_root}',\n            ];\n            if (executor.reasoningEffort) {\n              args.push('--variant', executor.reasoningEffort);\n            }\n            args.push(message);\n\n            const dispatchFacts = {\n              command: 'deep/review',\n              mode: 'review',\n              specFolder: '{spec_folder}',\n              artifactDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}',\n              iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n              executorKind: '{config.executor.kind}',\n              branchId: '{config.executor.kind}',\n              sessionId: '{session_id}',\n              generation: Number('{generation}'),\n            };\n            const dispatchId = 'review-i{current_iteration}-g{generation}';\n            process.exit(\n              runAuditedExecutorCommand({\n                command: 'opencode',\n                args,\n                cwd: '{repo_root}',\n                timeoutSeconds: executor.timeoutSeconds,\n                stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n                executor,\n                iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n                // opencode v1.14.39 reads stdin at startup before session creation;\n                // an empty input gives EOF stdin, equivalent to </dev/null.\n                input: '',\n                receiptDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}/dispatch-receipts',\n                dispatchId,\n              }),\n            );\n            EOF\n          working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n          timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n          notes:\n            - \"Routed through runAuditedExecutorCommand so opencode produces INTENT + COMPLETION dispatch receipts; recursion guard + env allowlist enforced via buildExecutorDispatchEnv\"\n            - \"input:'' yields closed stdin (EOF), equivalent to </dev/null — opencode v1.14.39 reads stdin at startup and hangs at 0% CPU after +60s snapshot prune without it (the `cli-external/cli-opencode` mode's SKILL.md (`.opencode/skills/cli-external/cli-opencode/SKILL.md`) §4 ALWAYS rule)\"\n            - \"opencode run takes a positional message; prompt is the route-proof preamble + iteration body\"\n            - \"--variant maps reasoningEffort to opencode's provider-specific reasoning lever (e.g., high, medium, minimal)\"\n            - \"--dangerously-skip-permissions enables hands-off automation; sandboxMode='read-only' is not currently honored (no opencode equivalent)\"\n            - \"cli-opencode self-invocation guard: this single-executor branch must only run from a non-OpenCode dispatch surface (Claude Code/raw shell). Explicit parallel-detached cli-opencode fan-out is handled by step_fanout_spawn_cli/fanout-run.cjs, not this branch. the `cli-external/cli-opencode` mode's SKILL.md (`.opencode/skills/cli-external/cli-opencode/SKILL.md`) §SELF-INVOCATION PROHIBITED contract is the authoritative gate\"\n        post_dispatch_validate:\n          validator: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/post-dispatch-validate.ts#validateIterationOutputs\"\n          command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/verify-iteration.cjs --loop-type review --artifact-dir {artifact_dir} --iteration {current_iteration}\"\n          command_note: \"Mechanical leaf-reliability gate: exit 0 = complete; non-zero prints one machine reason (iteration_file_missing|iteration_verdict_missing|state_record_missing|route_proof_missing|route_proof_mismatch|delta_file_missing). The script enforces the artifact + route-proof contract instead of trusting the leaf to self-report, and a non-zero exit triggers on_failure.redispatch_once.\"\n          assert_exists: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n          assert_appended: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          assert_jsonl_fields: [type, iteration, mode, run, status, focus, dimensions, filesReviewed, findingsCount, findingsSummary, findingsNew, findingDetails, newFindingsRatio, sessionId, generation, lineageMode, timestamp, durationMs]\n          route_proof:\n            mode: review\n            target_agent: deep-review\n            agent_definition_loaded: true\n            resolved_route: \"Resolved route: mode=review target_agent=deep-review\"\n          dispatchReceipt:\n            receiptDir: \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/dispatch-receipts\"\n            dispatchId: \"review-i{current_iteration}-g{generation}\"\n          assert_canonical_type: \"iteration\"\n          assert_delta_file_exists: \"{state_paths.delta_pattern}\"\n          assert_delta_file_has_iteration_record: true\n          failure_reasons:\n            - iteration_file_missing\n            - iteration_file_empty\n            - jsonl_not_appended\n            - jsonl_missing_fields\n            - jsonl_parse_error\n            - jsonl_wrong_type\n            - delta_file_missing\n            - delta_file_empty\n            - delta_file_missing_iteration_record\n            - executor_missing\n            - dispatch_failure_logged\n            - v2_missing_ledger\n            - v2_uncited_ledger_row\n            - v2_broken_linked_finding\n            - v2_shallow_finding_details\n            - delta_iteration_id_mismatch\n            - state_delta_iteration_mismatch\n            - route_proof_missing\n            - route_proof_mismatch\n          warning_surface:\n            source: \"result.warnings\"\n            action: \"emit schema_advisory canonical conflict event\"\n            severity: \"advisory\"\n            event_shape: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"schema_advisory\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"iteration\":{current_iteration},\"warnings\":{result.warnings},\"severity\":\"advisory\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n            note: \"Warnings do not fail dispatch. Hard failures still emit schema_mismatch through on_failure.\"\n          on_failure:\n            action: \"emit schema_mismatch canonical conflict event\"\n            redispatch_once: \"On the FIRST failure of the mechanical command check for this iteration, re-run step_dispatch_iteration exactly once for the same iteration number, then re-run the check. If it still fails, record the iteration as error (per step_evaluate_results.on_missing_outputs) and continue. Never re-dispatch a given iteration more than once.\"\n            escalation: \"After 3 consecutive failures across iterations, trigger stuck_recovery event with diagnostic context\"\n        record_executor_audit:\n          skip_when: \"config.executor.kind == 'native'\"\n          target: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          field: \"executor\"\n          value:\n            kind: \"{config.executor.kind}\"\n            model: \"{config.executor.model}\"\n            reasoningEffort: \"{config.executor.reasoningEffort}\"\n            serviceTier: \"{config.executor.serviceTier}\"\n\n      step_evaluate_results:\n        action: \"Verify iteration outputs and extract metrics\"\n        verify:\n          - file_exists: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n          - jsonl_appended: \"New iteration record in state.jsonl\"\n          - strategy_updated: \"Strategy.md has been modified\"\n        extract:\n          - newFindingsRatio: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n          - findings_count: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n          - severity_counts: \"From latest JSONL iteration record (P0, P1, P2)\"\n          - dimensions: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n          - files_reviewed: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n          - status: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n          - reviewed_artifacts: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n          - traceability_checks: \"From latest JSONL iteration record when present\"\n        on_missing_outputs:\n          action: \"Mark iteration as 'error', continue to next\"\n          # Canonical iteration record: include sessionId, generation, durationMs so the reducer can persist\n          # the failure without dropping the iteration. Schema source: state_format.md §Iteration Records.\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":{current_iteration},\"run\":{current_iteration},\"mode\":\"review\",\"status\":\"error\",\"focus\":\"{next_dimension}\",\"dimensions\":[\"{next_dimension}\"],\"filesReviewed\":[],\"findingsCount\":0,\"findingsSummary\":{\"P0\":0,\"P1\":0,\"P2\":0},\"findingsNew\":{\"P0\":0,\"P1\":0,\"P2\":0},\"findingDetails\":[],\"traceabilityChecks\":{\"summary\":{\"required\":0,\"executed\":0,\"pass\":0,\"partial\":0,\"fail\":0,\"blocked\":0,\"notApplicable\":0,\"gatingFailures\":0},\"results\":[]},\"newFindingsRatio\":0.0,\"durationMs\":0,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation},\"lineageMode\":\"{config.lineage.lineageMode}\"}'\n\n      step_post_iteration_claim_adjudication:\n        action: \"Validate typed claim-adjudication packets for any new P0/P1 findings and persist the result to state.jsonl so the next iteration's claimAdjudicationGate can read it\"\n        verify:\n          - typed_packets_present: \"Every new P0/P1 finding in review/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md contains a claim-adjudication JSON block\"\n          - packet_fields: \"Each packet includes claim, evidenceRefs, counterevidenceSought, alternativeExplanation, finalSeverity, confidence, downgradeTrigger\"\n          - missing_packet_ids: \"List of new P0/P1 finding IDs that are missing a typed packet or field; empty array when all packets validate\"\n        on_pass:\n          set:\n            claim_adjudication_passed: true\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"claim_adjudication\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"passed\":true,\"activeP0P1\":{active_p0_p1_count},\"missingPackets\":[],\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n          log: \"Claim adjudication passed for iteration {current_iteration}. All new P0/P1 findings have typed packets.\"\n        on_fail:\n          action: \"Mark the iteration as invalid for convergence. The next iteration's claimAdjudicationGate (step_check_convergence step 0) reads the persisted `passed: false` event and vetoes STOP until a follow-up iteration rewrites the packets.\"\n          set:\n            claim_adjudication_passed: false\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"claim_adjudication\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"passed\":false,\"activeP0P1\":{active_p0_p1_count},\"missingPackets\":{missing_packet_ids},\"reason\":\"Missing typed packet fields for new P0/P1 findings\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n          log: \"Claim adjudication incomplete for new P0/P1 findings. Event persisted. The next iteration's step_check_convergence claim-adjudication pre-check will veto STOP while `passed: false` remains the latest event and active P0/P1 > 0.\"\n\n      step_reduce_review_state:\n        action: \"Run reducer to refresh the canonical findings registry before dashboard generation\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder}\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        write:\n          - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.dashboard}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        failure_modes:\n          malformed_delta: \"skip + warn\"\n          missing_iteration_file: \"no-op + error\"\n          schema_mismatch: \"reject + conflict event\"\n        guarantee: \"Idempotent for identical inputs\"\n        note: \"Reducer outputs findingsRegistry, dashboardMetrics, and strategyUpdates. Re-running the same inputs must be idempotent.\"\n\n      step_graph_upsert:","lineStart":634,"lineEnd":1400,"totalLines":1401,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml","time":{"start":1783915559385,"end":1783915559438}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0df59b61eea8d697016a546427542c8191a5bc924451b2d11f"}},"id":"prt_f59a739b40017zxwaPD99v2Dd6","sessionID":"ses_0a65ac472ffeDn3G1fX5LbU2k8","messageID":"msg_f59a6ea830011kqj0WvDYGJREd"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783915559446,"sessionID":"ses_0a65ac472ffeDn3G1fX5LbU2k8","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_obHQ21hoL09vAQ22rgvLYfbW","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/deep_review_config.json","offset":1,"limit":2000},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/deep_review_config.json</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\n2:   \"topic\": \"\",\n3:   \"sessionId\": \"\",\n4:   \"parentSessionId\": null,\n5:   \"lineageMode\": \"new\",\n6:   \"generation\": 1,\n7:   \"continuedFromRun\": null,\n8:   \"migrationWindowEndsAt\": \"\",\n9:   \"maxIterations\": 7,\n10:   \"convergenceThreshold\": 0.10,\n11:   \"antiConvergence\": {\n12:     \"minIterations\": 2,\n13:     \"convergenceMode\": \"default\",\n14:     \"stopPolicy\": \"fail-closed\"\n15:   },\n16:   \"stuckThreshold\": 2,\n17:   \"maxDurationMinutes\": 120,\n18:   \"maxToolCallsPerIteration\": 12,\n19:   \"maxMinutesPerIteration\": 10,\n20:   \"progressiveSynthesis\": false,\n21:   \"specFolder\": \"\",\n22:   \"createdAt\": \"\",\n23:   \"status\": \"initialized\",\n24:   \"releaseReadinessState\": \"in-progress\",\n25:   \"executionMode\": \"auto\",\n26:   \"executor\": {\n27:     \"kind\": \"native\",\n28:     \"model\": null,\n29:     \"reasoningEffort\": null,\n30:     \"serviceTier\": null,\n31:     \"sandboxMode\": null,\n32:     \"timeoutSeconds\": 900\n33:   },\n34:   \"mode\": \"review\",\n35:   \"reviewTarget\": \"\",\n36:   \"reviewTargetType\": \"spec-folder\",\n37:   \"reviewDimensions\": [\n38:     \"correctness\",\n39:     \"security\",\n40:     \"traceability\",\n41:     \"maintainability\"\n42:   ],\n43:   \"severityThreshold\": \"P2\",\n44:   \"crossReference\": {\n45:     \"core\": [\n46:       \"spec_code\",\n47:       \"checklist_evidence\"\n48:     ],\n49:     \"overlay\": [\n50:       \"skill_agent\",\n51:       \"agent_cross_runtime\",\n52:       \"feature_catalog_code\",\n53:       \"playbook_capability\"\n54:     ]\n55:   },\n56:   \"qualityGateThreshold\": true,\n57:   \"runtimeCapabilityResolver\": \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/scripts/runtime-capabilities.cjs\",\n58:   \"reducerScriptPath\": \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/reduce-state.cjs\",\n59:   \"fileProtection\": {\n60:     \"deep-review-config.json\": \"immutable\",\n61:     \"deep-review-state.jsonl\": \"append-only\",\n62:     \"deep-review-findings-registry.json\": \"auto-generated\",\n63:     \"deep-review-strategy.md\": \"mutable\",\n64:     \"deep-review-dashboard.md\": \"auto-generated\",\n65:     \".deep-review-pause\": \"operator-controlled\",\n66:     \"review-report.md\": \"mutable\",\n67:     \"review-report-v*.md\": \"write-once\",\n68:     \"iteration-*.md\": \"write-once\"\n69:   },\n70:   \"reducer\": {\n71:     \"enabled\": true,\n72:     \"inputs\": [\n73:       \"latestJSONLDelta\",\n74:       \"newIterationFile\",\n75:       \"priorReducedState\"\n76:     ],\n77:     \"outputs\": [\n78:       \"findingsRegistry\",\n79:       \"dashboardMetrics\",\n80:       \"strategyUpdates\"\n81:     ],\n82:     \"metrics\": [\n83:       \"dimensionsCovered\",\n84:       \"findingsBySeverity\",\n85:       \"openFindings\",\n86:       \"resolvedFindings\",\n87:       \"convergenceScore\"\n88:     ]\n89:   },\n90:   \"_optimizerManaged\": {\n91:     \"description\": \"Fields managed by the offline loop optimizer (042.004). See optimizer-manifest.json for the canonical tunable/locked field registry.\",\n92:     \"manifestPath\": \".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/optimizer/optimizer-manifest.json\",\n93:     \"tunableFields\": [\"convergenceThreshold\", \"stuckThreshold\", \"maxIterations\"],\n94:     \"lockedFields\": [\"lineageMode\", \"reducer\", \"fileProtection\", \"sessionId\", \"mode\", \"reviewDimensions\", \"antiConvergence.convergenceMode\", \"antiConvergence.stopPolicy\"],\n95:     \"promotionMode\": \"advisory-only\"\n96:   }\n97: }\n\n(End of file - total 97 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\n  \"topic\": \"\",\n  \"sessionId\": \"\",\n  \"parentSessionId\": null,\n  \"lineageMode\": \"new\",\n  \"generation\": 1,\n  \"continuedFromRun\": null,\n  \"migrationWindowEndsAt\": \"\",\n  \"maxIterations\": 7,\n  \"convergenceThreshold\": 0.10,\n  \"antiConvergence\": {\n    \"minIterations\": 2,\n    \"convergenceMode\": \"default\",\n    \"stopPolicy\": \"fail-closed\"\n  },\n  \"stuckThreshold\": 2,\n  \"maxDurationMinutes\": 120,\n  \"maxToolCallsPerIteration\": 12,\n  \"maxMinutesPerIteration\": 10,\n  \"progressiveSynthesis\": false,","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/deep_review_config.json","text":"{\n  \"topic\": \"\",\n  \"sessionId\": \"\",\n  \"parentSessionId\": null,\n  \"lineageMode\": \"new\",\n  \"generation\": 1,\n  \"continuedFromRun\": null,\n  \"migrationWindowEndsAt\": \"\",\n  \"maxIterations\": 7,\n  \"convergenceThreshold\": 0.10,\n  \"antiConvergence\": {\n    \"minIterations\": 2,\n    \"convergenceMode\": \"default\",\n    \"stopPolicy\": \"fail-closed\"\n  },\n  \"stuckThreshold\": 2,\n  \"maxDurationMinutes\": 120,\n  \"maxToolCallsPerIteration\": 12,\n  \"maxMinutesPerIteration\": 10,\n  \"progressiveSynthesis\": false,\n  \"specFolder\": \"\",\n  \"createdAt\": \"\",\n  \"status\": \"initialized\",\n  \"releaseReadinessState\": \"in-progress\",\n  \"executionMode\": \"auto\",\n  \"executor\": {\n    \"kind\": \"native\",\n    \"model\": null,\n    \"reasoningEffort\": null,\n    \"serviceTier\": null,\n    \"sandboxMode\": null,\n    \"timeoutSeconds\": 900\n  },\n  \"mode\": \"review\",\n  \"reviewTarget\": \"\",\n  \"reviewTargetType\": \"spec-folder\",\n  \"reviewDimensions\": [\n    \"correctness\",\n    \"security\",\n    \"traceability\",\n    \"maintainability\"\n  ],\n  \"severityThreshold\": \"P2\",\n  \"crossReference\": {\n    \"core\": [\n      \"spec_code\",\n      \"checklist_evidence\"\n    ],\n    \"overlay\": [\n      \"skill_agent\",\n      \"agent_cross_runtime\",\n      \"feature_catalog_code\",\n      \"playbook_capability\"\n    ]\n  },\n  \"qualityGateThreshold\": true,\n  \"runtimeCapabilityResolver\": \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/scripts/runtime-capabilities.cjs\",\n  \"reducerScriptPath\": \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/reduce-state.cjs\",\n  \"fileProtection\": {\n    \"deep-review-config.json\": \"immutable\",\n    \"deep-review-state.jsonl\": \"append-only\",\n    \"deep-review-findings-registry.json\": \"auto-generated\",\n    \"deep-review-strategy.md\": \"mutable\",\n    \"deep-review-dashboard.md\": \"auto-generated\",\n    \".deep-review-pause\": \"operator-controlled\",\n    \"review-report.md\": \"mutable\",\n    \"review-report-v*.md\": \"write-once\",\n    \"iteration-*.md\": \"write-once\"\n  },\n  \"reducer\": {\n    \"enabled\": true,\n    \"inputs\": [\n      \"latestJSONLDelta\",\n      \"newIterationFile\",\n      \"priorReducedState\"\n    ],\n    \"outputs\": [\n      \"findingsRegistry\",\n      \"dashboardMetrics\",\n      \"strategyUpdates\"\n    ],\n    \"metrics\": [\n      \"dimensionsCovered\",\n      \"findingsBySeverity\",\n      \"openFindings\",\n      \"resolvedFindings\",\n      \"convergenceScore\"\n    ]\n  },\n  \"_optimizerManaged\": {\n    \"description\": \"Fields managed by the offline loop optimizer (042.004). See optimizer-manifest.json for the canonical tunable/locked field registry.\",\n    \"manifestPath\": \".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/optimizer/optimizer-manifest.json\",\n    \"tunableFields\": [\"convergenceThreshold\", \"stuckThreshold\", \"maxIterations\"],\n    \"lockedFields\": [\"lineageMode\", \"reducer\", \"fileProtection\", \"sessionId\", \"mode\", \"reviewDimensions\", \"antiConvergence.convergenceMode\", \"antiConvergence.stopPolicy\"],\n    \"promotionMode\": \"advisory-only\"\n  }\n}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":97,"totalLines":97,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/deep_review_config.json","time":{"start":1783915559410,"end":1783915559440}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0df59b61eea8d697016a546427545081918c228b7694df2f93"}},"id":"prt_f59a739f10015NOldlD5JnIyrE","sessionID":"ses_0a65ac472ffeDn3G1fX5LbU2k8","messageID":"msg_f59a6ea830011kqj0WvDYGJREd"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783915559446,"sessionID":"ses_0a65ac472ffeDn3G1fX5LbU2k8","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_0cse55nMShQ9GpqSugTj7EBf","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl","offset":1,"limit":2000},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: DEEP-REVIEW\n2: Resolved route: mode=review; target_agent=@deep-review; execution=single_review_iteration; state_source=externalized_files; do_not_switch_mode=true\n3: \n4: # Deep-Review Iteration Prompt Pack\n5: \n6: This prompt pack renders the per-iteration context for the `@deep-review` LEAF agent (native executor) or a CLI executor (e.g. `opencode run`). Tokens use curly-brace syntax and are substituted by `renderPromptPack` before dispatch.\n7: \n8: ## STATE\n9: \n10: {state_summary}\n11: \n12: Review Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\n13: Mode: review\n14: Dimension: {next_dimension}\n15: Review Target: {review_target}\n16: Review Scope Files: {review_scope_files}\n17: Prior Findings: P0={p0_count} P1={p1_count} P2={p2_count}\n18: \n19: ## PIVOT LINEAGE\n20: \n21: {pivot_lineage}\n22: \n23: Swept or saturated review directions that MUST NOT be re-entered:\n24: {saturated_directions}\n25: \n26: ## SHARED DOCTRINE\n27: \n28: Load `.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review_core.md` before final severity calls.\n29: \n30: ## REVIEW DIMENSIONS\n31: \n32: correctness, security, traceability, maintainability\n33: \n34: ## TRACEABILITY PROTOCOLS\n35: \n36: - **Core**: spec_code, checklist_evidence\n37: - **Overlay**: skill_agent, agent_cross_runtime, feature_catalog_code, playbook_capability\n38: \n39: ## QUALITY GATES\n40: \n41: evidence, scope, coverage\n42: \n43: ## VERDICTS\n44: \n45: `FAIL | CONDITIONAL | PASS`, PASS may set `hasAdvisories=true` when only P2 remain.\n46: \n47: ## CLAIM ADJUDICATION\n48: \n49: Every new P0/P1 must include: claim, evidenceRefs, counterevidenceSought, alternativeExplanation, finalSeverity, confidence, and downgradeTrigger.\n50: \n51: ## STATE FILES\n52: \n53: All paths are relative to the repo root.\n54: \n55: - Config: {state_paths_config}\n56: - State Log: {state_paths_state_log}\n57: - Findings Registry: {state_paths_findings_registry}\n58: - Strategy: {state_paths_strategy}\n59: - Write iteration narrative to: {state_paths_iteration_pattern}\n60: - Write per-iteration delta file to: {state_paths_delta_pattern}\n61: \n62: ## CONSTRAINTS\n63: \n64: - You are a LEAF agent. Do NOT dispatch sub-agents.\n65: - Target 9 tool calls. Soft max 12, hard max 13.\n66: - Write ALL findings to files. Do not hold in context.\n67: - Review target is READ-ONLY. Do not modify reviewed files.\n68: - Do not re-enter or restate any direction listed as swept or saturated above. The pivot-selected focus is a new read-only review direction, never permission to change the target.\n69: - Do not implement fixes during review. Report findings only; implementation is a separate follow-up step.\n70: - **ALLOWED WRITE PATHS (the ONLY paths you may create, modify, or append to)**:\n71:   - `{state_paths_iteration_pattern}`, this iteration's narrative markdown\n72:   - `{state_paths_state_log}`, append-only JSONL state log\n73:   - `{state_paths_delta_pattern}`, this iteration's delta JSONL\n74:   - `{state_paths_strategy}`, strategy.md (in-place updates only)\n75: - **BANNED OPERATIONS (NEVER execute against any path)**: `rm`, `rm -rf`, `git rm`, `mv`, `sed -i` (including `sed -i ''`), `rmdir`, `find ... -delete`, shell output-redirect truncate `>` against any file not in the allowed-write list, and any tool call whose effect is to delete, rename, or replace a file outside the allowed-write list. Reading is unrestricted; **writing, renaming, and deleting are scoped**.\n76: - **SCOPE VIOLATION PROTOCOL**: if your plan would require modifying any path NOT in the allowed-write list, you MUST STOP that action and emit a finding instead. Record the would-be mutation as a `scope_violation` entry in the iteration narrative (under a `## SCOPE VIOLATIONS` heading) and continue the review. NEVER execute the out-of-scope mutation. The review packet (`{state_paths_iteration_pattern}` directory and parents) is the only zone for your writes; the reviewed target spec/code is off-limits.\n77: - Append JSONL record with dimensions, filesReviewed, findingsSummary, findingsNew, traceabilityChecks, newFindingsRatio, and optional graphEvents.\n78: - When emitting the iteration JSONL record, include an optional `graphEvents` array representing coverage graph nodes and edges discovered this iteration. Omit the field when no graph events are produced. Each event MUST use one of these two EXACT shapes. The reducer discriminates node vs edge by `type`, then validates each node's `kind` against the node vocabulary and each edge's `relation` against the relation vocabulary — any event outside these vocabularies is silently dropped, and if every event is dropped the convergence graph stays empty (nodeCount 0, empty signals):\n79:   - Node: `{\"type\":\"node\",\"id\":\"<stable-id>\",\"kind\":\"<SLICE|DIMENSION|FILE|FINDING|EVIDENCE|REMEDIATION|BUG_CLASS|INVARIANT|PRODUCER|CONSUMER|TEST>\",\"label\":\"<short human name>\"}` — the semantic kind goes in the dedicated `kind` field (uppercase, one of those listed); `label` is a free-text display name ONLY, never the kind.\n80:   - Edge: `{\"type\":\"edge\",\"id\":\"<stable-id>\",\"source\":\"<nodeId>\",\"target\":\"<nodeId>\",\"relation\":\"<COVERS|EVIDENCE_FOR|CONTRADICTS|RESOLVES|CONFIRMS|ESCALATES|IN_DIMENSION|IN_FILE>\"}` — use `source`/`target`/`relation` (NOT `from`/`to`/`label`); `source` and `target` must reference node `id`s.\n81: \n82: ## OUTPUT CONTRACT\n83: \n84: You MUST produce THREE artifacts per iteration. The YAML-owned post_dispatch_validate step emits a `schema_mismatch` conflict event if any is missing or malformed.\n85: \n86: 1. **Iteration narrative markdown** at `{state_paths_iteration_pattern}` (path pre-substituted for the current iteration number). Structure: headings for Dimension, Files Reviewed, Findings by Severity (P0/P1/P2), Traceability Checks, Verdict, Next Dimension.\n87: \n88: 2. **Canonical JSONL iteration record** APPENDED to `{state_paths_state_log}`. The record MUST use `\"type\":\"iteration\"` EXACTLY, NOT `\"iteration_delta\"` or any other variant. The reducer counts records where `type === \"iteration\"` only; other types are silently ignored. Required schema:\n89: \n90: ```json\n91: {\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":<n>,\"mode\":\"review\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-review\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=review target_agent=deep-review\",\"run\":\"<run-id>\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"<dimension-or-focus>\",\"dimensions\":[\"...\"],\"filesReviewed\":[\"path:line\"],\"findingsCount\":<n>,\"findingsSummary\":{\"P0\":<n>,\"P1\":<n>,\"P2\":<n>},\"findingsNew\":[],\"findingDetails\":[],\"traceabilityChecks\":{},\"newFindingsRatio\":<0..1>,\"sessionId\":\"<session-id>\",\"generation\":<n>,\"lineageMode\":\"new\",\"timestamp\":\"<ISO-8601>\",\"durationMs\":<n>,\"graphEvents\":[/* optional */]}\n92: ```\n93: \n94: ### v2 Search Depth Output (when scopeClass is standard or complex)\n95: \n96: For standard or complex review scope, set `\"reviewDepthSchemaVersion\":2` on the same iteration JSONL record and include these v2 fields in addition to the v1 fields above:\n97: \n98: - `reviewDepthApplicability`: `{scopeClass,enforcement,reason,evidenceRefs}` where `scopeClass` is `trivial`, `standard`, or `complex`; `enforcement` is `strict`, `warn`, or `skip`.\n99: - `targetSelection`: `{selectedTargets,selectionReason,discoveryMethods,omittedHighRiskTargets,graphStatus,semanticSearchStatus,evidenceRefs}`. Name how targets were chosen, what high-risk targets were omitted, and whether graph/semantic search was available, unavailable, or partial.\n100: - `searchCoverage`: `{requiredBugClasses,covered,ruledOut,deferred,blocked,graphCoverageMode}` where `graphCoverageMode` is `graph`, `graphless_fallback`, or `unavailable_blocked`.\n101: - `searchLedger[]`: ledger rows with required `id`, `dimension`, `targetRefs`, `bugClass`, `disposition`, and `rationale`; include `hypothesis` or `invariant` (at least one); include `searchActions[]` with `{method,queryOrPath,result,evidenceRefs}`.\n102: - Each ledger row needs exactly one disposition link: `linkedFindingId` for `finding` (must match an id in `findingDetails[]`), `ruledOutReason` for `ruled_out`, `deferredReason` for `deferred`, `blockedReason` for `blocked`, or `notApplicableReason` for `not_applicable`.\n103: \n104: Trivial-scope exemption: when `scopeClass` is `trivial` and `enforcement` is `skip`, `searchLedger` may be `[]`, but `reviewDepthApplicability.evidenceRefs` MUST cite proof that the target is trivial.\n105: \n106: Compact v2 example:\n107: \n108: ```json\n109: {\"reviewDepthSchemaVersion\":2,\"reviewDepthApplicability\":{\"scopeClass\":\"standard\",\"enforcement\":\"strict\",\"reason\":\"non-trivial target\",\"evidenceRefs\":[\"path/to/file.ts:42\"]},\"targetSelection\":{\"selectedTargets\":[\"path/to/file.ts\"],\"selectionReason\":\"state transition producer\",\"discoveryMethods\":[\"direct_read\",\"exact_search\"],\"omittedHighRiskTargets\":[],\"graphStatus\":\"unavailable\",\"semanticSearchStatus\":\"partial\",\"evidenceRefs\":[\"path/to/file.ts:42\"]},\"searchCoverage\":{\"requiredBugClasses\":[\"state_transition\"],\"covered\":[],\"ruledOut\":[\"state_transition\"],\"deferred\":[],\"blocked\":[],\"graphCoverageMode\":\"graphless_fallback\"},\"searchLedger\":[{\"id\":\"SL-001\",\"dimension\":\"correctness\",\"targetRefs\":[\"path/to/file.ts\"],\"bugClass\":\"state_transition\",\"hypothesis\":\"state transition can skip validation\",\"searchActions\":[{\"method\":\"direct_read\",\"queryOrPath\":\"path/to/file.ts\",\"result\":\"guard present on all branches\",\"evidenceRefs\":[\"path/to/file.ts:42\"]}],\"disposition\":\"ruled_out\",\"rationale\":\"all branches call the guard\",\"ruledOutReason\":\"verified by direct read\"}]}\n110: ```\n111: \n112: Legacy unversioned records remain valid during rollout. Phase D validator behavior should warn on legacy shallow records and strictly enforce this shape only for explicit v2 records.\n113: \n114: Append via single-line JSON with newline terminator, e.g. `echo '<single-line-json>' >> {state_paths_state_log}`. Do NOT pretty-print. Do NOT print to stdout only; it MUST land in the state log file.\n115: \n116: 3. **Per-iteration delta file** at `{state_paths_delta_pattern}` (path pre-substituted, e.g. `deltas/iter-001.jsonl`). This file holds the structured delta stream for this iteration: one `{\"type\":\"iteration\",...}` record (same as the state-log append) plus per-event structured records (one per graphEvent, finding, classification, traceability-check, ruled_out direction). Each record on its own JSON line.\n117: \n118: Example delta file contents (one review iteration):\n119: ```json\n120: {\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":3,\"mode\":\"review\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-review\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=review target_agent=deep-review\",\"run\":\"run-001\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"correctness\",\"dimensions\":[\"correctness\"],\"filesReviewed\":[\"path/to/file.ts:42\"],\"findingsCount\":7,\"findingsSummary\":{\"P0\":0,\"P1\":2,\"P2\":5},\"findingsNew\":[],\"findingDetails\":[],\"newFindingsRatio\":0.41,\"sessionId\":\"session-001\",\"generation\":1,\"lineageMode\":\"new\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-30T00:00:00Z\",\"durationMs\":120000,\"graphEvents\":[]}\n121: {\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"R3-P1-001\",\"severity\":\"P1\",\"cluster\":\"...\",\"file\":\"path:line\",\"title\":\"...\",\"iteration\":3}\n122: {\"type\":\"classification\",\"detail\":\"...\",\"iteration\":3}\n123: {\"type\":\"ruled_out\",\"direction\":\"...\",\"reason\":\"...\",\"iteration\":3}\n124: ```\n125: \n126: All three artifacts are REQUIRED. The post_dispatch_validate step fails the iteration if any artifact is missing, malformed, or if the state-log append uses the wrong record type (`iteration_delta` etc.).\n\n(End of file - total 126 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"DEEP-REVIEW\nResolved route: mode=review; target_agent=@deep-review; execution=single_review_iteration; state_source=externalized_files; do_not_switch_mode=true\n\n# Deep-Review Iteration Prompt Pack\n\nThis prompt pack renders the per-iteration context for the `@deep-review` LEAF agent (native executor) or a CLI executor (e.g. `opencode run`). Tokens use curly-brace syntax and are substituted by `renderPromptPack` before dispatch.\n\n## STATE\n\n{state_summary}\n\nReview Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\nMode: review\nDimension: {next_dimension}\nReview Target: {review_target}\nReview Scope Files: {review_scope_files}\nPrior Findings: P0={p0_count} P1={p1_count} P2={p2_count}\n\n## PIVOT LINEAGE\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl","text":"DEEP-REVIEW\nResolved route: mode=review; target_agent=@deep-review; execution=single_review_iteration; state_source=externalized_files; do_not_switch_mode=true\n\n# Deep-Review Iteration Prompt Pack\n\nThis prompt pack renders the per-iteration context for the `@deep-review` LEAF agent (native executor) or a CLI executor (e.g. `opencode run`). Tokens use curly-brace syntax and are substituted by `renderPromptPack` before dispatch.\n\n## STATE\n\n{state_summary}\n\nReview Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\nMode: review\nDimension: {next_dimension}\nReview Target: {review_target}\nReview Scope Files: {review_scope_files}\nPrior Findings: P0={p0_count} P1={p1_count} P2={p2_count}\n\n## PIVOT LINEAGE\n\n{pivot_lineage}\n\nSwept or saturated review directions that MUST NOT be re-entered:\n{saturated_directions}\n\n## SHARED DOCTRINE\n\nLoad `.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review_core.md` before final severity calls.\n\n## REVIEW DIMENSIONS\n\ncorrectness, security, traceability, maintainability\n\n## TRACEABILITY PROTOCOLS\n\n- **Core**: spec_code, checklist_evidence\n- **Overlay**: skill_agent, agent_cross_runtime, feature_catalog_code, playbook_capability\n\n## QUALITY GATES\n\nevidence, scope, coverage\n\n## VERDICTS\n\n`FAIL | CONDITIONAL | PASS`, PASS may set `hasAdvisories=true` when only P2 remain.\n\n## CLAIM ADJUDICATION\n\nEvery new P0/P1 must include: claim, evidenceRefs, counterevidenceSought, alternativeExplanation, finalSeverity, confidence, and downgradeTrigger.\n\n## STATE FILES\n\nAll paths are relative to the repo root.\n\n- Config: {state_paths_config}\n- State Log: {state_paths_state_log}\n- Findings Registry: {state_paths_findings_registry}\n- Strategy: {state_paths_strategy}\n- Write iteration narrative to: {state_paths_iteration_pattern}\n- Write per-iteration delta file to: {state_paths_delta_pattern}\n\n## CONSTRAINTS\n\n- You are a LEAF agent. Do NOT dispatch sub-agents.\n- Target 9 tool calls. Soft max 12, hard max 13.\n- Write ALL findings to files. Do not hold in context.\n- Review target is READ-ONLY. Do not modify reviewed files.\n- Do not re-enter or restate any direction listed as swept or saturated above. The pivot-selected focus is a new read-only review direction, never permission to change the target.\n- Do not implement fixes during review. Report findings only; implementation is a separate follow-up step.\n- **ALLOWED WRITE PATHS (the ONLY paths you may create, modify, or append to)**:\n  - `{state_paths_iteration_pattern}`, this iteration's narrative markdown\n  - `{state_paths_state_log}`, append-only JSONL state log\n  - `{state_paths_delta_pattern}`, this iteration's delta JSONL\n  - `{state_paths_strategy}`, strategy.md (in-place updates only)\n- **BANNED OPERATIONS (NEVER execute against any path)**: `rm`, `rm -rf`, `git rm`, `mv`, `sed -i` (including `sed -i ''`), `rmdir`, `find ... -delete`, shell output-redirect truncate `>` against any file not in the allowed-write list, and any tool call whose effect is to delete, rename, or replace a file outside the allowed-write list. Reading is unrestricted; **writing, renaming, and deleting are scoped**.\n- **SCOPE VIOLATION PROTOCOL**: if your plan would require modifying any path NOT in the allowed-write list, you MUST STOP that action and emit a finding instead. Record the would-be mutation as a `scope_violation` entry in the iteration narrative (under a `## SCOPE VIOLATIONS` heading) and continue the review. NEVER execute the out-of-scope mutation. The review packet (`{state_paths_iteration_pattern}` directory and parents) is the only zone for your writes; the reviewed target spec/code is off-limits.\n- Append JSONL record with dimensions, filesReviewed, findingsSummary, findingsNew, traceabilityChecks, newFindingsRatio, and optional graphEvents.\n- When emitting the iteration JSONL record, include an optional `graphEvents` array representing coverage graph nodes and edges discovered this iteration. Omit the field when no graph events are produced. Each event MUST use one of these two EXACT shapes. The reducer discriminates node vs edge by `type`, then validates each node's `kind` against the node vocabulary and each edge's `relation` against the relation vocabulary — any event outside these vocabularies is silently dropped, and if every event is dropped the convergence graph stays empty (nodeCount 0, empty signals):\n  - Node: `{\"type\":\"node\",\"id\":\"<stable-id>\",\"kind\":\"<SLICE|DIMENSION|FILE|FINDING|EVIDENCE|REMEDIATION|BUG_CLASS|INVARIANT|PRODUCER|CONSUMER|TEST>\",\"label\":\"<short human name>\"}` — the semantic kind goes in the dedicated `kind` field (uppercase, one of those listed); `label` is a free-text display name ONLY, never the kind.\n  - Edge: `{\"type\":\"edge\",\"id\":\"<stable-id>\",\"source\":\"<nodeId>\",\"target\":\"<nodeId>\",\"relation\":\"<COVERS|EVIDENCE_FOR|CONTRADICTS|RESOLVES|CONFIRMS|ESCALATES|IN_DIMENSION|IN_FILE>\"}` — use `source`/`target`/`relation` (NOT `from`/`to`/`label`); `source` and `target` must reference node `id`s.\n\n## OUTPUT CONTRACT\n\nYou MUST produce THREE artifacts per iteration. The YAML-owned post_dispatch_validate step emits a `schema_mismatch` conflict event if any is missing or malformed.\n\n1. **Iteration narrative markdown** at `{state_paths_iteration_pattern}` (path pre-substituted for the current iteration number). Structure: headings for Dimension, Files Reviewed, Findings by Severity (P0/P1/P2), Traceability Checks, Verdict, Next Dimension.\n\n2. **Canonical JSONL iteration record** APPENDED to `{state_paths_state_log}`. The record MUST use `\"type\":\"iteration\"` EXACTLY, NOT `\"iteration_delta\"` or any other variant. The reducer counts records where `type === \"iteration\"` only; other types are silently ignored. Required schema:\n\n```json\n{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":<n>,\"mode\":\"review\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-review\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=review target_agent=deep-review\",\"run\":\"<run-id>\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"<dimension-or-focus>\",\"dimensions\":[\"...\"],\"filesReviewed\":[\"path:line\"],\"findingsCount\":<n>,\"findingsSummary\":{\"P0\":<n>,\"P1\":<n>,\"P2\":<n>},\"findingsNew\":[],\"findingDetails\":[],\"traceabilityChecks\":{},\"newFindingsRatio\":<0..1>,\"sessionId\":\"<session-id>\",\"generation\":<n>,\"lineageMode\":\"new\",\"timestamp\":\"<ISO-8601>\",\"durationMs\":<n>,\"graphEvents\":[/* optional */]}\n```\n\n### v2 Search Depth Output (when scopeClass is standard or complex)\n\nFor standard or complex review scope, set `\"reviewDepthSchemaVersion\":2` on the same iteration JSONL record and include these v2 fields in addition to the v1 fields above:\n\n- `reviewDepthApplicability`: `{scopeClass,enforcement,reason,evidenceRefs}` where `scopeClass` is `trivial`, `standard`, or `complex`; `enforcement` is `strict`, `warn`, or `skip`.\n- `targetSelection`: `{selectedTargets,selectionReason,discoveryMethods,omittedHighRiskTargets,graphStatus,semanticSearchStatus,evidenceRefs}`. Name how targets were chosen, what high-risk targets were omitted, and whether graph/semantic search was available, unavailable, or partial.\n- `searchCoverage`: `{requiredBugClasses,covered,ruledOut,deferred,blocked,graphCoverageMode}` where `graphCoverageMode` is `graph`, `graphless_fallback`, or `unavailable_blocked`.\n- `searchLedger[]`: ledger rows with required `id`, `dimension`, `targetRefs`, `bugClass`, `disposition`, and `rationale`; include `hypothesis` or `invariant` (at least one); include `searchActions[]` with `{method,queryOrPath,result,evidenceRefs}`.\n- Each ledger row needs exactly one disposition link: `linkedFindingId` for `finding` (must match an id in `findingDetails[]`), `ruledOutReason` for `ruled_out`, `deferredReason` for `deferred`, `blockedReason` for `blocked`, or `notApplicableReason` for `not_applicable`.\n\nTrivial-scope exemption: when `scopeClass` is `trivial` and `enforcement` is `skip`, `searchLedger` may be `[]`, but `reviewDepthApplicability.evidenceRefs` MUST cite proof that the target is trivial.\n\nCompact v2 example:\n\n```json\n{\"reviewDepthSchemaVersion\":2,\"reviewDepthApplicability\":{\"scopeClass\":\"standard\",\"enforcement\":\"strict\",\"reason\":\"non-trivial target\",\"evidenceRefs\":[\"path/to/file.ts:42\"]},\"targetSelection\":{\"selectedTargets\":[\"path/to/file.ts\"],\"selectionReason\":\"state transition producer\",\"discoveryMethods\":[\"direct_read\",\"exact_search\"],\"omittedHighRiskTargets\":[],\"graphStatus\":\"unavailable\",\"semanticSearchStatus\":\"partial\",\"evidenceRefs\":[\"path/to/file.ts:42\"]},\"searchCoverage\":{\"requiredBugClasses\":[\"state_transition\"],\"covered\":[],\"ruledOut\":[\"state_transition\"],\"deferred\":[],\"blocked\":[],\"graphCoverageMode\":\"graphless_fallback\"},\"searchLedger\":[{\"id\":\"SL-001\",\"dimension\":\"correctness\",\"targetRefs\":[\"path/to/file.ts\"],\"bugClass\":\"state_transition\",\"hypothesis\":\"state transition can skip validation\",\"searchActions\":[{\"method\":\"direct_read\",\"queryOrPath\":\"path/to/file.ts\",\"result\":\"guard present on all branches\",\"evidenceRefs\":[\"path/to/file.ts:42\"]}],\"disposition\":\"ruled_out\",\"rationale\":\"all branches call the guard\",\"ruledOutReason\":\"verified by direct read\"}]}\n```\n\nLegacy unversioned records remain valid during rollout. Phase D validator behavior should warn on legacy shallow records and strictly enforce this shape only for explicit v2 records.\n\nAppend via single-line JSON with newline terminator, e.g. `echo '<single-line-json>' >> {state_paths_state_log}`. Do NOT pretty-print. Do NOT print to stdout only; it MUST land in the state log file.\n\n3. **Per-iteration delta file** at `{state_paths_delta_pattern}` (path pre-substituted, e.g. `deltas/iter-001.jsonl`). This file holds the structured delta stream for this iteration: one `{\"type\":\"iteration\",...}` record (same as the state-log append) plus per-event structured records (one per graphEvent, finding, classification, traceability-check, ruled_out direction). Each record on its own JSON line.\n\nExample delta file contents (one review iteration):\n```json\n{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":3,\"mode\":\"review\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-review\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=review target_agent=deep-review\",\"run\":\"run-001\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"correctness\",\"dimensions\":[\"correctness\"],\"filesReviewed\":[\"path/to/file.ts:42\"],\"findingsCount\":7,\"findingsSummary\":{\"P0\":0,\"P1\":2,\"P2\":5},\"findingsNew\":[],\"findingDetails\":[],\"newFindingsRatio\":0.41,\"sessionId\":\"session-001\",\"generation\":1,\"lineageMode\":\"new\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-30T00:00:00Z\",\"durationMs\":120000,\"graphEvents\":[]}\n{\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"R3-P1-001\",\"severity\":\"P1\",\"cluster\":\"...\",\"file\":\"path:line\",\"title\":\"...\",\"iteration\":3}\n{\"type\":\"classification\",\"detail\":\"...\",\"iteration\":3}\n{\"type\":\"ruled_out\",\"direction\":\"...\",\"reason\":\"...\",\"iteration\":3}\n```\n\nAll three artifacts are REQUIRED. The post_dispatch_validate step fails the iteration if any artifact is missing, malformed, or if the state-log append uses the wrong record type (`iteration_delta` etc.).","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":126,"totalLines":126,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl","time":{"start":1783915559414,"end":1783915559442}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0df59b61eea8d697016a546427545c819183d5cec9757bcd01"}},"id":"prt_f59a739f5001mzDeoAN3hx540p","sessionID":"ses_0a65ac472ffeDn3G1fX5LbU2k8","messageID":"msg_f59a6ea830011kqj0WvDYGJREd"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783915559446,"sessionID":"ses_0a65ac472ffeDn3G1fX5LbU2k8","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_lWZUy5FB9akSebgNn4aaT5Ua","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/deep_review_strategy.md","offset":1,"limit":2000},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/deep_review_strategy.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Review Strategy Template\n3: description: Runtime template copied to review/ during initialization to track review progress, dimension coverage, findings, and outcomes across iterations.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"deep review strategy template\"\n6:   - \"review dimension tracking\"\n7:   - \"exhausted review approaches\"\n8:   - \"review session tracking\"\n9: importance_tier: normal\n10: contextType: planning\n11: version: 1.11.0.13\n12: ---\n13: \n14: # Deep Review Strategy - Session Tracking Template\n15: \n16: Runtime template copied into the resolved `{artifact_dir}/` during initialization. Tracks review progress across iterations.\n17: \n18: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n19: \n20: ### Purpose\n21: \n22: Serves as the \"persistent brain\" for a deep review session. Records which dimensions remain, what was found (P0/P1/P2), what review approaches worked or failed, and where to focus next. Read by the orchestrator and agents at every iteration.\n23: \n24: ### Usage\n25: \n26: - **Init:** Orchestrator copies this template to `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md` and populates Topic, Review Dimensions, Known Context, and Review Boundaries from config and memory context.\n27: - **Per iteration:** Agent reads Next Focus, reviews the assigned dimension/files, updates findings, marks dimensions complete, and sets new Next Focus.\n28: - **Mutability:** Mutable, updated by both orchestrator and agents throughout the session.\n29: - **Protection:** None (shared mutable state). Orchestrator validates consistency on resume.\n30: - **Ownership:** Machine-managed metrics and coverage blocks are wrapped in explicit ownership markers. Human commentary and operator overrides live outside those markers.\n31: \n32: ---\n33: \n34: ## 2. TOPIC\n35: [Review target description from config -- set during initialization]\n36: \n37: ---\n38: \n39: ## 3. REVIEW DIMENSIONS (remaining)\n40: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n41: - [ ] D1 Correctness, Logic errors, off-by-one, wrong return types, broken invariants\n42: - [ ] D2 Security, Injection, auth bypass, secrets exposure, unsafe deserialization\n43: - [ ] D3 Traceability, Spec/code alignment, checklist evidence, cross-reference integrity\n44: - [ ] D4 Maintainability, Patterns, clarity, documentation quality, safe follow-on change cost\n45: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n46: \n47: ---\n48: \n49: ## 4. NON-GOALS\n50: [What this review session is NOT trying to assess -- populated during initialization]\n51: \n52: ---\n53: \n54: ## 5. STOP CONDITIONS\n55: [Explicit conditions beyond convergence that should end the session -- populated during initialization]\n56: \n57: ---\n58: \n59: ## 6. COMPLETED DIMENSIONS\n60: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n61: [None yet -- populated as iterations complete dimension reviews]\n62: \n63: | Dimension | Verdict | Iteration | Summary |\n64: |-----------|---------|-----------|---------|\n65: | [D1 Correctness] | [PASS/CONDITIONAL/FAIL] | [N] | [1-sentence result] |\n66: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n67: \n68: ---\n69: \n70: ## 7. RUNNING FINDINGS\n71: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n72: - **P0 (Critical):** 0 active\n73: - **P1 (Major):** 0 active\n74: - **P2 (Minor):** 0 active\n75: - **Delta this iteration:** +0 P0, +0 P1, +0 P2\n76: \n77: [Findings are tracked in `deep-review-findings-registry.json`. This section provides a running count summary updated after each iteration.]\n78: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n79: \n80: ---\n81: \n82: ## 8. WHAT WORKED\n83: [First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n84: - [Approach]: [Why it worked] (iteration N)\n85: \n86: ---\n87: \n88: ## 9. WHAT FAILED\n89: [First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n90: - [Approach]: [Why it failed] (iteration N)\n91: \n92: ---\n93: \n94: ## 10. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n95: [Populated when a review approach has been tried from multiple angles without yielding new findings]\n96: \n97: ### [Category Name] -- BLOCKED (iteration N, N attempts)\n98: - What was tried: [specific review approaches attempted]\n99: - Why blocked: [root cause of exhaustion]\n100: - Do NOT retry: [explicit prohibition]\n101: \n102: ### [Category Name] -- PRODUCTIVE (iteration N)\n103: - What worked: [successful review approaches in this category]\n104: - Prefer for: [related dimensions where this category may help]\n105: \n106: ---\n107: \n108: ## 10A. SATURATED / SWEPT DIMENSIONS AND EXPANSION FRONTIER\n109: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n110: - Completed pivots: 0\n111: - Failed pivots: 0\n112: - Audited overrides: 0\n113: - Swept: none yet\n114: - Pivot lineage: none yet\n115: - Remaining frontier: none recorded\n116: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n117: \n118: ---\n119: \n120: ## 11. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n121: [Review angles that were investigated and definitively eliminated -- consolidated from iteration dead-end data]\n122: - [Approach]: [Why ruled out] (iteration N, evidence: [source])\n123: \n124: ---\n125: \n126: ## 12. NEXT FOCUS\n127: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n128: [Recommended focus area for the next iteration -- updated at end of each iteration. Includes target dimension and/or specific files to review.]\n129: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n130: \n131: ---\n132: \n133: ## 13. KNOWN CONTEXT\n134: [Populated during initialization from memory_context() results, if any prior work exists]\n135: \n136: ### Bounded Context Snapshot\n137: \n138: Populate during initialization before the first review dimension runs. Keep this pointer-based and scoped to the declared review target:\n139: \n140: - Target pointers: files, specs, symbols, or resource-map entries under review.\n141: - Behavior claims: acceptance criteria, public contracts, or docs to verify.\n142: - Reuse and conventions: existing patterns that define expected implementation shape.\n143: - Review risks and gaps: stale graph or memory caveats, missing files, and out-of-scope areas.\n144: \n145: Do not inline full source bodies. Do not dispatch the retired standalone context loop. Use this snapshot only to seed review dimensions and final traceability.\n146: \n147: ---\n148: \n149: ## 14. CROSS-REFERENCE STATUS\n150: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n151: [Alignment checks completed across core and overlay protocols]\n152: \n153: | Protocol | Level | Status | Iteration | Notes |\n154: |----------|-------|--------|-----------|-------|\n155: | `spec_code` | core | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked] | [N] | [details] |\n156: | `checklist_evidence` | core | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked] | [N] | [details] |\n157: | `skill_agent` | overlay | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked/notApplicable] | [N] | [details] |\n158: | `agent_cross_runtime` | overlay | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked/notApplicable] | [N] | [details] |\n159: | `feature_catalog_code` | overlay | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked/notApplicable] | [N] | [details] |\n160: | `playbook_capability` | overlay | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked/notApplicable] | [N] | [details] |\n161: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n162: \n163: ---\n164: \n165: ## 15. FILES UNDER REVIEW\n166: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n167: [Per-file coverage state table -- populated during initialization from scope discovery]\n168: \n169: | File | Dimensions Reviewed | Last Iteration | Findings | Status |\n170: |------|-------------------|----------------|----------|--------|\n171: | [path/to/file] | [D1, D3] | [N] | [0 P0, 1 P1, 2 P2] | [partial/complete] |\n172: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n173: \n174: ---\n175: \n176: ## 16. REVIEW BOUNDARIES\n177: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n178: - Max iterations: [from config]\n179: - Convergence threshold: [from config]\n180: - Rolling STOP threshold: 0.08\n181: - No-progress threshold: 0.05\n182: - Coverage stabilization passes required: 1\n183: - Session lineage: sessionId=[from config.sessionId], parentSessionId=[from config.parentSessionId], generation=[from config.generation], lineageMode=[from config.lineageMode]\n184: - Findings registry: `deep-review-findings-registry.json`\n185: - Release-readiness states: in-progress | converged | release-blocking\n186: - Per-iteration budget: [from config.maxToolCallsPerIteration] tool calls, [from config.maxMinutesPerIteration] minutes\n187: - Severity threshold: [from config.severityThreshold]\n188: - Review target type: [from config.reviewTargetType]\n189: - Cross-reference checks: core=[from config.crossReference.core], overlay=[from config.crossReference.overlay]\n190: - Started: [timestamp]\n191: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n192: \n193: ---\n194: \n195: ## 17. EXAMPLE (POPULATED)\n196: \n197: Reference snippet showing a partially populated strategy file mid-review. Use this as a visual anchor when opening a live strategy doc.\n198: \n199: ```markdown\n200: ## 1. REVIEW CHARTER\n201: - Target: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research (skill, v1.4.0)\n202: - Dimensions: correctness, test-coverage, cross-runtime-parity, observability\n203: - Stop conditions: rolling newInfoRatio < 0.08 for 2 iterations OR all dimensions converged OR max=7 reached\n204: - Success criteria: zero P0 in correctness; test-coverage P0 resolved or deferred with rationale\n205: \n206: ## 4. NEXT FOCUS\n207: - Dimension: test-coverage\n208: - Files: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs, .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/tests/deep-research-contract-parity.vitest.ts\n209: - Why: Iteration 2 surfaced a P0 (convergence-path coverage gap); needs a focused follow-up before correctness can terminate PASS.\n210: \n211: ## 9. COVERAGE MATRIX\n212: | Dimension            | Status     | Iterations touched |\n213: |----------------------|------------|--------------------|\n214: | correctness          | converged  | 1                  |\n215: | test-coverage        | converging | 2, 4               |\n216: | cross-runtime-parity | converging | 3                  |\n217: | observability        | converging | 4                  |\n218: ```\n\n(End of file - total 218 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Review Strategy Template\ndescription: Runtime template copied to review/ during initialization to track review progress, dimension coverage, findings, and outcomes across iterations.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review strategy template\"\n  - \"review dimension tracking\"\n  - \"exhausted review approaches\"\n  - \"review session tracking\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: planning\nversion: 1.11.0.13\n---\n\n# Deep Review Strategy - Session Tracking Template\n\nRuntime template copied into the resolved `{artifact_dir}/` during initialization. Tracks review progress across iterations.\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/deep_review_strategy.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Review Strategy Template\ndescription: Runtime template copied to review/ during initialization to track review progress, dimension coverage, findings, and outcomes across iterations.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review strategy template\"\n  - \"review dimension tracking\"\n  - \"exhausted review approaches\"\n  - \"review session tracking\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: planning\nversion: 1.11.0.13\n---\n\n# Deep Review Strategy - Session Tracking Template\n\nRuntime template copied into the resolved `{artifact_dir}/` during initialization. Tracks review progress across iterations.\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nServes as the \"persistent brain\" for a deep review session. Records which dimensions remain, what was found (P0/P1/P2), what review approaches worked or failed, and where to focus next. Read by the orchestrator and agents at every iteration.\n\n### Usage\n\n- **Init:** Orchestrator copies this template to `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md` and populates Topic, Review Dimensions, Known Context, and Review Boundaries from config and memory context.\n- **Per iteration:** Agent reads Next Focus, reviews the assigned dimension/files, updates findings, marks dimensions complete, and sets new Next Focus.\n- **Mutability:** Mutable, updated by both orchestrator and agents throughout the session.\n- **Protection:** None (shared mutable state). Orchestrator validates consistency on resume.\n- **Ownership:** Machine-managed metrics and coverage blocks are wrapped in explicit ownership markers. Human commentary and operator overrides live outside those markers.\n\n---\n\n## 2. TOPIC\n[Review target description from config -- set during initialization]\n\n---\n\n## 3. REVIEW DIMENSIONS (remaining)\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n- [ ] D1 Correctness, Logic errors, off-by-one, wrong return types, broken invariants\n- [ ] D2 Security, Injection, auth bypass, secrets exposure, unsafe deserialization\n- [ ] D3 Traceability, Spec/code alignment, checklist evidence, cross-reference integrity\n- [ ] D4 Maintainability, Patterns, clarity, documentation quality, safe follow-on change cost\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 4. NON-GOALS\n[What this review session is NOT trying to assess -- populated during initialization]\n\n---\n\n## 5. STOP CONDITIONS\n[Explicit conditions beyond convergence that should end the session -- populated during initialization]\n\n---\n\n## 6. COMPLETED DIMENSIONS\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n[None yet -- populated as iterations complete dimension reviews]\n\n| Dimension | Verdict | Iteration | Summary |\n|-----------|---------|-----------|---------|\n| [D1 Correctness] | [PASS/CONDITIONAL/FAIL] | [N] | [1-sentence result] |\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 7. RUNNING FINDINGS\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n- **P0 (Critical):** 0 active\n- **P1 (Major):** 0 active\n- **P2 (Minor):** 0 active\n- **Delta this iteration:** +0 P0, +0 P1, +0 P2\n\n[Findings are tracked in `deep-review-findings-registry.json`. This section provides a running count summary updated after each iteration.]\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 8. WHAT WORKED\n[First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n- [Approach]: [Why it worked] (iteration N)\n\n---\n\n## 9. WHAT FAILED\n[First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n- [Approach]: [Why it failed] (iteration N)\n\n---\n\n## 10. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n[Populated when a review approach has been tried from multiple angles without yielding new findings]\n\n### [Category Name] -- BLOCKED (iteration N, N attempts)\n- What was tried: [specific review approaches attempted]\n- Why blocked: [root cause of exhaustion]\n- Do NOT retry: [explicit prohibition]\n\n### [Category Name] -- PRODUCTIVE (iteration N)\n- What worked: [successful review approaches in this category]\n- Prefer for: [related dimensions where this category may help]\n\n---\n\n## 10A. SATURATED / SWEPT DIMENSIONS AND EXPANSION FRONTIER\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n- Completed pivots: 0\n- Failed pivots: 0\n- Audited overrides: 0\n- Swept: none yet\n- Pivot lineage: none yet\n- Remaining frontier: none recorded\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 11. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n[Review angles that were investigated and definitively eliminated -- consolidated from iteration dead-end data]\n- [Approach]: [Why ruled out] (iteration N, evidence: [source])\n\n---\n\n## 12. NEXT FOCUS\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n[Recommended focus area for the next iteration -- updated at end of each iteration. Includes target dimension and/or specific files to review.]\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 13. KNOWN CONTEXT\n[Populated during initialization from memory_context() results, if any prior work exists]\n\n### Bounded Context Snapshot\n\nPopulate during initialization before the first review dimension runs. Keep this pointer-based and scoped to the declared review target:\n\n- Target pointers: files, specs, symbols, or resource-map entries under review.\n- Behavior claims: acceptance criteria, public contracts, or docs to verify.\n- Reuse and conventions: existing patterns that define expected implementation shape.\n- Review risks and gaps: stale graph or memory caveats, missing files, and out-of-scope areas.\n\nDo not inline full source bodies. Do not dispatch the retired standalone context loop. Use this snapshot only to seed review dimensions and final traceability.\n\n---\n\n## 14. CROSS-REFERENCE STATUS\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n[Alignment checks completed across core and overlay protocols]\n\n| Protocol | Level | Status | Iteration | Notes |\n|----------|-------|--------|-----------|-------|\n| `spec_code` | core | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked] | [N] | [details] |\n| `checklist_evidence` | core | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked] | [N] | [details] |\n| `skill_agent` | overlay | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked/notApplicable] | [N] | [details] |\n| `agent_cross_runtime` | overlay | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked/notApplicable] | [N] | [details] |\n| `feature_catalog_code` | overlay | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked/notApplicable] | [N] | [details] |\n| `playbook_capability` | overlay | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked/notApplicable] | [N] | [details] |\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 15. FILES UNDER REVIEW\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n[Per-file coverage state table -- populated during initialization from scope discovery]\n\n| File | Dimensions Reviewed | Last Iteration | Findings | Status |\n|------|-------------------|----------------|----------|--------|\n| [path/to/file] | [D1, D3] | [N] | [0 P0, 1 P1, 2 P2] | [partial/complete] |\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 16. REVIEW BOUNDARIES\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n- Max iterations: [from config]\n- Convergence threshold: [from config]\n- Rolling STOP threshold: 0.08\n- No-progress threshold: 0.05\n- Coverage stabilization passes required: 1\n- Session lineage: sessionId=[from config.sessionId], parentSessionId=[from config.parentSessionId], generation=[from config.generation], lineageMode=[from config.lineageMode]\n- Findings registry: `deep-review-findings-registry.json`\n- Release-readiness states: in-progress | converged | release-blocking\n- Per-iteration budget: [from config.maxToolCallsPerIteration] tool calls, [from config.maxMinutesPerIteration] minutes\n- Severity threshold: [from config.severityThreshold]\n- Review target type: [from config.reviewTargetType]\n- Cross-reference checks: core=[from config.crossReference.core], overlay=[from config.crossReference.overlay]\n- Started: [timestamp]\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 17. EXAMPLE (POPULATED)\n\nReference snippet showing a partially populated strategy file mid-review. Use this as a visual anchor when opening a live strategy doc.\n\n```markdown\n## 1. REVIEW CHARTER\n- Target: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research (skill, v1.4.0)\n- Dimensions: correctness, test-coverage, cross-runtime-parity, observability\n- Stop conditions: rolling newInfoRatio < 0.08 for 2 iterations OR all dimensions converged OR max=7 reached\n- Success criteria: zero P0 in correctness; test-coverage P0 resolved or deferred with rationale\n\n## 4. NEXT FOCUS\n- Dimension: test-coverage\n- Files: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs, .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/tests/deep-research-contract-parity.vitest.ts\n- Why: Iteration 2 surfaced a P0 (convergence-path coverage gap); needs a focused follow-up before correctness can terminate PASS.\n\n## 9. COVERAGE MATRIX\n| Dimension            | Status     | Iterations touched |\n|----------------------|------------|--------------------|\n| correctness          | converged  | 1                  |\n| test-coverage        | converging | 2, 4               |\n| cross-runtime-parity | converging | 3                  |\n| observability        | converging | 4                  |\n```","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":218,"totalLines":218,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/deep_review_strategy.md","time":{"start":1783915559412,"end":1783915559444}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0df59b61eea8d697016a54642754548191979f333e28d464fc"}},"id":"prt_f59a739f3001y55IJb0JTOxL0I","sessionID":"ses_0a65ac472ffeDn3G1fX5LbU2k8","messageID":"msg_f59a6ea830011kqj0WvDYGJREd"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783915559449,"sessionID":"ses_0a65ac472ffeDn3G1fX5LbU2k8","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_9rIlZscwuUlxoNkV62I2R47d","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/references/state/state_reducer_registry.md","offset":1,"limit":2000},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/references/state/state_reducer_registry.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"Deep Review State Reducer And Registry\"\n3: description: \"Focused reference for reducer ownership, findings registry semantics, fail-closed behavior, and reconstruction rules.\"\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"deep review reducer registry\"\n6:   - \"review findings registry\"\n7:   - \"deep review reducer ownership\"\n8:   - \"review state reconstruction\"\n9: importance_tier: important\n10: contextType: implementation\n11: version: 1.11.0.4\n12: ---\n13: \n14: # Deep Review State Reducer And Registry\n15: \n16: The reducer is the single writer for derived review state. Iteration agents append evidence; the reducer reconciles it into registry, dashboard, and strategy views.\n17: \n18: ---\n19: \n20: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n21: \n22: The reducer turns append-only review evidence into the current findings registry, dashboard, and strategy state. It is the authority for derived outputs, not a second source of truth.\n23: \n24: ---\n25: \n26: ## 2. OWNERSHIP\n27: \n28: | Surface | Writer | Rule |\n29: |---------|--------|------|\n30: | JSONL state | Workflow plus validated iteration append | Append-only |\n31: | Findings registry | `scripts/reduce-state.cjs` | Regenerate from JSONL |\n32: | Dashboard | `scripts/reduce-state.cjs` | Regenerate from registry and latest events |\n33: | Strategy machine sections | `scripts/reduce-state.cjs` | Update from coverage and findings |\n34: | Iteration markdown | Review iteration agent | Write-once |\n35: | Review report | Synthesis | Final handoff |\n36: \n37: No agent should hand-edit reducer-owned derived state as the authoritative fix. Repair JSONL or rerun the reducer.\n38: \n39: ---\n40: \n41: ## 3. FINDINGS REGISTRY\n42: \n43: The registry groups findings into:\n44: \n45: - Active findings.\n46: - Resolved findings.\n47: - Repeated findings.\n48: - Blocked or disputed findings.\n49: - Claim-adjudicated severity changes.\n50: \n51: Each active finding needs severity, category, file:line evidence, finding class, content hash, first-seen iteration, and latest-seen iteration.\n52: \n53: ---\n54: \n55: ## 4. FAIL-CLOSED BEHAVIOR\n56: \n57: The reducer must refuse to publish derived state when JSONL is corrupt in strict mode. That protects dashboards and verdict previews from silently losing findings.\n58: \n59: Recovery order:\n60: \n61: 1. Identify the malformed JSONL line.\n62: 2. Repair or remove only the invalid appended record with an audit note.\n63: 3. Re-run the reducer.\n64: 4. Confirm registry and dashboard regenerate from the repaired log.\n65: \n66: ---\n67: \n68: ## 5. RECONSTRUCTION\n69: \n70: When derived files are missing but JSONL and iteration markdown exist:\n71: \n72: 1. Rebuild the registry from JSONL finding details.\n73: 2. Rebuild dashboard metrics from registry and latest convergence events.\n74: 3. Rebuild strategy from completed dimensions and active findings.\n75: 4. Re-run synthesis only after reducer outputs are consistent.\n76: \n77: If JSONL is incomplete but iteration files exist, recovery is manual and must be recorded before release readiness is claimed.\n78: \n79: ---\n80: \n81: ## 6. FINDING DEDUPLICATION\n82: \n83: The reducer deduplicates findings at synthesis time using a two-tier match.\n84: \n85: ### Two-Tier Match\n86: \n87: 1. **PRIMARY: content_hash** = `sha256(file_path + line_range + finding_type + normalized_description_80chars)`\n88:    - `file_path`: repo-relative path of the finding\n89:    - `line_range`: e.g., `\"42\"` or `\"42-56\"`\n90:    - `finding_type`: one of `security`, `correctness`, `performance`, `maintainability`, `test_quality`, `contract_safety`, `removal`\n91:    - `normalized_description_80chars`: first 80 characters of the description, whitespace-collapsed and lowercased\n92: 2. **FALLBACK (legacy records): file:line + normalized_title** - applied when one or both records lack a `content_hash`, preserving existing behavior unchanged.\n93: \n94: ### Synthesis Behavior\n95: \n96: When the same `content_hash` appears across iterations from different dimensions, synthesis collapses them to ONE entry with `dimensions: [<all dimensions that emitted it>]` rather than emitting multiple records. Records without `content_hash` fall back to `file:line + normalized_title`; no migration is required for existing JSONL state.\n97: \n98: ### Emission Requirement\n99: \n100: Every finding emitted into the JSONL delta (`findingDetails[]`) MUST include a `content_hash` field computed per the two-tier match. `reduce-state.cjs` reads this field for synthesis dedup.\n101: \n102: ---\n103: \n104: ## 7. RELATED RESOURCES\n105: \n106: - `scripts/reduce-state.cjs` is the reducer implementation.\n107: - `references/state/state_format.md` defines state records.\n108: - `references/state/state_outputs.md` defines operator-visible outputs.\n109: - `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md` defines STOP fields reducer views display.\n\n(End of file - total 109 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"Deep Review State Reducer And Registry\"\ndescription: \"Focused reference for reducer ownership, findings registry semantics, fail-closed behavior, and reconstruction rules.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review reducer registry\"\n  - \"review findings registry\"\n  - \"deep review reducer ownership\"\n  - \"review state reconstruction\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.11.0.4\n---\n\n# Deep Review State Reducer And Registry\n\nThe reducer is the single writer for derived review state. Iteration agents append evidence; the reducer reconciles it into registry, dashboard, and strategy views.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/references/state/state_reducer_registry.md","text":"---\ntitle: \"Deep Review State Reducer And Registry\"\ndescription: \"Focused reference for reducer ownership, findings registry semantics, fail-closed behavior, and reconstruction rules.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review reducer registry\"\n  - \"review findings registry\"\n  - \"deep review reducer ownership\"\n  - \"review state reconstruction\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.11.0.4\n---\n\n# Deep Review State Reducer And Registry\n\nThe reducer is the single writer for derived review state. Iteration agents append evidence; the reducer reconciles it into registry, dashboard, and strategy views.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nThe reducer turns append-only review evidence into the current findings registry, dashboard, and strategy state. It is the authority for derived outputs, not a second source of truth.\n\n---\n\n## 2. OWNERSHIP\n\n| Surface | Writer | Rule |\n|---------|--------|------|\n| JSONL state | Workflow plus validated iteration append | Append-only |\n| Findings registry | `scripts/reduce-state.cjs` | Regenerate from JSONL |\n| Dashboard | `scripts/reduce-state.cjs` | Regenerate from registry and latest events |\n| Strategy machine sections | `scripts/reduce-state.cjs` | Update from coverage and findings |\n| Iteration markdown | Review iteration agent | Write-once |\n| Review report | Synthesis | Final handoff |\n\nNo agent should hand-edit reducer-owned derived state as the authoritative fix. Repair JSONL or rerun the reducer.\n\n---\n\n## 3. FINDINGS REGISTRY\n\nThe registry groups findings into:\n\n- Active findings.\n- Resolved findings.\n- Repeated findings.\n- Blocked or disputed findings.\n- Claim-adjudicated severity changes.\n\nEach active finding needs severity, category, file:line evidence, finding class, content hash, first-seen iteration, and latest-seen iteration.\n\n---\n\n## 4. FAIL-CLOSED BEHAVIOR\n\nThe reducer must refuse to publish derived state when JSONL is corrupt in strict mode. That protects dashboards and verdict previews from silently losing findings.\n\nRecovery order:\n\n1. Identify the malformed JSONL line.\n2. Repair or remove only the invalid appended record with an audit note.\n3. Re-run the reducer.\n4. Confirm registry and dashboard regenerate from the repaired log.\n\n---\n\n## 5. RECONSTRUCTION\n\nWhen derived files are missing but JSONL and iteration markdown exist:\n\n1. Rebuild the registry from JSONL finding details.\n2. Rebuild dashboard metrics from registry and latest convergence events.\n3. Rebuild strategy from completed dimensions and active findings.\n4. Re-run synthesis only after reducer outputs are consistent.\n\nIf JSONL is incomplete but iteration files exist, recovery is manual and must be recorded before release readiness is claimed.\n\n---\n\n## 6. FINDING DEDUPLICATION\n\nThe reducer deduplicates findings at synthesis time using a two-tier match.\n\n### Two-Tier Match\n\n1. **PRIMARY: content_hash** = `sha256(file_path + line_range + finding_type + normalized_description_80chars)`\n   - `file_path`: repo-relative path of the finding\n   - `line_range`: e.g., `\"42\"` or `\"42-56\"`\n   - `finding_type`: one of `security`, `correctness`, `performance`, `maintainability`, `test_quality`, `contract_safety`, `removal`\n   - `normalized_description_80chars`: first 80 characters of the description, whitespace-collapsed and lowercased\n2. **FALLBACK (legacy records): file:line + normalized_title** - applied when one or both records lack a `content_hash`, preserving existing behavior unchanged.\n\n### Synthesis Behavior\n\nWhen the same `content_hash` appears across iterations from different dimensions, synthesis collapses them to ONE entry with `dimensions: [<all dimensions that emitted it>]` rather than emitting multiple records. Records without `content_hash` fall back to `file:line + normalized_title`; no migration is required for existing JSONL state.\n\n### Emission Requirement\n\nEvery finding emitted into the JSONL delta (`findingDetails[]`) MUST include a `content_hash` field computed per the two-tier match. `reduce-state.cjs` reads this field for synthesis dedup.\n\n---\n\n## 7. RELATED RESOURCES\n\n- `scripts/reduce-state.cjs` is the reducer implementation.\n- `references/state/state_format.md` defines state records.\n- `references/state/state_outputs.md` defines operator-visible outputs.\n- `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md` defines STOP fields reducer views display.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":109,"totalLines":109,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/references/state/state_reducer_registry.md","time":{"start":1783915559415,"end":1783915559449}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0df59b61eea8d697016a54642754608191acb2e0a12c66ebe3"}},"id":"prt_f59a739f6001FuDBOmbDMiOUDz","sessionID":"ses_0a65ac472ffeDn3G1fX5LbU2k8","messageID":"msg_f59a6ea830011kqj0WvDYGJREd"}}
