{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783915578591,"sessionID":"ses_0a65ac472ffeDn3G1fX5LbU2k8","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_cglH8Ls5BEyl1eY2kQ0gBIgd","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment/implementation-summary.md","offset":1,"limit":2000},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment/implementation-summary.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"Implementation Summary: sk-code Split-Doc Template Alignment\"\n3: description: \"Conformed all 163 mechanically-split reference/asset files under sk-code/{code-opencode,code-webflow,code-quality} to the create-skill asset/reference templates: snake_case renames, 5-field frontmatter + 4-part version, OVERVIEW wrapper, content preserved, every in-hub reference updated. Executed by GPT-5.6-sol-fast in an isolated worktree, orchestrator-verified per batch; 0 hyphenated names, 0 broken links to renamed files; committed + pushed to v4. Post-ship 10-iteration deep review (GPT-5.6-sol-fast HIGH) drove two P1 remediations: 21 code-webflow Purpose paragraphs de-duplicated from their H1 intro, and the broken-link completion claim narrowed to its true renamed-file scope.\"\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"019 summary sk-code split doc alignment\"\n6: importance_tier: \"important\"\n7: contextType: \"implementation\"\n8: _memory:\n9:   continuity:\n10:     packet_pointer: \"sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment\"\n11:     last_updated_at: \"2026-07-13T03:40:30Z\"\n12:     last_updated_by: \"claude-code\"\n13:     recent_action: \"Post-ship deep review remediation: F001 (21 Purpose de-dups) + F002 (link-claim narrowed)\"\n14:     next_safe_action: \"Terminal gates + xHigh verification re-review\"\n15:     blockers: []\n16:     completion_pct: 100\n17:     status: \"Complete\"\n18: ---\n19: # Implementation Summary\n20: \n21: <!-- SPECKIT_LEVEL: 2 -->\n22: <!-- SPECKIT_TEMPLATE_SOURCE: impl-summary-core | v2.2 -->\n23: \n24: ---\n25: \n26: <!-- ANCHOR:metadata -->\n27: ## Metadata\n28: | Field | Value |\n29: |-------|-------|\n30: | **Packet** | 019 — sk-code Split-Doc Template Alignment |\n31: | **Status** | Complete |\n32: | **Track** | sk-code |\n33: <!-- /ANCHOR:metadata -->\n34: \n35: ---\n36: \n37: <!-- ANCHOR:what-built -->\n38: ## What Was Built\n39: All 163 mechanically-split reference/asset `.md` files across the three sk-code surfaces conformed to the create-skill templates.\n40: \n41: | Surface | Files | Result |\n42: |---|---|---|\n43: | code-quality (assets) | 3 | conformed |\n44: | code-opencode (refs+assets) | 65 | conformed |\n45: | code-webflow (refs+assets) | 95 | conformed |\n46: | **Total** | **163** | **163/163 at 0 issues** |\n47: \n48: Each file: hyphen→underscore rename (snake_case), 5-field frontmatter + 4-part version, H1 + intro + `## 1. OVERVIEW` (Purpose/When-to-Use for refs, Purpose/Usage for assets), content sections renumbered (content preserved verbatim), and every in-hub reference to renamed files updated.\n49: <!-- /ANCHOR:what-built -->\n50: \n51: ---\n52: \n53: <!-- ANCHOR:how-delivered -->\n54: ## How It Was Delivered\n55: Serial GPT-5.6-sol-fast batches (opencode, --variant medium) in an isolated worktree, one subtree per batch (batches serialize on each surface's shared SKILL.md RESOURCE_MAP). The orchestrator verified each batch (validate_document 0 + full-hub broken-link scan) and committed the whole hub before dispatching the next. Every batch committed + pushed to v4.\n56: <!-- /ANCHOR:how-delivered -->\n57: \n58: ---\n59: \n60: <!-- ANCHOR:decisions -->\n61: ## Key Decisions\n62: - **Recurse into nested split dirs.** Verification caught GPT initially skipping nested `<lang>/quality_standards/` split dirs; every subsequent batch prompt made recursion explicit.\n63: - **Whole-hub staging.** Early per-surface `git add <surface>` commits dropped cross-surface reference-link fixes, leaving 2 broken links on v4; switched to staging the whole sk-code hub per commit and repaired them.\n64: - **snake_case per operator + 027.** Renames use underscore, aligning with the concurrent 027 naming migration (which had not covered these reference/asset split files).\n65: - **Post-ship deep review → two P1 remediations.** A 10-iteration GPT-5.6-sol-fast HIGH review (verdict FAIL, convergence 1.0) surfaced two confirmed P1s that the structural validators could not catch. F001: 21 code-webflow references had `### Purpose` copied verbatim from the H1 intro, violating the create-skill template's explicit non-duplication rule — each Purpose was rewritten to a section-derived, intro-distinct statement (0 duplicates across all 163). F002: the completion claim overstated \"0 broken links hub-wide\"; a fenced-code-aware scan found two pre-existing non-navigational artifacts (an illustrative `005-example.com` example path and a filename quoted in changelog prose, both authored by prior commits) — the claim was narrowed to its true renamed-file scope rather than editing correct documentation.\n66: <!-- /ANCHOR:decisions -->\n67: \n68: ---\n69: \n70: <!-- ANCHOR:verification -->\n71: ## Verification\n72: | Check | Result |\n73: |---|---|\n74: | validate_document.py on all sk-code ref+asset files | 163/163 at 0 issues |\n75: | Hyphenated split filenames remaining | 0 |\n76: | Broken relative .md links (whole hub) | 0 |\n77: | Edits under system-deep-loop/deep-alignment | None |\n78: <!-- /ANCHOR:verification -->\n79: \n80: ---\n81: \n82: <!-- ANCHOR:limitations -->\n83: ## Known Limitations\n84: - The surface SKILL.md files (code-opencode/code-webflow) still FAIL `package_skill.py --check` for a pre-existing reason (deliberate surface-packet headers, not the create-skill required-section names) — out of scope; per-file resource-doc conformance verified via validate_document.py instead.\n85: <!-- /ANCHOR:limitations -->\n86: \n87: ---\n88: \n89: ## Post-Completion Follow-Up\n90: - Sibling `sk-doc/017-smart-routing-mechanism-notes` completes Request 2.\n\n(End of file - total 90 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"Implementation Summary: sk-code Split-Doc Template Alignment\"\ndescription: \"Conformed all 163 mechanically-split reference/asset files under sk-code/{code-opencode,code-webflow,code-quality} to the create-skill asset/reference templates: snake_case renames, 5-field frontmatter + 4-part version, OVERVIEW wrapper, content preserved, every in-hub reference updated. Executed by GPT-5.6-sol-fast in an isolated worktree, orchestrator-verified per batch; 0 hyphenated names, 0 broken links to renamed files; committed + pushed to v4. Post-ship 10-iteration deep review (GPT-5.6-sol-fast HIGH) drove two P1 remediations: 21 code-webflow Purpose paragraphs de-duplicated from their H1 intro, and the broken-link completion claim narrowed to its true renamed-file scope.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"019 summary sk-code split doc alignment\"\nimportance_tier: \"important\"\ncontextType: \"implementation\"\n_memory:\n  continuity:\n    packet_pointer: \"sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment\"\n    last_updated_at: \"2026-07-13T03:40:30Z\"\n    last_updated_by: \"claude-code\"\n    recent_action: \"Post-ship deep review remediation: F001 (21 Purpose de-dups) + F002 (link-claim narrowed)\"\n    next_safe_action: \"Terminal gates + xHigh verification re-review\"\n    blockers: []\n    completion_pct: 100\n    status: \"Complete\"\n---\n# Implementation Summary\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment/implementation-summary.md","text":"---\ntitle: \"Implementation Summary: sk-code Split-Doc Template Alignment\"\ndescription: \"Conformed all 163 mechanically-split reference/asset files under sk-code/{code-opencode,code-webflow,code-quality} to the create-skill asset/reference templates: snake_case renames, 5-field frontmatter + 4-part version, OVERVIEW wrapper, content preserved, every in-hub reference updated. Executed by GPT-5.6-sol-fast in an isolated worktree, orchestrator-verified per batch; 0 hyphenated names, 0 broken links to renamed files; committed + pushed to v4. Post-ship 10-iteration deep review (GPT-5.6-sol-fast HIGH) drove two P1 remediations: 21 code-webflow Purpose paragraphs de-duplicated from their H1 intro, and the broken-link completion claim narrowed to its true renamed-file scope.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"019 summary sk-code split doc alignment\"\nimportance_tier: \"important\"\ncontextType: \"implementation\"\n_memory:\n  continuity:\n    packet_pointer: \"sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment\"\n    last_updated_at: \"2026-07-13T03:40:30Z\"\n    last_updated_by: \"claude-code\"\n    recent_action: \"Post-ship deep review remediation: F001 (21 Purpose de-dups) + F002 (link-claim narrowed)\"\n    next_safe_action: \"Terminal gates + xHigh verification re-review\"\n    blockers: []\n    completion_pct: 100\n    status: \"Complete\"\n---\n# Implementation Summary\n\n<!-- SPECKIT_LEVEL: 2 -->\n<!-- SPECKIT_TEMPLATE_SOURCE: impl-summary-core | v2.2 -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:metadata -->\n## Metadata\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| **Packet** | 019 — sk-code Split-Doc Template Alignment |\n| **Status** | Complete |\n| **Track** | sk-code |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:metadata -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-built -->\n## What Was Built\nAll 163 mechanically-split reference/asset `.md` files across the three sk-code surfaces conformed to the create-skill templates.\n\n| Surface | Files | Result |\n|---|---|---|\n| code-quality (assets) | 3 | conformed |\n| code-opencode (refs+assets) | 65 | conformed |\n| code-webflow (refs+assets) | 95 | conformed |\n| **Total** | **163** | **163/163 at 0 issues** |\n\nEach file: hyphen→underscore rename (snake_case), 5-field frontmatter + 4-part version, H1 + intro + `## 1. OVERVIEW` (Purpose/When-to-Use for refs, Purpose/Usage for assets), content sections renumbered (content preserved verbatim), and every in-hub reference to renamed files updated.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-built -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:how-delivered -->\n## How It Was Delivered\nSerial GPT-5.6-sol-fast batches (opencode, --variant medium) in an isolated worktree, one subtree per batch (batches serialize on each surface's shared SKILL.md RESOURCE_MAP). The orchestrator verified each batch (validate_document 0 + full-hub broken-link scan) and committed the whole hub before dispatching the next. Every batch committed + pushed to v4.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:how-delivered -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:decisions -->\n## Key Decisions\n- **Recurse into nested split dirs.** Verification caught GPT initially skipping nested `<lang>/quality_standards/` split dirs; every subsequent batch prompt made recursion explicit.\n- **Whole-hub staging.** Early per-surface `git add <surface>` commits dropped cross-surface reference-link fixes, leaving 2 broken links on v4; switched to staging the whole sk-code hub per commit and repaired them.\n- **snake_case per operator + 027.** Renames use underscore, aligning with the concurrent 027 naming migration (which had not covered these reference/asset split files).\n- **Post-ship deep review → two P1 remediations.** A 10-iteration GPT-5.6-sol-fast HIGH review (verdict FAIL, convergence 1.0) surfaced two confirmed P1s that the structural validators could not catch. F001: 21 code-webflow references had `### Purpose` copied verbatim from the H1 intro, violating the create-skill template's explicit non-duplication rule — each Purpose was rewritten to a section-derived, intro-distinct statement (0 duplicates across all 163). F002: the completion claim overstated \"0 broken links hub-wide\"; a fenced-code-aware scan found two pre-existing non-navigational artifacts (an illustrative `005-example.com` example path and a filename quoted in changelog prose, both authored by prior commits) — the claim was narrowed to its true renamed-file scope rather than editing correct documentation.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:decisions -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:verification -->\n## Verification\n| Check | Result |\n|---|---|\n| validate_document.py on all sk-code ref+asset files | 163/163 at 0 issues |\n| Hyphenated split filenames remaining | 0 |\n| Broken relative .md links (whole hub) | 0 |\n| Edits under system-deep-loop/deep-alignment | None |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:verification -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:limitations -->\n## Known Limitations\n- The surface SKILL.md files (code-opencode/code-webflow) still FAIL `package_skill.py --check` for a pre-existing reason (deliberate surface-packet headers, not the create-skill required-section names) — out of scope; per-file resource-doc conformance verified via validate_document.py instead.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:limitations -->\n\n---\n\n## Post-Completion Follow-Up\n- Sibling `sk-doc/017-smart-routing-mechanism-notes` completes Request 2.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":90,"totalLines":90,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment/implementation-summary.md","time":{"start":1783915578571,"end":1783915578587}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_078591be60775bef016a54643a514c81919cc3ce78f7429967"}},"id":"prt_f59a784ca001SDA6We7UzzqWAB","sessionID":"ses_0a65ac472ffeDn3G1fX5LbU2k8","messageID":"msg_f59a73ed9001dvJoau9vBj16oW"}}
