{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783916264470,"sessionID":"ses_0a65ac472ffeDn3G1fX5LbU2k8","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_emaF92Ebqfqf2QffrQSAv7yf","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/implementation/security_patterns/overview_and_checklist.md","offset":34,"limit":150},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/implementation/security_patterns/overview_and_checklist.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n34: \n35: ## 2. SECURITY CHECKLIST\n36: \n37: ### Input Validation & XSS Prevention\n38: \n39: **Sanitize User Input:**\n40: ```javascript\n41: // ✅ GOOD: Sanitize before display\n42: function sanitize_html(str) {\n43:   const div = document.createElement('div');\n44:   div.textContent = str;  // Automatically escapes HTML\n45:   return div.innerHTML;\n46: }\n47: \n48: const user_input = '<script>alert(\"XSS\")</script>';\n49: element.innerHTML = sanitize_html(user_input);\n50: // Result: &lt;script&gt;alert(\"XSS\")&lt;/script&gt;\n51: \n52: // ❌ BAD: Direct innerHTML without sanitization\n53: element.innerHTML = user_input;  // XSS vulnerability!\n54: ```\n55: \n56: **Use textContent When Possible:**\n57: ```javascript\n58: // ✅ GOOD: Use textContent for plain text\n59: element.textContent = user_input;  // Safe, no HTML rendering\n60: \n61: // ❌ BAD: innerHTML for plain text\n62: element.innerHTML = user_input;  // Unnecessary risk\n63: ```\n64: \n65: **Validate Input Format:**\n66: ```javascript\n67: // ✅ GOOD: Validate email format\n68: function is_valid_email(email) {\n69:   const email_regex = /^[^\\s@]+@[^\\s@]+\\.[^\\s@]+$/;\n70:   return email_regex.test(email);\n71: }\n72: \n73: if (!is_valid_email(user_email)) {\n74:   throw new Error('Invalid email format');\n75: }\n76: \n77: // ❌ BAD: Accept any input\n78: const user_email = input.value;  // No validation\n79: send_to_api(user_email);\n80: ```\n81: \n82: **Checklist:**\n83: - [ ] All user input sanitized before display\n84: - [ ] textContent used instead of innerHTML when possible\n85: - [ ] HTML entities escaped in user-generated content\n86: - [ ] Input format validated (email, phone, URL, etc.)\n87: - [ ] No eval() or Function() constructor with user input\n88: \n89: ### CSRF Protection\n90: \n91: **SameSite Cookies:**\n92: ```javascript\n93: // ✅ GOOD: Set SameSite cookie attribute\n94: document.cookie = \"session=abc123; SameSite=Strict; Secure\";\n95: \n96: // ❌ BAD: No SameSite attribute\n97: document.cookie = \"session=abc123\";  // Vulnerable to CSRF\n98: ```\n99: \n100: **CSRF Tokens:**\n101: ```html\n102: <!-- ✅ GOOD: Include CSRF token in forms -->\n103: <form method=\"POST\">\n104:   <input type=\"hidden\" name=\"csrf_token\" value=\"${csrfToken}\">\n105:   <input type=\"text\" name=\"username\">\n106:   <button type=\"submit\">Submit</button>\n107: </form>\n108: \n109: <!-- Server-side verification required -->\n110: ```\n111: \n112: **Verify Origin/Referer:**\n113: ```javascript\n114: // ✅ GOOD: Verify request origin (server-side)\n115: const allowed_origins = ['https://example.com'];\n116: if (!allowed_origins.includes(req.headers.origin)) {\n117:   throw new Error('Invalid origin');\n118: }\n119: ```\n120: \n121: **Checklist:**\n122: - [ ] SameSite=Strict set on cookies\n123: - [ ] CSRF tokens implemented for state-changing operations\n124: - [ ] Origin/Referer headers verified (server-side)\n125: - [ ] GET requests never modify state\n126: \n127: ### Injection Prevention\n128: \n129: **SQL/NoSQL Injection:**\n130: ```javascript\n131: // ✅ GOOD: Parameterized queries (server-side)\n132: const query = 'SELECT * FROM users WHERE email = ?';\n133: db.execute(query, [user_email]);\n134: \n135: // ❌ BAD: String concatenation\n136: const query = `SELECT * FROM users WHERE email = '${user_email}'`;\n137: // Vulnerable to SQL injection!\n138: ```\n139: \n140: **Command Injection:**\n141: ```javascript\n142: // ✅ GOOD: Validate and sanitize inputs\n143: const allowed_commands = ['start', 'stop', 'restart'];\n144: if (!allowed_commands.includes(user_command)) {\n145:   throw new Error('Invalid command');\n146: }\n147: \n148: // ❌ BAD: Execute user input directly\n149: exec(user_command);  // Command injection vulnerability!\n150: ```\n151: \n152: **Never Execute User Input:**\n153: ```javascript\n154: // ❌ BAD: eval() with user input\n155: eval(user_input);  // Extreme vulnerability\n156: \n157: // ❌ BAD: Function constructor\n158: new Function(user_input)();  // Also vulnerable\n159: \n160: // ❌ BAD: setTimeout/setInterval with strings\n161: setTimeout(user_input, 1000);  // Vulnerable\n162: ```\n163: \n164: **Checklist:**\n165: - [ ] Parameterized queries used (no string concatenation)\n166: - [ ] All inputs validated and sanitized\n167: - [ ] Never use eval(), Function(), or execute user input\n168: - [ ] Whitelist approach for allowed values\n169: \n170: ### Security Headers\n171: \n172: **Content Security Policy (CSP):**\n173: ```html\n174: <!-- ✅ GOOD: Strict CSP -->\n175: <meta http-equiv=\"Content-Security-Policy\"\n176:       content=\"default-src 'self'; script-src 'self' https://cdn.jsdelivr.net; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'\">\n177: \n178: <!-- ❌ BAD: No CSP or overly permissive -->\n179: <meta http-equiv=\"Content-Security-Policy\" content=\"default-src *\">\n180: ```\n181: \n182: **Other Security Headers:**\n183: ```html\n\n(Showing lines 34-183 of 263. Use offset=184 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\n## 2. SECURITY CHECKLIST\n\n### Input Validation & XSS Prevention\n\n**Sanitize User Input:**\n```javascript\n// ✅ GOOD: Sanitize before display\nfunction sanitize_html(str) {\n  const div = document.createElement('div');\n  div.textContent = str;  // Automatically escapes HTML\n  return div.innerHTML;\n}\n\nconst user_input = '<script>alert(\"XSS\")</script>';\nelement.innerHTML = sanitize_html(user_input);\n// Result: &lt;script&gt;alert(\"XSS\")&lt;/script&gt;\n\n// ❌ BAD: Direct innerHTML without sanitization\nelement.innerHTML = user_input;  // XSS vulnerability!","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/implementation/security_patterns/overview_and_checklist.md","text":"\n## 2. SECURITY CHECKLIST\n\n### Input Validation & XSS Prevention\n\n**Sanitize User Input:**\n```javascript\n// ✅ GOOD: Sanitize before display\nfunction sanitize_html(str) {\n  const div = document.createElement('div');\n  div.textContent = str;  // Automatically escapes HTML\n  return div.innerHTML;\n}\n\nconst user_input = '<script>alert(\"XSS\")</script>';\nelement.innerHTML = sanitize_html(user_input);\n// Result: &lt;script&gt;alert(\"XSS\")&lt;/script&gt;\n\n// ❌ BAD: Direct innerHTML without sanitization\nelement.innerHTML = user_input;  // XSS vulnerability!\n```\n\n**Use textContent When Possible:**\n```javascript\n// ✅ GOOD: Use textContent for plain text\nelement.textContent = user_input;  // Safe, no HTML rendering\n\n// ❌ BAD: innerHTML for plain text\nelement.innerHTML = user_input;  // Unnecessary risk\n```\n\n**Validate Input Format:**\n```javascript\n// ✅ GOOD: Validate email format\nfunction is_valid_email(email) {\n  const email_regex = /^[^\\s@]+@[^\\s@]+\\.[^\\s@]+$/;\n  return email_regex.test(email);\n}\n\nif (!is_valid_email(user_email)) {\n  throw new Error('Invalid email format');\n}\n\n// ❌ BAD: Accept any input\nconst user_email = input.value;  // No validation\nsend_to_api(user_email);\n```\n\n**Checklist:**\n- [ ] All user input sanitized before display\n- [ ] textContent used instead of innerHTML when possible\n- [ ] HTML entities escaped in user-generated content\n- [ ] Input format validated (email, phone, URL, etc.)\n- [ ] No eval() or Function() constructor with user input\n\n### CSRF Protection\n\n**SameSite Cookies:**\n```javascript\n// ✅ GOOD: Set SameSite cookie attribute\ndocument.cookie = \"session=abc123; SameSite=Strict; Secure\";\n\n// ❌ BAD: No SameSite attribute\ndocument.cookie = \"session=abc123\";  // Vulnerable to CSRF\n```\n\n**CSRF Tokens:**\n```html\n<!-- ✅ GOOD: Include CSRF token in forms -->\n<form method=\"POST\">\n  <input type=\"hidden\" name=\"csrf_token\" value=\"${csrfToken}\">\n  <input type=\"text\" name=\"username\">\n  <button type=\"submit\">Submit</button>\n</form>\n\n<!-- Server-side verification required -->\n```\n\n**Verify Origin/Referer:**\n```javascript\n// ✅ GOOD: Verify request origin (server-side)\nconst allowed_origins = ['https://example.com'];\nif (!allowed_origins.includes(req.headers.origin)) {\n  throw new Error('Invalid origin');\n}\n```\n\n**Checklist:**\n- [ ] SameSite=Strict set on cookies\n- [ ] CSRF tokens implemented for state-changing operations\n- [ ] Origin/Referer headers verified (server-side)\n- [ ] GET requests never modify state\n\n### Injection Prevention\n\n**SQL/NoSQL Injection:**\n```javascript\n// ✅ GOOD: Parameterized queries (server-side)\nconst query = 'SELECT * FROM users WHERE email = ?';\ndb.execute(query, [user_email]);\n\n// ❌ BAD: String concatenation\nconst query = `SELECT * FROM users WHERE email = '${user_email}'`;\n// Vulnerable to SQL injection!\n```\n\n**Command Injection:**\n```javascript\n// ✅ GOOD: Validate and sanitize inputs\nconst allowed_commands = ['start', 'stop', 'restart'];\nif (!allowed_commands.includes(user_command)) {\n  throw new Error('Invalid command');\n}\n\n// ❌ BAD: Execute user input directly\nexec(user_command);  // Command injection vulnerability!\n```\n\n**Never Execute User Input:**\n```javascript\n// ❌ BAD: eval() with user input\neval(user_input);  // Extreme vulnerability\n\n// ❌ BAD: Function constructor\nnew Function(user_input)();  // Also vulnerable\n\n// ❌ BAD: setTimeout/setInterval with strings\nsetTimeout(user_input, 1000);  // Vulnerable\n```\n\n**Checklist:**\n- [ ] Parameterized queries used (no string concatenation)\n- [ ] All inputs validated and sanitized\n- [ ] Never use eval(), Function(), or execute user input\n- [ ] Whitelist approach for allowed values\n\n### Security Headers\n\n**Content Security Policy (CSP):**\n```html\n<!-- ✅ GOOD: Strict CSP -->\n<meta http-equiv=\"Content-Security-Policy\"\n      content=\"default-src 'self'; script-src 'self' https://cdn.jsdelivr.net; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'\">\n\n<!-- ❌ BAD: No CSP or overly permissive -->\n<meta http-equiv=\"Content-Security-Policy\" content=\"default-src *\">\n```\n\n**Other Security Headers:**\n```html","lineStart":34,"lineEnd":183,"totalLines":263,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/implementation/security_patterns/overview_and_checklist.md","time":{"start":1783916264463,"end":1783916264469}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0902f2ecea87b42e016a5466e851cc8191981245d380050d42"}},"id":"prt_f59b1fbcf0012nHhVGpAqSSbAe","sessionID":"ses_0a65ac472ffeDn3G1fX5LbU2k8","messageID":"msg_f59b1bc23001BAtYDL9vznc1gE"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783916264513,"sessionID":"ses_0a65ac472ffeDn3G1fX5LbU2k8","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_MzYhzFTOnAMBR0YIuGBE3YSK","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/implementation/security_patterns/owasp_prototype_and_safe_access.md","offset":300,"limit":40},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/implementation/security_patterns/owasp_prototype_and_safe_access.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n300: | Old Pattern | New Pattern |\n301: |-------------|-------------|\n302: | `'key' in obj` | `Object.hasOwn(obj, 'key')` |\n303: | `obj.hasOwnProperty('key')` | `Object.hasOwn(obj, 'key')` |\n304: | `Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty.call(obj, 'key')` | `Object.hasOwn(obj, 'key')` |\n305: \n306: ### Checklist\n307: \n308: - [ ] Replace `in` operator with `Object.hasOwn()` for property checks\n309: - [ ] Replace `.hasOwnProperty()` calls with `Object.hasOwn()`\n310: - [ ] Validate user input before using as property lookup key\n311: - [ ] Combine with null-prototype objects for maximum safety\n312: \n313: ---\n314: \n315: ## 6. ANTI-PATTERNS\n316: \n317: **Never:**\n318: - ❌ Use innerHTML with unsanitized user input\n319: - ❌ Store passwords, tokens, or sensitive data in localStorage\n320: - ❌ Trust client-side authorization checks\n321: - ❌ Use eval(), Function(), or execute user input\n322: - ❌ Skip input validation (\"I'll sanitize on display\")\n323: - ❌ Ignore security headers (CSP, X-Frame-Options, etc.)\n324: - ❌ Concatenate SQL queries with user input\n325: - ❌ Use `in` operator for property checks with user input (prototype pollution)\n326: - ❌ Use `Math.random()` for security-sensitive randomness (predictable)\n327: - ❌ Create lookup objects without null prototype when keys are user-controlled\n328: - ❌ Use `.hasOwnProperty()` directly on objects (can be overridden)\n329: - ❌ Allow `__proto__`, `constructor`, or `prototype` as user-controlled keys\n330: \n331: ---\n332: \n333: ## 7. RELATED RESOURCES\n334: \n335: ### Reference Files\n336: - [implementation_workflows.md](../implementation_workflows/condition_based_waiting.md) - Defense-in-depth validation\n337: - [verification_workflows.md](../../verification/verification_workflows/gate_and_automated_options.md) - Security testing\n338: - See `mcp-chrome-devtools` skill for DevTools security audits\n339: \n\n(Showing lines 300-339 of 342. Use offset=340 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"| Old Pattern | New Pattern |\n|-------------|-------------|\n| `'key' in obj` | `Object.hasOwn(obj, 'key')` |\n| `obj.hasOwnProperty('key')` | `Object.hasOwn(obj, 'key')` |\n| `Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty.call(obj, 'key')` | `Object.hasOwn(obj, 'key')` |\n\n### Checklist\n\n- [ ] Replace `in` operator with `Object.hasOwn()` for property checks\n- [ ] Replace `.hasOwnProperty()` calls with `Object.hasOwn()`\n- [ ] Validate user input before using as property lookup key\n- [ ] Combine with null-prototype objects for maximum safety\n\n---\n\n## 6. ANTI-PATTERNS\n\n**Never:**\n- ❌ Use innerHTML with unsanitized user input\n- ❌ Store passwords, tokens, or sensitive data in localStorage","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/implementation/security_patterns/owasp_prototype_and_safe_access.md","text":"| Old Pattern | New Pattern |\n|-------------|-------------|\n| `'key' in obj` | `Object.hasOwn(obj, 'key')` |\n| `obj.hasOwnProperty('key')` | `Object.hasOwn(obj, 'key')` |\n| `Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty.call(obj, 'key')` | `Object.hasOwn(obj, 'key')` |\n\n### Checklist\n\n- [ ] Replace `in` operator with `Object.hasOwn()` for property checks\n- [ ] Replace `.hasOwnProperty()` calls with `Object.hasOwn()`\n- [ ] Validate user input before using as property lookup key\n- [ ] Combine with null-prototype objects for maximum safety\n\n---\n\n## 6. ANTI-PATTERNS\n\n**Never:**\n- ❌ Use innerHTML with unsanitized user input\n- ❌ Store passwords, tokens, or sensitive data in localStorage\n- ❌ Trust client-side authorization checks\n- ❌ Use eval(), Function(), or execute user input\n- ❌ Skip input validation (\"I'll sanitize on display\")\n- ❌ Ignore security headers (CSP, X-Frame-Options, etc.)\n- ❌ Concatenate SQL queries with user input\n- ❌ Use `in` operator for property checks with user input (prototype pollution)\n- ❌ Use `Math.random()` for security-sensitive randomness (predictable)\n- ❌ Create lookup objects without null prototype when keys are user-controlled\n- ❌ Use `.hasOwnProperty()` directly on objects (can be overridden)\n- ❌ Allow `__proto__`, `constructor`, or `prototype` as user-controlled keys\n\n---\n\n## 7. RELATED RESOURCES\n\n### Reference Files\n- [implementation_workflows.md](../implementation_workflows/condition_based_waiting.md) - Defense-in-depth validation\n- [verification_workflows.md](../../verification/verification_workflows/gate_and_automated_options.md) - Security testing\n- See `mcp-chrome-devtools` skill for DevTools security audits\n","lineStart":300,"lineEnd":339,"totalLines":342,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/implementation/security_patterns/owasp_prototype_and_safe_access.md","time":{"start":1783916264498,"end":1783916264512}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0902f2ecea87b42e016a5466e8533481918a64bd026ded5615"}},"id":"prt_f59b1fc2c001AHn7lxAYHe3qEk","sessionID":"ses_0a65ac472ffeDn3G1fX5LbU2k8","messageID":"msg_f59b1bc23001BAtYDL9vznc1gE"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783916264514,"sessionID":"ses_0a65ac472ffeDn3G1fX5LbU2k8","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_jJPd1gRqVezvHhBslnclNd0b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/shared/dev_workflow/automation_errors_and_compat.md","offset":235,"limit":40},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/shared/dev_workflow/automation_errors_and_compat.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n235: \n236: **3. Race Condition**\n237: ```javascript\n238: // Error: Intermittent failures\n239: // Cause: Code runs before dependencies ready\n240: \n241: // Solution: Use condition-based waiting\n242: await Promise.all([\n243:   domReady(),\n244:   waitForLibrary('Hls'),\n245:   waitForElement('[video]')\n246: ]);\n247: // Now safe to initialize\n248: ```\n249: \n250: **4. XSS Vulnerability**\n251: ```javascript\n252: // Risk: element.innerHTML = userInput\n253: // Cause: Unsanitized user data\n254: \n255: // Solution: Use textContent or sanitize\n256: element.textContent = userInput; // Safe\n257: // OR\n258: element.innerHTML = sanitizeHTML(userInput); // Sanitized\n259: ```\n260: \n261: **5. Memory Leak**\n262: ```javascript\n263: // Cause: Event listeners not removed\n264: \n265: // Solution: Clean up in destroy\n266: class Component {\n267:   constructor() {\n268:     this.handleClick = this.handleClick.bind(this);\n269:     element.addEventListener('click', this.handleClick);\n270:   }\n271: \n272:   destroy() {\n273:     element.removeEventListener('click', this.handleClick);\n274:   }\n\n(Showing lines 235-274 of 362. Use offset=275 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\n**3. Race Condition**\n```javascript\n// Error: Intermittent failures\n// Cause: Code runs before dependencies ready\n\n// Solution: Use condition-based waiting\nawait Promise.all([\n  domReady(),\n  waitForLibrary('Hls'),\n  waitForElement('[video]')\n]);\n// Now safe to initialize\n```\n\n**4. XSS Vulnerability**\n```javascript\n// Risk: element.innerHTML = userInput\n// Cause: Unsanitized user data\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/shared/dev_workflow/automation_errors_and_compat.md","text":"\n**3. Race Condition**\n```javascript\n// Error: Intermittent failures\n// Cause: Code runs before dependencies ready\n\n// Solution: Use condition-based waiting\nawait Promise.all([\n  domReady(),\n  waitForLibrary('Hls'),\n  waitForElement('[video]')\n]);\n// Now safe to initialize\n```\n\n**4. XSS Vulnerability**\n```javascript\n// Risk: element.innerHTML = userInput\n// Cause: Unsanitized user data\n\n// Solution: Use textContent or sanitize\nelement.textContent = userInput; // Safe\n// OR\nelement.innerHTML = sanitizeHTML(userInput); // Sanitized\n```\n\n**5. Memory Leak**\n```javascript\n// Cause: Event listeners not removed\n\n// Solution: Clean up in destroy\nclass Component {\n  constructor() {\n    this.handleClick = this.handleClick.bind(this);\n    element.addEventListener('click', this.handleClick);\n  }\n\n  destroy() {\n    element.removeEventListener('click', this.handleClick);\n  }","lineStart":235,"lineEnd":274,"totalLines":362,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/shared/dev_workflow/automation_errors_and_compat.md","time":{"start":1783916264505,"end":1783916264513}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0902f2ecea87b42e016a5466e853408191acb2df22a5f6f631"}},"id":"prt_f59b1fc33001IDzW75fxMANKOj","sessionID":"ses_0a65ac472ffeDn3G1fX5LbU2k8","messageID":"msg_f59b1bc23001BAtYDL9vznc1gE"}}
