KED\n\n- Packet-local continuity and deterministic corpus checks are available.\n- Iteration 1: a full Git-tracked corpus scan plus focused direct reads separated validator-clean mechanics from two semantic/order contract defects.\n- Iteration 2: exact target-root searches plus direct context reads distinguished intentionally unsafe counterexamples from recommendations and found no security regression.\n\n## 7. WHAT FAILED\n\n- Spec Memory context retrieval timed out twice; direct packet and target reads are authoritative fallback evidence.\n\n## 8. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n\n- Re-running or modifying the canonical review packet is out of scope for this detached lineage.\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n### Non-Markdown benchmark changes introduce executable behavior: ruled out by direct path-substitution diff. -- BLOCKED (iteration 2, 1 attempts)\n- What was tried: Non-Markdown benchmark changes introduce executable behavior: ruled out by direct path-substitution diff.\n- Why blocked: Repeated iteration evidence ruled this direction out.\n- Do NOT retry: Non-Markdown benchmark changes introduce executable behavior: ruled out by direct path-substitution diff.\n\n### The original 21-file exact Purpose duplication set remains active: ruled out by the current full-corpus scan; only F002 remains. -- BLOCKED (iteration 1, 1 attempts)\n- What was tried: The original 21-file exact Purpose duplication set remains active: ruled out by the current full-corpus scan; only F002 remains.\n- Why blocked: Repeated iteration evidence ruled this direction out.\n- Do NOT retry: The original 21-file exact Purpose duplication set remains active: ruled out by the current full-corpus scan; only F002 remains.\n\n### Unsafe snippets are promoted as valid guidance: ruled out by adjacent GOOD/BAD and checklist framing. -- BLOCKED (iteration 2, 1 attempts)\n- What was tried: Unsafe snippets are promoted as valid guidance: ruled out by adjacent GOOD/BAD and checklist framing.\n- Why blocked: Repeated iteration evidence ruled this direction out.\n- Do NOT retry: Unsafe snippets are promoted as valid guidance: ruled out by adjacent GOOD/BAD and checklist framing.\n\n### Validator failures explain F001/F002: ruled out because all 163 validator subprocesses exit zero. -- BLOCKED (iteration 1, 1 attempts)\n- What was tried: Validator failures explain F001/F002: ruled out because all 163 validator subprocesses exit zero.\n- Why blocked: Repeated iteration evidence ruled this direction out.\n- Do NOT retry: Validator failures explain F001/F002: ruled out because all 163 validator subprocesses exit zero.\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n\n## 10A. SATURATED / SWEPT DIMENSIONS AND EXPANSION FRONTIER\n- Completed pivots: 0\n- Failed pivots: 0\n- Audited overrides: 0\n- Swept: none yet\n- Pivot lineage: none yet\n- Remaining frontier: none recorded\n\n## 11. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n\n- None beyond the write-scope boundary.\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n## 11. NEXT FOCUS\ntraceability: replay `spec_code` and `checklist_evidence`, verify current completion wording against deterministic matrices, and adjudicate any contradiction between packet docs. Review verdict: PASS\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n\n## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n\n- Packet docs claim 163/163 target files pass structural validation, no hyphenated split filenames remain, and renamed-file references resolve.\n- A prior 10-iteration lineage found two P1 issues: 21 intro/Purpose duplicates and an overbroad broken-link completion claim.\n- The implementation summary records both remediations and requests an xHigh verification re-review.\n- `resource-map.md` is absent at initialization, so the source resource-map coverage gate is skipped.\n\n### Bounded Context Snapshot\n\n- Target pointers: packet docs plus sk-code reference/asset Markdown under code-opencode, code-webflow, and code-quality.\n- Behavior claims: five routing frontmatter fields plus four-part version, snake_case basenames, H1/intro/OVERVIEW structure, mode-specific OVERVIEW subsection, contiguous numbering, RELATED RESOURCES last, and in-scope links intact.\n- Reuse and conventions: create-skill `skill_reference_template.md`, `skill_asset_template.md`, and `validate_document.py`.\n- Review risks and gaps: semantic intro/Purpose duplication is not enforced by the structural validator; packet completion wording must match the exact link-scan scope.\n\n## 13. CROSS-REFERENCE STATUS\n\n| Protocol | Level | Status | Iteration | Notes |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| `spec_code` | core | pending | - | Verify requirements against target corpus. |\n| `checklist_evidence` | core | pending | - | Replay checked completion evidence. |\n| `feature_catalog_code` | overlay | notApplicable | - | Documentation conformance packet, no feature catalog claim. |\n| `playbook_capability` | overlay | notApplicable | - | Documentation conformance packet, no executable playbook capability. |\n\n## 14. FILES UNDER REVIEW\n\n| File or scope | Dimensions Reviewed | Last Iteration | Findings | Status |\n|---|---|---:|---|---|\n| Packet canonical docs | - | - | 0 | pending |\n| code-opencode references/assets | - | - | 0 | pending |\n| code-webflow references/assets | - | - | 0 | pending |\n| code-quality references/assets | - | - | 0 | pending |\n\n## 15. REVIEW BOUNDARIES\n\n- Max iterations: 4\n- Stop policy: max-iterations; convergence before iteration 4 is telemetry only\n- Convergence threshold: 0.1\n- Session lineage: `fanout-xhigh-b-1783915428096-y929h9`, generation 1, lineage mode new\n- Writable root: `.opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment/review/xhigh-verify/lineages/xhigh-b`\n- Target files and every path outside the writable root are read-only.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":133,"totalLines":133,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment/review/xhigh-verify/lineages/xhigh-b/deep-review-strategy.md","time":{"start":1783916459747,"end":1783916459750}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_052170248f677f6b016a5467ab88e88191a1902bc643360bb1"}},"id":"prt_f59b4f6a4001icT3v2yJegkhS7","sessionID":"ses_0a65ac472ffeDn3G1fX5LbU2k8","messageID":"msg_f59b48cd70019XQ6di6HN7J72s"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783916459928,"sessionID":"ses_0a65ac472ffeDn3G1fX5LbU2k8","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_DqXI2LhgR6kBzP8BhCfuoIlA","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment/implementation-summary.md","offset":60,"limit":30},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment/implementation-summary.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n60: <!-- ANCHOR:decisions -->\n61: ## Key Decisions\n62: - **Recurse into nested split dirs.** Verification caught GPT initially skipping nested `<lang>/quality_standards/` split dirs; every subsequent batch prompt made recursion explicit.\n63: - **Whole-hub staging.** Early per-surface `git add <surface>` commits dropped cross-surface reference-link fixes, leaving 2 broken links on v4; switched to staging the whole sk-code hub per commit and repaired them.\n64: - **snake_case per operator + 027.** Renames use underscore, aligning with the concurrent 027 naming migration (which had not covered these reference/asset split files).\n65: - **Post-ship deep review → two P1 remediations.** A 10-iteration GPT-5.6-sol-fast HIGH review (verdict FAIL, convergence 1.0) surfaced two confirmed P1s that the structural validators could not catch. F001: 21 code-webflow references had `### Purpose` copied verbatim from the H1 intro, violating the create-skill template's explicit non-duplication rule — each Purpose was rewritten to a section-derived, intro-distinct statement (0 duplicates across all 163). F002: the completion claim overstated \"0 broken links hub-wide\"; a fenced-code-aware scan found two pre-existing non-navigational artifacts (an illustrative `005-example.com` example path and a filename quoted in changelog prose, both authored by prior commits) — the claim was narrowed to its true renamed-file scope rather than editing correct documentation.\n66: <!-- /ANCHOR:decisions -->\n67: \n68: ---\n69: \n70: <!-- ANCHOR:verification -->\n71: ## Verification\n72: | Check | Result |\n73: |---|---|\n74: | validate_document.py on all sk-code ref+asset files | 163/163 at 0 issues |\n75: | Hyphenated split filenames remaining | 0 |\n76: | Broken relative .md links (whole hub) | 0 |\n77: | Edits under system-deep-loop/deep-alignment | None |\n78: <!-- /ANCHOR:verification -->\n79: \n80: ---\n81: \n82: <!-- ANCHOR:limitations -->\n83: ## Known Limitations\n84: - The surface SKILL.md files (code-opencode/code-webflow) still FAIL `package_skill.py --check` for a pre-existing reason (deliberate surface-packet headers, not the create-skill required-section names) — out of scope; per-file resource-doc conformance verified via validate_document.py instead.\n85: <!-- /ANCHOR:limitations -->\n86: \n87: ---\n88: \n89: ## Post-Completion Follow-Up\n\n(Showing lines 60-89 of 90. Use offset=90 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"<!-- ANCHOR:decisions -->\n## Key Decisions\n- **Recurse into nested split dirs.** Verification caught GPT initially skipping nested `<lang>/quality_standards/` split dirs; every subsequent batch prompt made recursion explicit.\n- **Whole-hub staging.** Early per-surface `git add <surface>` commits dropped cross-surface reference-link fixes, leaving 2 broken links on v4; switched to staging the whole sk-code hub per commit and repaired them.\n- **snake_case per operator + 027.** Renames use underscore, aligning with the concurrent 027 naming migration (which had not covered these reference/asset split files).\n- **Post-ship deep review → two P1 remediations.** A 10-iteration GPT-5.6-sol-fast HIGH review (verdict FAIL, convergence 1.0) surfaced two confirmed P1s that the structural validators could not catch. F001: 21 code-webflow references had `### Purpose` copied verbatim from the H1 intro, violating the create-skill template's explicit non-duplication rule — each Purpose was rewritten to a section-derived, intro-distinct statement (0 duplicates across all 163). F002: the completion claim overstated \"0 broken links hub-wide\"; a fenced-code-aware scan found two pre-existing non-navigational artifacts (an illustrative `005-example.com` example path and a filename quoted in changelog prose, both authored by prior commits) — the claim was narrowed to its true renamed-file scope rather than editing correct documentation.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:decisions -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:verification -->\n## Verification\n| Check | Result |\n|---|---|\n| validate_document.py on all sk-code ref+asset files | 163/163 at 0 issues |\n| Hyphenated split filenames remaining | 0 |\n| Broken relative .md links (whole hub) | 0 |\n| Edits under system-deep-loop/deep-alignment | None |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:verification -->\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment/implementation-summary.md","text":"<!-- ANCHOR:decisions -->\n## Key Decisions\n- **Recurse into nested split dirs.** Verification caught GPT initially skipping nested `<lang>/quality_standards/` split dirs; every subsequent batch prompt made recursion explicit.\n- **Whole-hub staging.** Early per-surface `git add <surface>` commits dropped cross-surface reference-link fixes, leaving 2 broken links on v4; switched to staging the whole sk-code hub per commit and repaired them.\n- **snake_case per operator + 027.** Renames use underscore, aligning with the concurrent 027 naming migration (which had not covered these reference/asset split files).\n- **Post-ship deep review → two P1 remediations.** A 10-iteration GPT-5.6-sol-fast HIGH review (verdict FAIL, convergence 1.0) surfaced two confirmed P1s that the structural validators could not catch. F001: 21 code-webflow references had `### Purpose` copied verbatim from the H1 intro, violating the create-skill template's explicit non-duplication rule — each Purpose was rewritten to a section-derived, intro-distinct statement (0 duplicates across all 163). F002: the completion claim overstated \"0 broken links hub-wide\"; a fenced-code-aware scan found two pre-existing non-navigational artifacts (an illustrative `005-example.com` example path and a filename quoted in changelog prose, both authored by prior commits) — the claim was narrowed to its true renamed-file scope rather than editing correct documentation.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:decisions -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:verification -->\n## Verification\n| Check | Result |\n|---|---|\n| validate_document.py on all sk-code ref+asset files | 163/163 at 0 issues |\n| Hyphenated split filenames remaining | 0 |\n| Broken relative .md links (whole hub) | 0 |\n| Edits under system-deep-loop/deep-alignment | None |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:verification -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:limitations -->\n## Known Limitations\n- The surface SKILL.md files (code-opencode/code-webflow) still FAIL `package_skill.py --check` for a pre-existing reason (deliberate surface-packet headers, not the create-skill required-section names) — out of scope; per-file resource-doc conformance verified via validate_document.py instead.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:limitations -->\n\n---\n\n## Post-Completion Follow-Up","lineStart":60,"lineEnd":89,"totalLines":90,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment/implementation-summary.md","time":{"start":1783916459924,"end":1783916459927}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_052170248f677f6b016a5467ab88f08191ac5481f1e9ffaa4f"}},"id":"prt_f59b4f6f0001FfOunqpc8az7lW","sessionID":"ses_0a65ac472ffeDn3G1fX5LbU2k8","messageID":"msg_f59b48cd70019XQ6di6HN7J72s"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783916460006,"sessionID":"ses_0a65ac472ffeDn3G1fX5LbU2k8","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_UzhYqmLWdczAML2qcmSnLSfP","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment/checklist.md","offset":47,"limit":50},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment/checklist.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n47: <!-- ANCHOR:testing -->\n48: ## Testing\n49: - [x] validate_document.py 0 issues on all 163 sk-code ref+asset files\n50: - [x] 0 hyphenated split filenames remaining\n51: - [x] 0 broken .md links to/among the renamed files — every conformed file and its referrers resolve\n52: - [x] 2 pre-existing non-navigational artifacts hub-wide are out of this packet's scope: an illustrative `005-example.com` example path (`webflow_constraints.md`) and a bare filename quoted in changelog prose (`changelog/v3.3.0.0.md`) — both predate this work, neither is a rename referrer\n53: <!-- /ANCHOR:testing -->\n54: \n55: ---\n56: \n57: <!-- ANCHOR:fix-completeness -->\n58: ## Fix Completeness\n59: - [x] All in-scope files/packets processed; no partial batch left uncommitted\n60: - [x] Every verification gate passed before the batch was committed\n61: <!-- /ANCHOR:fix-completeness -->\n62: \n63: ---\n64: \n65: <!-- ANCHOR:security -->\n66: ## Security\n67: - [x] Documentation-only; no executable/tooling changes; no new capabilities\n68: <!-- /ANCHOR:security -->\n69: \n70: ---\n71: \n72: <!-- ANCHOR:docs -->\n73: ## Documentation\n74: - [x] Batch commits carry evidence in messages; spec/plan/tasks/summary consistent\n75: <!-- /ANCHOR:docs -->\n76: \n77: ---\n78: \n79: <!-- ANCHOR:file-org -->\n80: ## File Organization\n81: - [x] Whole-hub staging captures cross-surface reference-link fixes (process fix after early per-surface staging dropped 2)\n82: - [x] Zero edits under system-deep-loop/deep-alignment\n83: <!-- /ANCHOR:file-org -->\n84: \n85: ---\n86: \n87: <!-- ANCHOR:summary -->\n88: ## Verification Summary\n89: \n90: | Category | Total | Verified |\n91: |----------|-------|----------|\n92: | sk-code ref+asset files conformed | 163 | 163/163 at 0 issues |\n93: | Hyphenated split filenames remaining | 0 | 0 |\n94: | Broken .md links to/among renamed files | 0 | 0 (2 pre-existing non-nav artifacts hub-wide out of scope) |\n95: | Batches committed + pushed to v4 | 11 | 11/11 |\n96: \n\n(Showing lines 47-96 of 98. Use offset=97 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"<!-- ANCHOR:testing -->\n## Testing\n- [x] validate_document.py 0 issues on all 163 sk-code ref+asset files\n- [x] 0 hyphenated split filenames remaining\n- [x] 0 broken .md links to/among the renamed files — every conformed file and its referrers resolve\n- [x] 2 pre-existing non-navigational artifacts hub-wide are out of this packet's scope: an illustrative `005-example.com` example path (`webflow_constraints.md`) and a bare filename quoted in changelog prose (`changelog/v3.3.0.0.md`) — both predate this work, neither is a rename referrer\n<!-- /ANCHOR:testing -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:fix-completeness -->\n## Fix Completeness\n- [x] All in-scope files/packets processed; no partial batch left uncommitted\n- [x] Every verification gate passed before the batch was committed\n<!-- /ANCHOR:fix-completeness -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:security -->\n## Security","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment/checklist.md","text":"<!-- ANCHOR:testing -->\n## Testing\n- [x] validate_document.py 0 issues on all 163 sk-code ref+asset files\n- [x] 0 hyphenated split filenames remaining\n- [x] 0 broken .md links to/among the renamed files — every conformed file and its referrers resolve\n- [x] 2 pre-existing non-navigational artifacts hub-wide are out of this packet's scope: an illustrative `005-example.com` example path (`webflow_constraints.md`) and a bare filename quoted in changelog prose (`changelog/v3.3.0.0.md`) — both predate this work, neither is a rename referrer\n<!-- /ANCHOR:testing -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:fix-completeness -->\n## Fix Completeness\n- [x] All in-scope files/packets processed; no partial batch left uncommitted\n- [x] Every verification gate passed before the batch was committed\n<!-- /ANCHOR:fix-completeness -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:security -->\n## Security\n- [x] Documentation-only; no executable/tooling changes; no new capabilities\n<!-- /ANCHOR:security -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:docs -->\n## Documentation\n- [x] Batch commits carry evidence in messages; spec/plan/tasks/summary consistent\n<!-- /ANCHOR:docs -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:file-org -->\n## File Organization\n- [x] Whole-hub staging captures cross-surface reference-link fixes (process fix after early per-surface staging dropped 2)\n- [x] Zero edits under system-deep-loop/deep-alignment\n<!-- /ANCHOR:file-org -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:summary -->\n## Verification Summary\n\n| Category | Total | Verified |\n|----------|-------|----------|\n| sk-code ref+asset files conformed | 163 | 163/163 at 0 issues |\n| Hyphenated split filenames remaining | 0 | 0 |\n| Broken .md links to/among renamed files | 0 | 0 (2 pre-existing non-nav artifacts hub-wide out of scope) |\n| Batches committed + pushed to v4 | 11 | 11/11 |\n","lineStart":47,"lineEnd":96,"totalLines":98,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment/checklist.md","time":{"start":1783916460001,"end":1783916460005}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_052170248f677f6b016a5467ab88f8819188c31e1143811ce6"}},"id":"prt_f59b4f79b001iYoTMNHmEO2z3C","sessionID":"ses_0a65ac472ffeDn3G1fX5LbU2k8","messageID":"msg_f59b48cd70019XQ6di6HN7J72s"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783916460049,"sessionID":"ses_0a65ac472ffeDn3G1fX5LbU2k8","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_irTkq9zqExzIH9MO6DxOjKUv","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/changelog/v3.3.0.0.md","offset":60,"limit":25},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/changelog/v3.3.0.0.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n60: ## Bug Fixes\n61: \n62: A multi-AI council audit (three lenses: maintainability, discoverability, symmetry) over the post-refactor tree surfaced 14 alignment findings. All 14 are resolved in this release.\n63: \n64: #### Restored a quick-reference file lost during refactor\n65: \n66: A python regex pass during the refactor accidentally deleted `webflow/javascript/quick_reference.md` from disk. The file was untracked at the time of the recovery so `git checkout HEAD --` did not restore it. Four other files were already cross-referencing the missing file. This release restores `webflow/javascript/quick_reference.md` (294 lines covering pre-commit checklist, code snippets like `waitForElement` and `waitForLibrary`, eleven one-liners for MutationObserver, IntersectionObserver, Lenis scrollTo, Motion.dev animate and inView, custom event dispatch, optional chaining, and form validation classes).\n67: \n68: &nbsp;\n69: \n70: #### Fixed stale references the bulk sweep missed\n71: \n72: The Phase 3 bulk sed pass missed six references in `webflow/shared/enforcement.md` because the sweep regex did not match the bare-filename references like `[code_quality_standards.md](code_quality_standards.md)` (no path prefix). This release replaces all six with the correct per-language tree paths and rewrites the surrounding \"Related Documents\" block as a five-link tree map.\n73: \n74: &nbsp;\n75: \n76: #### Fixed broken relative paths in moved files\n77: \n78: When `implementation/css_patterns.md` moved to `css/patterns.md`, three internal links continued pointing at the old `./` (same directory) path that no longer resolved (`./animation_workflows.md`, `./webflow_patterns.md` are in `../implementation/`, not the new `css/` location). Three more broken paths in `shared/dev_workflow.md` section 9 pointed at sibling files that actually live in `../implementation/` and `../debugging/`. This release fixes all six paths with the correct relative prefixes.\n79: \n80: &nbsp;\n81: \n82: #### Added inbound references to orphan deep-dive\n83: \n84: The 1,263-line `css/patterns.md` had zero inbound references after the move (orphan: a new contributor would never discover it through the reference tree). This release adds inbound links from `css/style_guide.md`, `css/quality_standards.md`, `implementation/webflow_patterns.md`, and `implementation/animation_workflows.md`.\n\n(Showing lines 60-84 of 212. Use offset=85 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"## Bug Fixes\n\nA multi-AI council audit (three lenses: maintainability, discoverability, symmetry) over the post-refactor tree surfaced 14 alignment findings. All 14 are resolved in this release.\n\n#### Restored a quick-reference file lost during refactor\n\nA python regex pass during the refactor accidentally deleted `webflow/javascript/quick_reference.md` from disk. The file was untracked at the time of the recovery so `git checkout HEAD --` did not restore it. Four other files were already cross-referencing the missing file. This release restores `webflow/javascript/quick_reference.md` (294 lines covering pre-commit checklist, code snippets like `waitForElement` and `waitForLibrary`, eleven one-liners for MutationObserver, IntersectionObserver, Lenis scrollTo, Motion.dev animate and inView, custom event dispatch, optional chaining, and form validation classes).\n\n&nbsp;\n\n#### Fixed stale references the bulk sweep missed\n\nThe Phase 3 bulk sed pass missed six references in `webflow/shared/enforcement.md` because the sweep regex did not match the bare-filename references like `[code_quality_standards.md](code_quality_standards.md)` (no path prefix). This release replaces all six with the correct per-language tree paths and rewrites the surrounding \"Related Documents\" block as a five-link tree map.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n#### Fixed broken relative paths in moved files\n\nWhen `implementation/css_patterns.md` moved to `css/patterns.md`, three internal links continued pointing at the old `./` (same directory) path that no longer resolved (`./animation_workflows.md`, `./webflow_patterns.md` are in `../implementation/`, not the new `css/` location). Three more broken paths in `shared/dev_workflow.md` section 9 pointed at sibling files that actually live in `../implementation/` and `../debugging/`. This release fixes all six paths with the correct relative prefixes.\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/changelog/v3.3.0.0.md","text":"## Bug Fixes\n\nA multi-AI council audit (three lenses: maintainability, discoverability, symmetry) over the post-refactor tree surfaced 14 alignment findings. All 14 are resolved in this release.\n\n#### Restored a quick-reference file lost during refactor\n\nA python regex pass during the refactor accidentally deleted `webflow/javascript/quick_reference.md` from disk. The file was untracked at the time of the recovery so `git checkout HEAD --` did not restore it. Four other files were already cross-referencing the missing file. This release restores `webflow/javascript/quick_reference.md` (294 lines covering pre-commit checklist, code snippets like `waitForElement` and `waitForLibrary`, eleven one-liners for MutationObserver, IntersectionObserver, Lenis scrollTo, Motion.dev animate and inView, custom event dispatch, optional chaining, and form validation classes).\n\n&nbsp;\n\n#### Fixed stale references the bulk sweep missed\n\nThe Phase 3 bulk sed pass missed six references in `webflow/shared/enforcement.md` because the sweep regex did not match the bare-filename references like `[code_quality_standards.md](code_quality_standards.md)` (no path prefix). This release replaces all six with the correct per-language tree paths and rewrites the surrounding \"Related Documents\" block as a five-link tree map.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n#### Fixed broken relative paths in moved files\n\nWhen `implementation/css_patterns.md` moved to `css/patterns.md`, three internal links continued pointing at the old `./` (same directory) path that no longer resolved (`./animation_workflows.md`, `./webflow_patterns.md` are in `../implementation/`, not the new `css/` location). Three more broken paths in `shared/dev_workflow.md` section 9 pointed at sibling files that actually live in `../implementation/` and `../debugging/`. This release fixes all six paths with the correct relative prefixes.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n#### Added inbound references to orphan deep-dive\n\nThe 1,263-line `css/patterns.md` had zero inbound references after the move (orphan: a new contributor would never discover it through the reference tree). This release adds inbound links from `css/style_guide.md`, `css/quality_standards.md`, `implementation/webflow_patterns.md`, and `implementation/animation_workflows.md`.","lineStart":60,"lineEnd":84,"totalLines":212,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-code/changelog/v3.3.0.0.md","time":{"start":1783916460042,"end":1783916460048}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_052170248f677f6b016a5467ab89008191a1760eda2470243b"}},"id":"prt_f59b4f809001Qz92pzXjY0eiBd","sessionID":"ses_0a65ac472ffeDn3G1fX5LbU2k8","messageID":"msg_f59b48cd70019XQ6di6HN7J72s"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783916460049,"sessionID":"ses_0a65ac472ffeDn3G1fX5LbU2k8","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_hQxFlnhAnyjprcoBhrPnqBwN","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/performance/webflow_constraints.md","offset":155,"limit":30},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/performance/webflow_constraints.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n155: ---\n156: \n157: ## 8. RELATED RESOURCES\n158: \n159: ### Internal References\n160: \n161: - [`../implementation/performance_patterns/overview_and_checklist.md`](../implementation/performance_patterns/overview_and_checklist.md) - Umbrella performance checklist + budgets + anti-patterns (high-level entry point)\n162: - [cwv_remediation.md](./cwv_remediation.md) - Core Web Vitals optimization patterns\n163: - [third_party.md](./third_party.md) - Third-party script optimization\n164: - [resource_loading.md](./resource_loading.md) - Resource hints and loading strategies\n165: \n166: ### Decision Records\n167: \n168: See [decision-record.md](/specs/005-example.com/024-performance-optimization/decision-record.md) for implementation decisions:\n169: \n170: - **DR-002**: TypeKit preconnect implementation\n171: - **DR-004**: GTM delay strategy (requestIdleCallback)\n172: - **DR-005**: Swiper CSS async loading pattern\n\n(End of file - total 172 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\n\n## 8. RELATED RESOURCES\n\n### Internal References\n\n- [`../implementation/performance_patterns/overview_and_checklist.md`](../implementation/performance_patterns/overview_and_checklist.md) - Umbrella performance checklist + budgets + anti-patterns (high-level entry point)\n- [cwv_remediation.md](./cwv_remediation.md) - Core Web Vitals optimization patterns\n- [third_party.md](./third_party.md) - Third-party script optimization\n- [resource_loading.md](./resource_loading.md) - Resource hints and loading strategies\n\n### Decision Records\n\nSee [decision-record.md](/specs/005-example.com/024-performance-optimization/decision-record.md) for implementation decisions:\n\n- **DR-002**: TypeKit preconnect implementation\n- **DR-004**: GTM delay strategy (requestIdleCallback)\n- **DR-005**: Swiper CSS async loading pattern","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/performance/webflow_constraints.md","text":"---\n\n## 8. RELATED RESOURCES\n\n### Internal References\n\n- [`../implementation/performance_patterns/overview_and_checklist.md`](../implementation/performance_patterns/overview_and_checklist.md) - Umbrella performance checklist + budgets + anti-patterns (high-level entry point)\n- [cwv_remediation.md](./cwv_remediation.md) - Core Web Vitals optimization patterns\n- [third_party.md](./third_party.md) - Third-party script optimization\n- [resource_loading.md](./resource_loading.md) - Resource hints and loading strategies\n\n### Decision Records\n\nSee [decision-record.md](/specs/005-example.com/024-performance-optimization/decision-record.md) for implementation decisions:\n\n- **DR-002**: TypeKit preconnect implementation\n- **DR-004**: GTM delay strategy (requestIdleCallback)\n- **DR-005**: Swiper CSS async loading pattern","lineStart":155,"lineEnd":172,"totalLines":172,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/performance/webflow_constraints.md","time":{"start":1783916460040,"end":1783916460049}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_052170248f677f6b016a5467ab88fc8191b448f5226a02cc15"}},"id":"prt_f59b4f7fb001Zk7wrAV2xgIA40","sessionID":"ses_0a65ac472ffeDn3G1fX5LbU2k8","messageID":"msg_f59b48cd70019XQ6di6HN7J72s"}}
