{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783916825185,"sessionID":"ses_0a65ac472ffeDn3G1fX5LbU2k8","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_WTJ4KR8YKTmLuLpHVbXmYrC3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/assets/scripts/README.md","offset":1,"limit":80},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/assets/scripts/README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"sk code assets scripts: Code README\"\n3: description: \"Code-facing README for .opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/assets/scripts.\"\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"sk-code assets/scripts\"\n6:   - \"code README\"\n7:   - \"opencode script maintenance\"\n8: importance_tier: normal\n9: contextType: implementation\n10: version: 1.0.0.8\n11: ---\n12: \n13: # sk code assets scripts\n14: \n15: Operator and maintenance scripts for this skill.\n16: \n17: ---\n18: \n19: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n20: \n21: ### Purpose\n22: \n23: This README documents the code-bearing folder `.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/assets/scripts` so operators can understand its role without opening every source file first. It follows the sk-doc skill README structure while staying focused on code navigation.\n24: \n25: ### Usage\n26: \n27: Use this file to identify the folder boundary, the likely verification path, and the local source files that need sk-code conventions. Keep behavior details in source comments and higher-level workflow details in the owning `SKILL.md`.\n28: \n29: ### Key Statistics\n30: \n31: | Metric | Value |\n32: |---|---:|\n33: | Code files | 3 |\n34: | README scope | Direct files in this folder |\n35: | Audit context | Internal validation notes |\n36: \n37: ---\n38: \n39: ## 2. QUICK START\n40: \n41: **Step 1: Confirm the owner.**\n42: \n43: Start with `.opencode/skills/sk-code/SKILL.md` for runtime routing and workflow boundaries.\n44: \n45: **Step 2: Inspect the local code.**\n46: \n47: ```bash\n48: rg --files .opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/assets/scripts\n49: ```\n50: \n51: Expected result: the command lists the source files summarized below.\n52: \n53: **Step 3: Verify changes.**\n54: \n55: Run individual scripts from the repository root with the documented arguments.\n56: \n57: ---\n58: \n59: ## 3. FEATURES\n60: \n61: | Feature | What It Does |\n62: |---|---|\n63: | Folder boundary | Documents direct code files under `assets/scripts`. |\n64: | sk-code alignment | Points reviewers at OpenCode naming, header, error-handling, and type-discipline checks. |\n65: | Verification handoff | Records the expected owner and audit packet for follow-up work. |\n66: \n67: ---\n68: \n69: ## 4. STRUCTURE\n70: \n71: | Path | Purpose |\n72: |---|---|\n73: | `test_verify_alignment_drift.py` | Unit-style coverage for alignment drift file discovery, language checks, severity behavior, and CLI exit codes. |\n74: | `verify_alignment_drift.py` | Recurring read-only alignment verifier for TypeScript, JavaScript, Python, shell, JSON, and JSONC files. |\n75: | `verify_stack_folders.py` | Verifies code-opencode language reference folders match the known language set and flags missing or orphan folders. |\n76: \n77: ---\n78: \n79: ## 5. CONFIGURATION\n80: \n\n(Showing lines 1-80 of 115. Use offset=81 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"sk code assets scripts: Code README\"\ndescription: \"Code-facing README for .opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/assets/scripts.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"sk-code assets/scripts\"\n  - \"code README\"\n  - \"opencode script maintenance\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.0.0.8\n---\n\n# sk code assets scripts\n\nOperator and maintenance scripts for this skill.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/assets/scripts/README.md","text":"---\ntitle: \"sk code assets scripts: Code README\"\ndescription: \"Code-facing README for .opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/assets/scripts.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"sk-code assets/scripts\"\n  - \"code README\"\n  - \"opencode script maintenance\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.0.0.8\n---\n\n# sk code assets scripts\n\nOperator and maintenance scripts for this skill.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nThis README documents the code-bearing folder `.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/assets/scripts` so operators can understand its role without opening every source file first. It follows the sk-doc skill README structure while staying focused on code navigation.\n\n### Usage\n\nUse this file to identify the folder boundary, the likely verification path, and the local source files that need sk-code conventions. Keep behavior details in source comments and higher-level workflow details in the owning `SKILL.md`.\n\n### Key Statistics\n\n| Metric | Value |\n|---|---:|\n| Code files | 3 |\n| README scope | Direct files in this folder |\n| Audit context | Internal validation notes |\n\n---\n\n## 2. QUICK START\n\n**Step 1: Confirm the owner.**\n\nStart with `.opencode/skills/sk-code/SKILL.md` for runtime routing and workflow boundaries.\n\n**Step 2: Inspect the local code.**\n\n```bash\nrg --files .opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/assets/scripts\n```\n\nExpected result: the command lists the source files summarized below.\n\n**Step 3: Verify changes.**\n\nRun individual scripts from the repository root with the documented arguments.\n\n---\n\n## 3. FEATURES\n\n| Feature | What It Does |\n|---|---|\n| Folder boundary | Documents direct code files under `assets/scripts`. |\n| sk-code alignment | Points reviewers at OpenCode naming, header, error-handling, and type-discipline checks. |\n| Verification handoff | Records the expected owner and audit packet for follow-up work. |\n\n---\n\n## 4. STRUCTURE\n\n| Path | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `test_verify_alignment_drift.py` | Unit-style coverage for alignment drift file discovery, language checks, severity behavior, and CLI exit codes. |\n| `verify_alignment_drift.py` | Recurring read-only alignment verifier for TypeScript, JavaScript, Python, shell, JSON, and JSONC files. |\n| `verify_stack_folders.py` | Verifies code-opencode language reference folders match the known language set and flags missing or orphan folders. |\n\n---\n\n## 5. CONFIGURATION\n","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":80,"totalLines":115,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/assets/scripts/README.md","time":{"start":1783916825172,"end":1783916825184}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_027a388b3d13796c016a5469181f2881918460ce14993dc7ed"}},"id":"prt_f59ba8638001k1gX88p3vPDMAx","sessionID":"ses_0a65ac472ffeDn3G1fX5LbU2k8","messageID":"msg_f59ba78b8001qCbY67GdNSPxJD"}}
